INSERT INTO `collections` VALUES (5,'Experiments with Farmers','Making research genuinely participatory is a complex process. Despite 30 years of ‘participatory’ research, this label often means farmers not contributing much more than free labour, with researchers doing everything else. \r\n\r\nWays of making research more participatory have been discussed from an institutional and a social perspective, so these videos focus on the technical issues surrounding truly participatory research. \r\n\r\nWe discuss the implications of farmers helping to design experiments (for example, by choosing treatments). We also explore ideas on participatory analysis and other activities that farmers can be involved in during the research.',1,'cover_images/collections/495fff9738625be64b8e0c84f491184d.jpg','2019-03-06 11:21:14','2019-07-11 14:46:25',1),(6,'Designing \"Right-N\" Trials - Webinar Series','These webinars were given by the RMS team as a response to a request from the West Africa Community of Practice (CoP), from the CCRP project.\r\n\r\nIn these 4 webinars, Ric Coe explores some of the key points about the process of designing \"Right-N\" trials with farmers, including what \"Right-N\" actually means!\r\n\r\nThe webinars include discussion of important practical considerations, how to answer important questions like what to measure, how to take measurements etc. \r\n\r\nRic also explains how vital your communication with the farmers is. If you are going to get farmers involved in managing your experiments, they have to be fully involved in each step, and have a feeling of ownership about the process. This is not easy to achieve, but it is possible with good communication. The final webinar in this series focuses specifically on this topic of communication.',1,'cover_images/collections/d92ebc0ef561688940c7e2dd43d30338.jpg','2019-03-06 11:34:40','2019-07-11 14:47:00',1),(7,'Frameworks for agroecology assessment','<p>A collection of resources that can be used to assess the use of agroecological principles. Useful to guide the work of planning, assessing or evaluating how agroecological principles or practices are being used.\r\n\r\nEach resource is also loaded to the resource bank as a separate trove.</p><p>Each resource is tagged into one of 3 categories:</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>frameworks</b> - the high level conceptual ideas\r\nto inform assessment methods<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b>methodology</b> - specific tools and methodologies\r\nfor assessment<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\">review&nbsp;</span>- review or suggestions for assessment</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>A listing of the resources in this collection can be found here:</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><a href=\"https://stats4sd.org/download/ae-frameworks-listing_2019-07-12_15:52:52/2019-07-12_15:52:52_ae-frameworks-collection.xlsx/AE%20Frameworks%20Collection.xlsx\" style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">https://stats4sd.org/download/ae-frameworks-listing_2019-07-12_15:52:52/2019-07-12_15:52:52_ae-frameworks-collection.xlsx/AE%20Frameworks%20Collection.xlsx</a></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><br><o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">A brief summary of each resource is provided, along with some editorial comments on the usage and relevance of the resources for a CCRP context.<br></p>',5,'cover_images/collections/0392f8c34a074e259c137904768f855c.jpg','2019-05-13 14:39:39','2019-07-12 15:57:35',0),(8,'CCRP Front Page Resources','This is a set of resources we promote on the main CCRP landing page. They are either resources developed specifically to support our work with grantees and the wider programme, or resources we feel would be useful for CCRP.',1,'cover_images/collections/2ea9a6fe7d5409db17ff06f96683782c.jpg','2019-05-15 05:38:31','2019-05-15 05:38:31',0),(9,'Análisis de textos usando R','Esta collección contiene la guía en español para RQDR, el video un webinario sobre análisis de textos y el archivo de PowerPoint usado para el webinario.\r\n\r\nEsta colección puede ser útil para personas que esten interesadas en una discusion de nivel intermedio sobre análisis de textos usando software, y que quieran probar usar la librería de R (RQDA) que hace ese tipo de análisis.',5,'cover_images/collections/31dfd319f11d025153b37ff407efc3d6.jpg','2019-07-09 11:06:02','2019-07-18 13:43:33',1),(10,'Digital Data Collection - Opportunities and Challenges','<p>This collection of resources covers a wide range of topics relating to digital data collection. These were originally developed for the <a href=\"http://drylandsystems.cgiar.org/\" target=\"_blank\">CGIAR Research Program on Dryland Systems</a> (CRP-DS) in 2015.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>In the videos, we interviewed a small team of data managers and statisticians, who reflect on their real-world experience of designing, building and using digital data forms to collect data across many projects, including for research and monitoring and evaluation purposes. The overall message is that digital tools for data collection are extremely powerful, but moving to use them instead of paper will (and should!) change the way you approach a collection project.</p><p><br></p>',1,'cover_images/collections/23ceb8b0160ef2f50dee0858cb3ffe2a.jpg','2019-07-24 14:49:51','2019-07-24 14:57:56',1),(11,'Statistical Good Practice Guides','<p>A series of guides covering the statistical aspects of research projects, aimed at research scientists who may not be very familiar with statistical concepts. An understanding of statistical ideas can save time and money for research projects, and result in more informative research outputs. <br></p><p>The guides were created by The University of Reading\r\nStatistical Services Centre, and were originally written as part of a \r\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \r\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \r\nstaff involved in the development and\r\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \r\nresearchers to\r\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.<br></p>',7,'cover_images/collections/055bb0ac9b764a362f81914207df3585.jpg','2019-10-10 16:27:05','2019-10-10 16:36:24',0),(12,'Webinars del Seminario Metodologías para la Investigación en Agroecología CCRP/CLACSO','<p>El seminario \"Metodologías para la investigación en agroecología\" consiste en una serie temas que\r\nse consideran útiles para iniciar una discusión sobre algunos enfoques y métodos de investigación\r\ncon estudiantes de doctorado y maestría en temas relacionados con la agroecología.\r\n</p><p>Los estudiantes para quienes se prepararon estos temas han recibido apoyo para su trabajo de\r\ncampo del Programa Colaborativo de Investigación de Cultivos (CCRP) Región de los Andes, de la\r\nFundación McKnight. Este apoyo incluye financiamiento para algunas actividades de campo, apoyo\r\nde tutores de CLACSO, financiamiento para el establecimiento de una comunidad de práctica de los\r\nestudiantes para intercambiar experiencias y la participación en una serie de seminarios, de los\r\ncuales este es el primero. El seminario también está abierto a otras personas que no han recibido\r\neste financiamiento pues tanto CLACSO como el CCRP quieren ser tan abiertos e inclusivos como sea\r\nposible.</p><p>El seminario incluye una serie de temas ligados a como pensamos o hacemos investigación. Algunos\r\nson más generales otros más específicos, pero todos están pensados para motivar discusión,\r\nreflexión y desafíos a la forma como conducimos investigación o tratamos los datos que se derivan\r\nde ella.<br></p>',5,'cover_images/collections/52f89bcf7778b40c28d56158c42b87d5.jpg','2019-10-15 16:53:51','2019-10-15 16:53:51',1),(13,'FRN Process - Collect and Handle Data','<p>FRN Process step 4 - </p><ul><li>Collect data</li><li>Test options</li><li>Manage data<br><br></li></ul>',7,'cover_images/collections/8538c99731075d68eb2966edd01d4949.jpg','2019-10-17 14:16:28','2019-11-20 10:17:51',0),(14,'FRN Process - Engage','<p><b>The \'engage\' step in the FRN process involves sharing the ideas and vision behind FRNs, engaging farmers in the process, and initiating working relationships with stakeholders and partners.</b></p> \r\n\r\n<p>In this section, you will find tools and guides aimed at helping understand and facilitate this process. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Highlights</h3>\r\n<p>Here are some of our favourite items from the collection:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nThe <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/resources/456\">Global Community Action Guides</a> contain a wealth of practical information that will be invaluable in setting up any participatory research group, and throughout the research process. It also provides further tools, templates and suggested activities that could be adapted for use with FRNs.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\nThe short guides from the Best Bets project cover topics throughout the FRN process. The ones at this step focus on <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/resources/280\">engaging and selecting farmers</a> to work with, and (in French only at the moment) <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/351\"> getting the community involved</a> and <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/resources/344\"> setting up an experiment</a>. \r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Get Involved</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'ve used any of the resources in this collection, we\'d love to know what you think! <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/resources/contact\">Get in touch</a> and tell us about your experience. \r\n \r\n</p><p>We\'re always looking to add to this collection. If you have any favourite guides, tools or other resources related to this step that you\'d like to share, <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/contact\">send us a message</a> to tell us about it. </p>',7,'cover_images/collections/05650fd55f96fda1fc9da2315a641c60.jpg','2019-10-17 14:26:39','2019-11-20 12:46:38',0),(15,'FRN Process - Prioritize','<p><b>This step is about understanding the local context, knowledge and values and combining that with global academic knowledge to identify options, facilitate decision-making and design research that takes into account the diverse range of interests, priorities and capacities within an FRN.\r\n\r\n</b></p> \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>Highlights</h3>\r\n<p>Here are some favourite items from the collection:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\nThe <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/resources/281\">FRN diagnosis and planning exercise</a> is a great example of an activity plan that can be adapted for use in different context, and which gives a good starting point for gaining an understanding of local context.\r\n</li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Get Involved</h3>\r\n<p>If you\'ve used any of the resources in this collection, we\'d love to know what you think! <a href=\"http://frn-data.test/contact\">Get in touch</a> and tell us about your experience. \r\n \r\n</p><p>We\'re always looking to add to the collection. If you have any favourite guides, tools or other resources related to this step that you\'d like to share, <a href=\"http://frn-data.test/contact\">send us a message</a> to tell us about it. </p>',7,'cover_images/collections/486a85533aa7060e8d61e72797672f3f.jpg','2019-10-17 14:35:41','2019-11-20 12:26:50',0),(16,'FRN Process - Design','<p><b>This step is about applying principles to facilitate the design of experiments for participatory research. </b></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It involves choosing technology and methodologies that are appropriate for farmer involvement, and building capacity to enable farmers to take an active role in research activities. Participatory experimental design must take into account the interests and priorities of farmers and community groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Highlights</h4>\r\nHere are some favourites from this collection:\r\n<ul><li>\r\n<a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/resources/333\">Principles of experimentation that farmers need to understand</a> - this resource concisely summarises the concepts farmers need to be familiar with to take part in research activities. It is up to individual groups to decide how best to facilitate an understanding of these principles within their network. If you have used this resource, we\'d be really interested to hear from you about how you applied it in an participatory research context. Use the <a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/contact\">contact form</a> to get in touch.  \r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<a href=\"https://staging-frn.stats4sd.org/resources/395\">Designing Participatory On-Farm Experiments: Resources for Training</a>: This handbook is a valuable source of information for training people with experience in research or extension on how to facilitate participatory research. It contains lots of useful training material on participatory experimental design.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Get Involved</h4>\r\n<p>If you\'ve used any of the resources in this collection, we\'d love to know what you think! <a href=\"http://frn-data.test/contact\">Get in touch</a> and tell us about your experience. \r\n \r\n</p><p>We\'re always looking to add to the collection. If you have any favourite guides, tools or other resources related to this step that you\'d like to share, <a href=\"http://frn-data.test/contact\">send us a message</a> to tell us about it. </p>',7,'cover_images/collections/bca30d9d8ed74c554ee9b71ddcab09bb.jpg','2019-10-17 14:39:12','2019-11-21 09:41:00',0),(17,'FRN Process - Observe','<ul><li>Thinking</li><li>Reflecting</li><li>Growing<br></li></ul>',7,'cover_images/collections/db2e8d41a4e4a97c20c23f5e6372ba14.jpg','2019-10-17 14:41:26','2019-10-17 14:41:26',0),(18,'FRN Process - Analyse','Analyse data<br>',7,'cover_images/collections/7ae1b5b7c379bf3968016a88e77e7a3b.jpg','2019-10-17 14:45:11','2019-10-17 14:45:11',0),(19,'FRN Process - Communicate','<ul><li>Share insights</li><li>Communicate (out and between)<br></li></ul>',7,'cover_images/collections/7b742d30673895665b8fe0f26da34d43.jpg','2019-10-17 14:52:04','2019-10-17 14:52:04',0),(20,'FRN Process - Implement Changes','<ul><li>Seek change in practice</li><li>Contextualized scaling</li><li>Market engagement</li><li>Learn / inspire others<br><br></li></ul>',7,'cover_images/collections/c3b9883a51629dc54643cd1c0b2a7257.jpg','2019-10-17 15:07:09','2019-10-17 15:07:09',0),(21,'FRN Process - Assess Impact','Assess impact,&nbsp; monitoring and evaluation.<br>',7,'cover_images/collections/eaf410c8ee7f8dc7eac2434919fe9350.jpg','2019-10-17 15:09:44','2019-10-17 15:09:44',0),(22,'Soil','<p>A collection of resources focused on soil health. This includes methods of maintaining, improving and protecting soil, and information about farmer-inclusive soil heath assessment and evaluation.</p>',7,'cover_images/collections/ecfeba492fa9c3e3cc1f411623c75be9.jpg','2019-10-22 11:23:13','2019-10-23 14:16:08',0),(23,'FRN - Agroecology Techniques','<p>Agroecology-related resources relevant to FRNs and those working with them. </p><p>Includes case studies and practical guides.<br></p>',7,'cover_images/collections/6d077ac1242276d85c33dac28737b44a.jpg','2019-10-22 11:36:38','2019-10-22 11:43:49',0),(24,'FRN - Pest Management','<p>Resources on weed and pest management, relevant for FRNs and those working with them. <br></p><p>Includes information on Striga, Fall Armyworm, and botanical pesticides.&nbsp; <br></p>',7,'cover_images/collections/16cb9ddcfde1eedf4177f293e264e837.jpg','2019-10-22 11:43:32','2019-10-22 11:43:32',0),(25,'Gender','FRN relsvant resources focused on women\'s equality and gender issues. <br>',7,'cover_images/collections/af4f00b52916067697a5ac7392b8bec9.jpg','2019-10-22 12:14:30','2019-10-22 13:36:49',0),(26,'Farmer Participation and Networks','A collection of more general guides and handbooks which provide an overview to participatory research, farmer research networks and community-led research.<br>',7,'cover_images/collections/987f168d6106a9c4d1016f98a3e98bfb.jpg','2019-10-22 12:32:27','2019-10-22 12:32:27',0),(27,'FRNs - Evaluation','Evaluation-related resources, including developmental evaluation. <br>',7,'cover_images/collections/efb56d6b070a9a588504bbe8040504d8.jpg','2019-10-22 12:47:17','2019-10-22 12:47:17',0),(28,'Local Knowledge','Resources that concern farmers\' local and traditional knowledge, and how this can be brought into dialogue with researchers and scientific knowledge systems. <br>',7,'cover_images/collections/4070ce3e10705749c64cc479e7a2963c.jpg','2019-10-22 12:53:10','2019-10-22 12:53:10',0);
