ts of using compost over manure. What is less known is that the \\r\\nmicro-organisms in compost attack striga seeds in the soil. Compost also\\r\\n decreases the amount of striga that will sprout, and reduces its \\r\\nnegative effect on cereal crops.<\\/p><p>The video also talks about how to make compost, showing how farmers in northeast\\r\\n Mali make compost as one of the strategies of integrated striga and \\r\\nsoil fertility management.<\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced for ICRISAT about the benefits of using compost over manure. What is less known is that the \\r\\nmicro-organisms in compost attack striga seeds in the soil. Compost also\\r\\n decreases the amount of striga that will sprout, and reduces its \\r\\nnegative effect on cereal crops.<\\/p><p>The video also talks about how to make compost, showing how farmers in northeast\\r\\n Mali make compost as one of the strategies of integrated striga and \\r\\nsoil fertility management.<\\/p>\",\"fr\":\"Une vid\\u00e9o r\\u00e9alis\\u00e9e pour l\'ICRISAT sur les avantages de l\'utilisation du compost sur le fumier. Ce que l\\u2019on sait moins, c\\u2019est que les micro-organismes pr\\u00e9sents dans le compost attaquent les graines de striga dans le sol. Le compost diminue \\u00e9galement la quantit\\u00e9 de striga qui va germer, ainsi que ses effets n\\u00e9gatifs sur les cultures de c\\u00e9r\\u00e9ales.<br><br>La vid\\u00e9o explique \\u00e9galement comment faire du compost, montrant comment les agriculteurs du nord-est du Mali font du compost l\'une des strat\\u00e9gies de gestion int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e de la striga et de la fertilit\\u00e9 des sols.\"}','2019-07-31 10:30:06','2019-07-31 10:30:06'),(568,'App\\Models\\Trove',326,7,'elements_files','{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\":\"[]\",\"fr\":\"[]\"}','2019-07-31 10:30:06','2019-07-31 10:30:06'),(569,'App\\Models\\Trove',326,7,'elements_urls','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/composting-beat-striga\"}]}','{\"en\":[{\"path\":\"https:\\/\\/www.accessagriculture.org\\/composting-beat-striga\"}],\"fr\":[{\"path\":\"https:\\/\\/www.accessagriculture.org\\/fr\\/du-compost-contre-le-striga\"}]}','2019-07-31 10:30:06','2019-07-31 10:30:06'),(570,'App\\Models\\Trove',327,7,'title','{\"en\":\"Video: Grow Row by Row\"}','{\"en\":\"Video: Grow Row by Row\",\"fr\":\"Cultiver ligne par ligne\"}','2019-07-31 10:32:12','2019-07-31 10:32:12'),(571,'App\\Models\\Trove',327,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced by ICRISAT about planting methods and practices that can be used to help manage striga. <\\/p><p>\\\"Farmers in northern Nigeria are changing the way they intercrop their \\r\\nsorghum and millet with cowpea. By planting both crops at higher \\r\\ndensities and in separate rows, and by applying some organic and mineral\\r\\n fertilizer, they harvest more and reduce damage by the parasitic weed \\r\\nstriga. It is one of the strategies of integrated striga and soil \\r\\nfertility management.\\\"<\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced by ICRISAT about planting methods and practices that can be used to help manage striga. <\\/p><p>\\\"Farmers in northern Nigeria are changing the way they intercrop their \\r\\nsorghum and millet with cowpea. By planting both crops at higher \\r\\ndensities and in separate rows, and by applying some organic and mineral\\r\\n fertilizer, they harvest more and reduce damage by the parasitic weed \\r\\nstriga. It is one of the strategies of integrated striga and soil \\r\\nfertility management.\\\"<\\/p>\",\"fr\":\"<p>Une vid\\u00e9o produite par l\'ICRISAT sur les m\\u00e9thodes et pratiques de plantation pouvant \\u00eatre utilis\\u00e9es pour aider \\u00e0 g\\u00e9rer la striga.<\\/p><p>\\\"Les agriculteurs du nord du Nigeria changent la fa\\u00e7on dont ils \\r\\nintercalent leurs sorgho et mil avec le ni\\u00e9b\\u00e9. En semant les deux \\r\\ncultures \\u00e0 plus haute densit\\u00e9 et dans des lignes s\\u00e9par\\u00e9es, et en \\r\\nappliquant un peu d\'engrais organiques et min\\u00e9ral, ils r\\u00e9coltent plus et\\r\\n r\\u00e9duisent les dommages caus\\u00e9s par le striga, une mauvaise herbe \\r\\nparasitaire. C\\u2019est une des strat\\u00e9gies de la gestion int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e du striga \\r\\net de la fertilit\\u00e9 du sol.\\\"<\\/p>\"}','2019-07-31 10:32:12','2019-07-31 10:32:12'),(572,'App\\Models\\Trove',327,7,'elements_files','{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\":\"[]\",\"fr\":\"[]\"}','2019-07-31 10:32:12','2019-07-31 10:32:12'),(573,'App\\Models\\Trove',327,7,'elements_urls','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/grow-row-row\"}]}','{\"en\":[{\"path\":\"https:\\/\\/www.accessagriculture.org\\/grow-row-row\"}],\"fr\":[{\"path\":\"https:\\/\\/www.accessagriculture.org\\/fr\\/cultiver-ligne-par-ligne\"},{}]}','2019-07-31 10:32:12','2019-07-31 10:32:12'),(574,'App\\Models\\Trove',58,7,'reviewer_id',NULL,'-1','2019-07-31 10:40:29','2019-07-31 10:40:29'),(575,'App\\Models\\Trove',58,7,'reviewer_id','-1',NULL,'2019-07-31 10:40:29','2019-07-31 10:40:29'),(576,'App\\Models\\Trove',59,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Examples<\\/span> of different graphical principles being used to maximise the potential of coveying information through data visualisation. Each example uses a real example, explains the rationale for choice of visualisation and provides R syntax of how to replicate a similar example.\"}','{\"en\":\"Examples of different graphical principles being used to maximise the potential of coveying information through data visualisation. Each example uses a real example, explains the rationale for choice of visualisation and provides R syntax of how to replicate a similar example.\"}','2019-07-31 10:40:35','2019-07-31 10:40:35'),(577,'App\\Models\\Trove',59,7,'reviewer_id',NULL,'-1','2019-07-31 10:40:35','2019-07-31 10:40:35'),(578,'App\\Models\\Trove',59,7,'reviewer_id','-1',NULL,'2019-07-31 10:40:35','2019-07-31 10:40:35'),(579,'App\\Models\\Trove',63,7,'description','{\"en\":\"The Sampling Decision Assistant was developed as a project for UNHCR in 2018. The tool is designed to help with the design of sampling schemes. It is for sampling that is done  to provide estimates of the values of characteristics of a population. Such studies are aimed at observing the population and measuring the factors of interest without trying to change anything. The decisions you make when designing this kind of study are about how you will sample the population. This type of study is used for things like profiling populations, setting baselines and assessing the value of indicators\\r\\n at midline or end-line points. \\r\\n \\r\\n It is a website that guides the user through a sequence of decisions that eventually build a sampling scheme. The process can be started, saved and continued on a different session. It contains help about how to use the tool, explanation about statistical issues that are of importance when designing a sampling scheme and a sampling glossary.\\r\\n \\r\\n The resulting set of decisions can be downloaded as a printable file.\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>The Sampling Decision Assistant was developed as a project for UNHCR in 2018. <\\/p><p>The tool is designed to help with the design of sampling schemes. It is for sampling that is done  to provide estimates of the values of characteristics of a population. Such studies are aimed at observing the population and measuring the factors of interest without trying to change anything. This type of study is used for things like profiling populations, setting baselines and assessing the value of indicators\\r\\n at midline or end-line points. \\r\\nThe decisions you make when designing this kind of study are about how you will sample the population.&nbsp; \\r\\n<\\/p><p> It is a website that guides the user through a sequence of decisions that eventually build a sampling scheme. The process can be started, saved and continued on a different session. It contains help about how to use the tool, explanation about statistical issues that are of importance when designing a sampling scheme and a sampling glossary.\\r\\n \\r\\n The resulting set of decisions can be downloaded as a printable file.<\\/p>\"}','2019-07-31 10:42:46','2019-07-31 10:42:46'),(580,'App\\Models\\Trove',63,7,'reviewer_id',NULL,'-1','2019-07-31 10:42:46','2019-07-31 10:42:46'),(581,'App\\Models\\Trove',63,7,'reviewer_id','-1',NULL,'2019-07-31 10:42:46','2019-07-31 10:42:46'),(582,'App\\Models\\Trove',66,7,'description','{\"en\":\"Data Tree is a free online course covering research data management, along with ways to engage and share data with business, policymakers, media and the wider public.  It was created particularly for postgraduates, PhD students and early career researchers who want to learn research data management skills, but it can be helpful for researchers, scientists and anyone working with data.\\r\\n\\r\\nStats4SD helped create Data Tree in cooperation with the Institute for Environmental Analytics (The IEA). The project was funded by the Natural Environment Research Council (NERC). \\r\\n\\r\\nData Tree Consists of 8 modules:\\r\\n\\r\\n1) Data Management: Context\\r\\n2) Data Management: Practicalities\\r\\n3) NERC\\r\\n4) Data Application: Analysis\\r\\n5) Data Application: Visualisation\\r\\n6) Working with Policy\\r\\n7) Working with Business\\r\\n8) Working with the Media and Public\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>Data Tree is a free online course covering research data management, along with ways to engage and share data with business, policymakers, media and the wider public.  It was created particularly for postgraduates, PhD students and early career researchers who want to learn research data management skills, but it can be helpful for researchers, scientists and anyone working with data.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>\\r\\nStats4SD helped create Data Tree in cooperation with the Institute for Environmental Analytics (The IEA). The project was funded by the Natural Environment Research Council (NERC). \\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Data Tree Consists of 8 modules:\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><ol><li>Data Management: Context<\\/li><li> Data Management: Practicalities\\r\\n<\\/li><li> NERC\\r\\n4) Data Application: Analysis\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Data Application: Visualisation\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Working with Policy\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Working with Business\\r\\n<\\/li><li>Working with the Media and Public<\\/li><\\/ol>\"}','2019-07-31 10:44:40','2019-07-31 10:44:40'),(583,'App\\Models\\Trove',66,7,'reviewer_id',NULL,'-1','2019-07-31 10:44:40','2019-07-31 10:44:40'),(584,'App\\Models\\Trove',66,7,'reviewer_id','-1',NULL,'2019-07-31 10:44:40','2019-07-31 10:44:40'),(585,'App\\Models\\Trove',66,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/data-tree_2019-05-10_15:50:06/data-tree_2019-05-10_15:50:06.zip','2019-07-31 10:44:42','2019-07-31 10:44:42'),(586,'App\\Models\\Trove',66,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/data-tree_2019-05-10_15:50:06/data-tree_2019-05-10_15:50:06.zip','2019-07-31 10:44:42','2019-07-31 10:44:42'),(587,'App\\Models\\Trove',67,7,'description','{\"en\":\"RHoMIS - the Rural Household Multi-Indicator Survey\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is a survey that uses standardised indicators to characterise rural households. The main advantage of Rhomis is that it offers the user a questionnaire that includes indicators that have been tested and have been accepted as useful by a large number of users and stakeholders. \\r\\n\\r\\nRhomis offers the ODK forms, the paper questionnaire and some R scripts to pre-process the data collected, but also there is the opportunity of support from the Rhomis team if the user accepts that the data they collect can become part of the multiple country database of rural households characterisitcs that Rhomis is building.\\r\\n\\r\\nAmong those indicators are the Food Insecurity Experience Scale (FIES), the Household Dietary Diversity Score (HDDS),  the Hunger and Food Insecurity Access Scale (HFIAS), Food Availabilty (FA), and the Progress out of Poverty Index (PPI). All of these have further documentation available from elsewhere and need to be adpated to the context where the survey is to be conducted\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is worth exporing their website for more information.\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>RHoMIS - the Rural Household Multi-Indicator Survey\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>This is a survey that uses standardised indicators to characterise rural households. The main advantage of Rhomis is that it offers the user a questionnaire that includes indicators that have been tested and have been accepted as useful by a large number of users and stakeholders. \\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Rhomis offers the ODK forms, the paper questionnaire and some R scripts to pre-process the data collected, but also there is the opportunity of support from the Rhomis team if the user accepts that the data they collect can become part of the multiple country database of rural households characteristics that Rhomis is building.\\r\\n\\r\\nAmong those indicators are the Food Insecurity Experience Scale (FIES), the Household Dietary Diversity Score (HDDS),  the Hunger and Food Insecurity Access Scale (HFIAS), Food Availabilty (FA), and the Progress out of Poverty Index (PPI). All of these have further documentation available from elsewhere and need to be adpated to the context where the survey is to be conducted.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>It is worth exporing their website for more information.<\\/p>\"}','2019-07-31 10:47:41','2019-07-31 10:47:41'),(588,'App\\Models\\Trove',67,7,'reviewer_id',NULL,'-1','2019-07-31 10:47:41','2019-07-31 10:47:41'),(589,'App\\Models\\Trove',67,7,'reviewer_id','-1',NULL,'2019-07-31 10:47:41','2019-07-31 10:47:41'),(590,'App\\Models\\Trove',67,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/rhomis-the-rural-household-multi-indicator-survey_2019-05-10_15:51:08/rhomis-the-rural-household-multi-indicator-survey_2019-05-10_15:51:08.zip','2019-07-31 10:47:42','2019-07-31 10:47:42'),(591,'App\\Models\\Trove',67,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/rhomis-the-rural-household-multi-i