os recursos consulte:<a href=\\\" http:\\/\\/ccrp.org\\/how-we-work\\/imep\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"> http:\\/\\/ccrp.org\\/how-we-work\\/imep<\\/a><\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p><p>A guide for monitoring and evaluation of research projects and development funded by the McKnight Foundation Collaborative Crop Research Program<span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Introduction to the Guide:<\\/span><\\/p><p>This guide is intended to orient project, regional,and program teams to the integrated monitoring, evaluation, and planning (IMEP) process of the Collaborative Crop Research Program (CCRP) at The McKnight Foundation. This framework is used to guide the program\'s strategies for grantmaking, grantee support, and shared learning at the project, regional,and program levels. For more information, see the<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ccrp.org\\/program-essentials\\/theory-change\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"> CCRP Theory of Change<\\/a>.<\\/p><p>The guide:<\\/p><ul><li>defines integrated monitoring, evaluation, and planning in the CCRP<\\/li><li>explains the theory behind the approach, and <br><\\/li><li>outlines how project, regional,and program teams use IMEP, including the documents that project teams produce as part of the grant implementation process.<\\/li><\\/ul><p>This document is one of many CCRP resources available to support project and regional teams in working efficiently and effectively. For other resources see: <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ccrp.org\\/how-we-work\\/imep\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">http:\\/\\/ccrp.org\\/how-we-work\\/imep<\\/a><\\/p>\"}','2019-08-15 15:08:25','2019-08-15 15:08:25'),(1048,'App\\Models\\Trove',369,7,'title','{\"en\":\"CCRP Integrated Monitoring,  Evaluation, and Planning (IMEP) Handbook\"}','{\"en\":\"CCRP Integrated Monitoring,  Evaluation, and Planning (IMEP) Handbook\",\"es\":\"Gu\\u00eda de Monitoreo, Evaluacion y Planificacion Integrado (MEPI) para la CCRP\"}','2019-08-15 15:10:24','2019-