Some Biometric Guidelines\"}','2019-10-10 11:45:18','2019-10-10 11:45:18'),(1735,'App\\Models\\Trove',439,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23.zip','2019-10-10 11:57:26','2019-10-10 11:57:26'),(1736,'App\\Models\\Trove',440,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/statistical-guides-using-excel-for-statistics-tips-and-warnings_2019-10-10_12:24:14/statistical-guides-using-excel-for-statistics-tips-and-warnings_2019-10-10_12:24:14.zip','2019-10-10 12:24:16','2019-10-10 12:24:16'),(1737,'App\\Models\\Trove',441,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_13:57:37/writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_13:57:37.zip','2019-10-10 13:57:40','2019-10-10 13:57:40'),(1738,'App\\Models\\Trove',441,7,'title','{\"en\":\"Writing up Research: A statistical perspective\"}','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Writing up Research: A statistical perspective\"}','2019-10-10 14:01:43','2019-10-10 14:01:43'),(1739,'App\\Models\\Trove',441,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p><p>A guide on how to write up a data analysis for data-related research work, aimed at research scientists who may not be experienced users of statistics. It could also be useful for a more experiences researcher writing up results from studies involving multidisciplinary teams and objectives.<br><\\/p>The guide is focused on natural resources research, but the general principles are also relevant in other types of research. The aim is to\\r\\nprovide guidance on how to report results of investigations in a way that clearly\\r\\ndemonstrates the evidence base for research recommendations. <\\/p><p>This guide was produced by the Statistical Services Centre of the University of Reading with funding from DFID\'s Forestry Research Programme (FRP), Project ZF0183, as part of work to support research scientists at DFID with the statistical aspects of research projects. <br><\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p><\\/p><p>A guide on how to write up a data analysis for data-related research work, aimed at research scientists who may not be experienced users of statistics. It could also be useful for a more experiences researcher writing up results from studies involving multidisciplinary teams and objectives.<br><\\/p>The guide is focused on natural resources research, but the general principles are also relevant in other types of research. The aim is to\\r\\nprovide guidance on how to report results of investigations in a way that clearly\\r\\ndemonstrates the evidence base for research recommendations. <p><\\/p><p>This guide was produced by the Statistical Services Centre of the University of Reading with funding from DFID\'s Forestry Research Programme (FRP), Project ZF0183, as part of work to support research scientists at DFID with the statistical aspects of research projects. <br><\\/p>\"}','2019-10-10 14:01:43','2019-10-10 14:01:43'),(1740,'App\\Models\\Trove',442,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/statistical-guides-writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_14:35:01/statistical-guides-writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_14:35:01.zip','2019-10-10 14:35:03','2019-10-10 14:35:03'),(1741,'App\\Models\\Trove',439,7,'title','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Statistical Guidelines for Natural Resources Projects\"}','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Statistical Guidelines for Natural Resources Projects\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos Estad\\u00edsticos para Proyectos de Recursos Naturales\"}','2019-10-10 15:01:07','2019-10-10 15:01:07'),(1742,'App\\Models\\Trove',439,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>This is the first in the series of guides aimed at supporting staff involved in research projects to identify their biometric or statistical needs. This is an introductory guide, and provides a more general overview of the areas of a research project where an understanding of statistical ideas is important.<br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">From the introduction:<\\/span><\\/p><p>\\\"Without sufficient confidence in statistics, researchers plan designs that are often conservative, primarily to ensure a simple analysis. While this is sometimes appropriate, simple improvements can often result in more informative experiments, or surveys, for the same cost. Measurements may be made that are inappropriate for the objectives of the study, and are subsequently not analysed. Data entry can become a very time-consuming part of the study if it is not planned in advance. The analysis may be rushed, using inappropriate software, because of the pressure to produce results quickly. The study is then concluded, with the realisation that there is much more that can still be learned from the data. However, funding is at an end, and problems in the data management have made it difficult to allow easy access to the data, even for future researchers within the country where the study was made.<br>In this guide we consider these stages, from planning to presentation, in turn. Its aim is to encourage the researcher to think about the crucial aspects of planning, analysing and interpreting data.\\\"<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<br><br><\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>This is the first in the series of guides aimed at supporting staff involved in research projects to identify their biometric or statistical needs. This is an introductory guide, and provides a more general overview of the areas of a research project where an understanding of statistical ideas is important.<br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">From the introduction:<\\/span><\\/p><p>\\\"Without sufficient confidence in statistics, researchers plan designs that are often conservative, primarily to ensure a simple analysis. While this is sometimes appropriate, simple improvements can often result in more informative experiments, or surveys, for the same cost. Measurements may be made that are inappropriate for the objectives of the study, and are subsequently not analysed. Data entry can become a very time-consuming part of the study if it is not planned in advance. The analysis may be rushed, using inappropriate software, because of the pressure to produce results quickly. The study is then concluded, with the realisation that there is much more that can still be learned from the data. However, funding is at an end, and problems in the data management have made it difficult to allow easy access to the data, even for future researchers within the country where the study was made.<br>In this guide we consider these stages, from planning to presentation, in turn. Its aim is to encourage the researcher to think about the crucial aspects of planning, analysing and interpreting data.\\\"<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<br><br><\\/p>\",\"es\":\"<p>Esta es la primera de la serie de gu\\u00edas destinadas a apoyar al personal involucrado en proyectos de investigaci\\u00f3n para identificar sus necesidades biom\\u00e9tricas o estad\\u00edsticas. Esta es una gu\\u00eda introductoria y proporciona una visi\\u00f3n general m\\u00e1s general de las \\u00e1reas de un proyecto de investigaci\\u00f3n donde es importante comprender las ideas estad\\u00edsticas.<\\/p><p>De la introducci\\u00f3n<\\/p><p>\\\"Sin suficiente confianza en la estad\\u00edstica, los investigadores usan a menudo dise\\u00f1os conservadores, fundamentalmente para asegurarse un an\\u00e1lisis simple. Aunque esto es algunas veces apropiado, la introducci\\u00f3n de mejoras sencillas pueden resultar en encuestas o experimentos m\\u00e1s informativos por el mismo costo. Por ejemplo, se pueden tomar medidas que no son adecuadas a los objetivos del estudio y en consecuencia, no son posteriormente analizadas. La recolecci\\u00f3n de datos puede llegar a requerir una parte importante del tiempo dedicado al estudio si ello no se planifica adecuadamente con anterioridad. El an\\u00e1lisis puede ser apresurado, usando programas inform\\u00e1ticos inapropiados, debido a la presi\\u00f3n de producir resultados r\\u00e1pidamente. El estudio se concluye de esa forma, con el convencimiento de que a\\u00fan puede aprenderse de los datos, pero ya est\\u00e1 por agotarse el financiamiento y los problemas con el manejo de los datos hacen dif\\u00edcil su acceso a\\u00fan para futuros investigadores dentro del mismo pa\\u00eds donde fue hecho el estudio.<br>En la presente gu\\u00eda consideramos esas etapas, desde la planificaci\\u00f3n hasta la presentaci\\u00f3n. Su objetivo es animar al investigador a pensar acerca de los aspectos cruciales de la planificaci\\u00f3n, el an\\u00e1lisis y la interpretaci\\u00f3n de los datos.\\\"<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>El SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC.<\\/p>\"}','2019-10-10 15:01:07','2019-10-10 15:01:07'),(1743,'App\\Models\\Trove',439,7,'elements_files','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23\\\\\\/2019-10-10_11:57:23_statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_11:57:23_statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Statistical_Guidelines_for_Natural_Resources_Projects.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":182432,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23\\\\\\/2019-10-10_11:57:23_statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_11:57:23_statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Statistical_Guidelines_for_Natural_Resources_Projects.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":182432,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\",\"es\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23\\\\\\/2019-10-10_15:01:07_guia1.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:01:07_guia1.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia1.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":117330,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','2019-10-10 15:01:07','2019-10-10 15:01:07'),(1744,'App\\Models\\Trove',439,7,'elements_urls','{\"en\":null}','{\"es\":null}','2019-10-10 15:01:07','2019-10-10 15:01:07'),(1745,'App\\Models\\Trove',443,NULL,'full_download',NULL,'files/lineamientos-para-archivo-de-datos-lecciones-de-un-estudio-de-caso_2019-10-10_15:13:40/lineamientos-para-archivo-de-datos-lecciones-de-un-estudio-de-caso_2019-10-10_15:13:40.zip','2019-10-10 15:13:42','2019-10-10 15:13:42'),(1746,'App\\Models\\Trove',402,7,'title','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Data Management Guidelines for Experimental Projects\"}','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Data Management Guidelines for Experimental Projects\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos para el manejo de datos de proyectos experimentales\"}','2019-10-10 15:32:19','2019-10-10 15:32:19'),(1747,'App\\Models\\Trove',402,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on managing data for research projects. Planning the data management aspects of a project from the outset helps avoid problems later on.<\\/p><p> \\\"Research projects often involve the collection of a large volume of data. The data\\r\\nhave then to be processed and analysed, with results and summaries being prepared for\\r\\npublication in some form. For this sequence to proceed smoothly, the project requires\\r\\na well-defined system of data management. This booklet gives some guidelines on the\\r\\ncomponents of such a system.\\\"\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on managing data for research projects. Planning the data management aspects of a project from the outset helps avoid problems later on.<\\/p><p> \\\"Research projects often involve the collection of a large volume of data. The data\\r\\nhave then to be processed and analysed, with results and summaries being prepared for\\r\\npublication in some form. For this sequence to proceed smoothly, the project requires\\r\\na well-defined system of data management. This booklet gives some guidelines on the\\r\\ncomponents of such a system.\\\"\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"es\":\"<p>Un folleto que proporciona orientaci\\u00f3n sobre la gesti\\u00f3n de datos para proyectos de investigaci\\u00f3n. Planificar los aspectos de gesti\\u00f3n de datos de un proyecto desde el principio ayuda a evitar problemas m\\u00e1s adelante.<\\/p><p>\\\"Los proyectos de investigacio\\u0301n frecuentemente comprenden la recoleccio\\u0301n de grandes volu\\u0301menes de datos. E\\u0301stos tienen que ser luego procesados y analizados y los resultados y si\\u0301ntesis deben ser preparados para su publicacio\\u0301n en algu\\u0301n formato. Para que e\\u0301sta secuencia ocurra de manera a\\u0301gil, el proyecto requiere un sistema de manejo de datos bien definido. La presente publicacio\\u0301n ofrece algunas gui\\u0301as sobre los componentes de tal sistema.\\\"<br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>El SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}','2019-10-10 15:32:19','2019-10-10 15:32:19'),(1748,'App\\Models\\Trove',402,7,'elements_files','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30\\\\\\/2019-08-21_09:36:30_data-management-guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_09:36:30_data-management-guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Data_Management_Guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":45008,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30\\\\\\/2019-08-21_09:36:30_data-management-guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_09:36:30_data-management-guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Data_Management_Guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":45008,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\",\"es\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30\\\\\\/2019-10-10_15:32:19_guia3.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:32:19_guia3.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia3.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":194897,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','2019-10-10 15:32:19','2019-10-10 15:32:19'),(1749,'App\\Models\\Trove',402,7,'elements_urls','{\"en\":null}','{\"es\":null}','2019-10-10 15:32:19','2019-10-10 15:32:19'),(1750,'App\\Models\\Trove',410,7,'title','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: On-Farm Trials \\u2013 Some Biometric Guidelines\"}','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: On-Farm Trials \\u2013 Some Biometric Guidelines\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos para experimentaci\\u00f3n en fincas de productores\"}','2019-10-10 15:39:22','2019-10-10 15:39:22'),(1751,'App\\Models\\Trove',410,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on how to design and conduct an on-farm experiment with the participation of farmers. Includes information about setting objectives, selecting farms to involve, choosing treatments and units, measurements and analysis of results. <br><\\/p><p>From the introduction:<\\/p><p>\\\"Farmer-participatory research trials have rapidly gained popularity in the past few\\r\\nyears with due consideration being given to the knowledge, problems and priorities of\\r\\nfarming families. The move towards participatory on-farm research means that many\\r\\nresearchers, such as breeders and agronomists, who have been trained in techniques of\\r\\non-station research, are now under pressure to move on-farm. It is therefore perhaps\\r\\nnot surprising that the design of such trials has, too often, resulted in miniaturised\\r\\nresearch institute experiments. Conditions for on-farm trials are typically less\\r\\ncontrolled than those for research institute fields, and this means that more thoughtful\\r\\ndesigns are needed.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\"><p>This booklet concentrates primarily on providing guidelines on aspects of the design\\r\\nand analysis of on-farm trials that are different from on-station research. It is\\r\\nconcerned primarily with experiments where the farmer has considerable involvement\\r\\n\\u2013 and not situations where the farmer\\u2019s only participation is by providing land.\\r\\nEqually, it does not include experiments that are really just demonstrations. You\\r\\nshould therefore ask yourself whether your experiment (a) involves the farmer in\\r\\ndesign, management or assessment, (b) seeks to address unanswered questions and (c)\\r\\nis an experiment, i.e. it involves planned changes.\\\"<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on how to design and conduct an on-farm experiment with the participation of farmers. Includes information about setting objectives, selecting farms to involve, choosing treatments and units, measurements and analysis of results. <br><\\/p><p>From the introduction:<\\/p><p>\\\"Farmer-participatory research trials have rapidly gained popularity in the past few\\r\\nyears with due consideration being given to the knowledge, problems and priorities of\\r\\nfarming families. The move towards participatory on-farm research means that many\\r\\nresearchers, such as breeders and agronomists, who have been trained in techniques of\\r\\non-station research, are now under pressure to move on-farm. It is therefore perhaps\\r\\nnot surprising that the design of such trials has, too often, resulted in miniaturised\\r\\nresearch institute experiments. Conditions for on-farm trials are typically less\\r\\ncontrolled than those for research institute fields, and this means that more thoughtful\\r\\ndesigns are needed.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\"><p>This booklet concentrates primarily on providing guidelines on aspects of the design\\r\\nand analysis of on-farm trials that are different from on-station research. It is\\r\\nconcerned primarily with experiments where the farmer has considerable involvement\\r\\n\\u2013 and not situations where the farmer\\u2019s only participation is by providing land.\\r\\nEqually, it does not include experiments that are really just demonstrations. You\\r\\nshould therefore ask yourself whether your experiment (a) involves the farmer in\\r\\ndesign, management or assessment, (b) seeks to address unanswered questions and (c)\\r\\nis an experiment, i.e. it involves planned changes.\\\"<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\",\"es\":\"<p>Un folleto que brinda orientaci\\u00f3n sobre c\\u00f3mo dise\\u00f1ar y realizar un experimento en la granja con la participaci\\u00f3n de los agricultores. Incluye informaci\\u00f3n sobre el establecimiento de objetivos, la selecci\\u00f3n de fincas para involucrar, la elecci\\u00f3n de tratamientos y unidades, mediciones y an\\u00e1lisis de resultados.<br><\\/p><p>\\\"Los trabajos de investigacio\\u0301n con participacio\\u0301n de los agricultores han ganado popularidad ra\\u0301pidamente en los an\\u0303os recientes, debido a la importancia que esta\\u0301 recibiendo el conocimiento, los problemas y prioridades del agricultor y su familia. Esta tendencia hacia la investigacio\\u0301n en finca significa que muchos investigadores, tales como mejoradores, zootecnistas o agro\\u0301nomos, quienes han sido entrenados en te\\u0301cnicas de investigacio\\u0301n tradicional en estaciones experimentales, esta\\u0301n ahora bajo la presio\\u0301n de trasladarse a la investigacio\\u0301n en la finca del agricultor. Es por esto que quiza\\u0301s no sorprenda que el disen\\u0303o de tales investigaciones ha resultado, muy a menudo, en experimentos de estacio\\u0301n experimental miniaturizados. Las condiciones de los experimentos en fincas de agricultores son ti\\u0301picamente menos controladas que en los campos de institutos de investigacio\\u0301n, y eso significa que se requieren disen\\u0303os mucho ma\\u0301s meditados.<br>Esta publicacio\\u0301n se concentra fundamentalmente en brindar gui\\u0301as sobre aspectos del disen\\u0303o y ana\\u0301lisis de experimentos en campos de productores que son diferentes de la investigacio\\u0301n en estaciones experimentales. Trata ba\\u0301sicamente con experimentos donde el agricultor esta\\u0301 involucrado de una manera importante - y no en situaciones donde la participacio\\u0301n del agricultor se limita solamente a facilitar sus campos. De igual manera, no incluye experimentos que son realmente solo demostrativos. Usted debe preguntarse si su experimento (a) involucra al agricultor en el disen\\u0303o, manejo y evaluacio\\u0301n, (b) busca responder a preguntas que no han sido contestadas y (c) es realmente un experimento, es decir, implica cambios planificados.\\\"<br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\nEl SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC\"}','2019-10-10 15:39:22','2019-10-10 15:39:22'),(1752,'App\\Models\\Trove',410,7,'elements_files','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18\\\\\\/2019-08-21_15:52:18_onfarmtrials.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_15:52:18_onfarmtrials.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"OnFarmTrials.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":232699,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18\\\\\\/2019-08-21_15:52:18_onfarmtrials.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_15:52:18_onfarmtrials.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"OnFarmTrials.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":232699,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\",\"es\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18\\\\\\/2019-10-10_15:39:22_guia4.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:39:22_guia4.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia4.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":118809,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','2019-10-10 15:39:22','2019-10-10 15:39:22'),(1753,'App\\Models\\Trove',410,7,'elements_urls','{\"en\":null}','{\"es\":null}','2019-10-10 15:39:22','2019-10-10 15:39:22'),(1754,'App\\Models\\Trove',404,7,'title','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Guidelines for Planning Effective Surveys\"}','{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Guidelines for Planning Effective Surveys\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos para planear encuestas efectivas\"}','2019-10-10 15:41:33','2019-10-10 15:41:33'),(1755,'App\\Models\\Trove',404,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A booklet on planning surveys for research. The guide covers planning, when a survey is appropriate to use, setting up a survey, designing questionnaires, sampling principles, quality assurance and survey data analysis.<br><\\/p><p>\\\"This booklet provides guidelines about surveys which may be contemplated as part of\\r\\nthe programme of project work. It is intended to provide guidance for those involved\\r\\nin natural resources research or bilateral projects, and to help those who review project\\r\\nactivities. They should be able to recognise where a survey may be needed to realise\\r\\nstated objectives of the project and to check that a survey is realistically formulated\\\"\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A booklet on planning surveys for research. The guide covers planning, when a survey is appropriate to use, setting up a survey, designing questionnaires, sampling principles, quality assurance and survey data analysis.<br><\\/p><p>\\\"This booklet provides guidelines about surveys which may be contemplated as part of\\r\\nthe programme of project work. It is intended to provide guidance for those involved\\r\\nin natural resources research or bilateral projects, and to help those who review project\\r\\nactivities. They should be able to recognise where a survey may be needed to realise\\r\\nstated objectives of the project and to check that a survey is realistically formulated\\\"\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\",\"es\":\"<p>Un folleto sobre la planificaci\\u00f3n de encuestas para la investigaci\\u00f3n. La gu\\u00eda cubre la planificaci\\u00f3n, cuando una encuesta es apropiada para usar, establecer una encuesta, dise\\u00f1ar cuestionarios, principios de muestreo, garant\\u00eda de calidad y an\\u00e1lisis de datos de encuestas.<br><\\/p><p>\\\"Esta publicacio\\u0301n ofrece gui\\u0301as acerca del disen\\u0303o de encuestas que pueden ser contempladas como parte del programa de trabajo de un proyecto. La misma pretende ser u\\u0301til a quienes este\\u0301n involucrados en investigacio\\u0301n en recursos naturales o proyectos bilaterales y puede ayudar a quienes supervisan actividades de los proyectos. Los unos y los otros deben estar en capacidad de reconocer cuando una encuesta puede ser necesaria para alcanzar los objetivos establecidos en el proyecto y de evaluar que la encuesta sea formulada de manera realista.\\\"<br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>El SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC.<\\/p>\"}','2019-10-10 15:41:33','2019-10-10 15:41:33'),(1756,'App\\Models\\Trove',404,7,'elements_files','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28\\\\\\/2019-08-21_10:14:28_guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:14:28_guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guidelines_for_Planning_Effective_Surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":188768,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28\\\\\\/2019-08-21_10:14:28_guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:14:28_guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guidelines_for_Planning_Effective_Surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":188768,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\",\"es\":\"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\\\/statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28\\\\\\/2019-10-10_15:41:33_guia5.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:41:33_guia5.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia5.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":126787,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','2019-10-10 15:41:33','2019-10-10 15:41:33'),(1757,'App\\Models\\Trove',404,7,'elements_urls','{\"en\":null}','{\"es\":null}','2019-10-10 15:41:33'