toryactionresearch.net\\/publications\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">sitio web de SAS2<\\/a>, aunque primero deber\\u00e1 registrarse con una direcci\\u00f3n de correo electr\\u00f3nico.<\\/span><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\",\"fr\":\"<p>Ce manuel est une collection int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e de moyens habiles pour engager les gens et mobiliser des preuves dans des environnements complexes impliquant de multiples parties prenantes. Il s\'inspire de diff\\u00e9rentes disciplines, perspectives th\\u00e9oriques et approches m\\u00e9thodologiques. Enti\\u00e8rement participatives et flexibles, les techniques et les id\\u00e9es sous-jacentes sont accessibles aux d\\u00e9butants et fourniront aux chercheurs exp\\u00e9riment\\u00e9s et aux animateurs une nouvelle approche de l\\u2019\\u00e9ducation, du milieu de travail, de la communaut\\u00e9 et du public. Les acteurs des secteurs associatif, acad\\u00e9mique, priv\\u00e9 et gouvernemental les utilisent pour des enqu\\u00eates et des enqu\\u00eates communautaires, pour la planification et l\'\\u00e9valuation de projets ou de programmes, pour l\'apprentissage organisationnel et pour la r\\u00e9solution de probl\\u00e8mes \\u00e0 toutes les \\u00e9chelles.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Le manuel est t\\u00e9l\\u00e9chargeable gratuitement sur <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.participatoryactionresearch.net\\/publications\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">le site Web de SAS2<\\/a>, bien que vous deviez d\'abord vous enregistrer avec une adresse \\u00e9lectronique.<br><\\/p>\"}','2019-10-23 14:45:22','2019-10-23 14:45:22'),(1865,'App\\Models\\Trove',309,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>Outlines the four principles of any social network (such as a Farmer Research Network) that strives to create positive, sustainable outcomes for individuals, families, and communities. <br><\\/p><p>Source: Hi Howard, The Piton Foundation<\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>Outlines the four principles of any social network (such as a Farmer Research Network) that strives to create positive, sustainable outcomes for individuals, families, and communities. <br><\\/p><p>Source: Hi Howard, The Piton Foundation<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\"}','2019-10-23 14:45:28','2019-10-23 14:45:28'),(1866,'App\\Models\\Trove',310,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>A sourcebook collecting together a range of methods for drying and storing grains to arrest the growth of aflatoxin. These methods can improve the safety and quality of grain. Each method is presented with diagrams, key facts, an overview of the operating parameters, resource\\r\\nrequirements, and positive and negative aspects of adoption.<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\"><p>The book was produced by the AflaSTOP project of ACDI-VOCA, with support of the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>A sourcebook collecting together a range of methods for drying and storing grains to arrest the growth of aflatoxin. These methods can improve the safety and quality of grain. Each method is presented with diagrams, key facts, an overview of the operating parameters, resource\\r\\nrequirements, and positive and negative aspects of adoption.<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\"><p>The book was produced by the AflaSTOP project of ACDI-VOCA, with support of the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','2019-10-23 14:46:04','2019-10-23 14:46:04'),(1867,'App\\Models\\Trove',311,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">Maize, millet, sorghum, sweetpotatoes and cassava are the major crops grown and consumed in\\r\\nUganda. However, most of the food produced is lost postharvest (20-30%), mainly due to poor\\r\\npostharvest handling methods, including late harvesting, poor harvesting and sorting methods,\\r\\ninsufficient drying, inappropriate storage conditions, poor processing, use of defective packaging,\\r\\nand infestation by molds, insects and rodents. <\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">This manual gives guidelines on post-harvest practices\\r\\nand technologies that can be used to maintain quality and reduce losses in maize, millet, sorghum,\\r\\ncassava and sweetpotatoes handling.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p><br><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">A manual from Makerere University, VEDCO and NARO.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">Maize, millet, sorghum, sweetpotatoes and cassava are the major crops grown and consumed in\\r\\nUganda. However, most of the food produced is lost postharvest (20-30%), mainly due to poor\\r\\npostharvest handling methods, including late harvesting, poor harvesting and sorting methods,\\r\\ninsufficient drying, inappropriate storage conditions, poor processing, use of defective packaging,\\r\\nand infestation by molds, insects and rodents. <\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">This manual gives guidelines on post-harvest practices\\r\\nand technologies that can be used to maintain quality and reduce losses in maize, millet, sorghum,\\r\\ncassava and sweetpotatoes handling.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p><br><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">A manual from Makerere University, VEDCO and NARO.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><br><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','2019-10-23 14:46:11','2019-10-23 14:46:11'),(1868,'App\\Models\\Trove',312,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Abstract\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A study was conducted to determine farmers\' perceptions of soil quality and common soil management practices that influenced soil fertility\\r\\nwithin farmers\' fields in Chuka and Gachoka divisions, Kenya. Soils were characterised by smallholders after which they were geo-referenced and\\r\\nsampled at surface depth (0\\u201320 cm) for subsequent physical and chemical analyses, to determine differences within farmers\' soil quality\\r\\ncategories. Indicators for distinguishing productive and non-productive fields included crop yield and performance, soil colour and soil texture.\\r\\nThere were significant differences among soil fertility categories, using parametric techniques (ANOVA) for key soil properties (pb0.005),\\r\\nimplying that there was a qualitative difference in the soils that were characterised as different by farmers. Fertile soils had significantly higher pH,\\r\\ntotal organic carbon, exchangeable cations and available-N. Factor analysis on 15 soil properties identified 4 main factors that explained 68% of\\r\\nthe total variance in soil quality. The four Varimax-rotated factors were designated as contrasts that described soil quality status on farmers\' fields.\\r\\nThe first factor grouped calcium, magnesium and soil pH, while the second component comprised available nitrogen, organic carbon and total\\r\\nnitrogen. The third factor included plant nutrients mainly extractable phosphorus and available nitrogen, while the fourth factor comprised soil\\r\\nphysical properties (macroaggregates, microaggregates, silt, and clay). Soil fertility and crop management practices that were investigated\\r\\nindicated that farmers understood and consequently utilised spatial heterogeneity and temporal variability in soil quality status within their farms\\r\\nas a resource to maintain or enhance agricultural productivity.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\u00a9 2007 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.<br>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Abstract\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\