\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\u00a9 2007 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}','2019-10-23 14:46:18','2019-10-23 14:46:18'),(1869,'App\\Models\\Trove',313,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>A poster summarising information about a project to implement a Soil Tool Kit which can be used by partners on smallholder farms to collect information about soil health and build a better understanding of the impact of management, crop rotations, forages and residue management. <\\/p><div class=\\\"site-branding\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p class=\\\"site-title\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/smallholder-sha.org\\/\\\" rel=\\\"home\\\">Smallholder Soil Health Assessment<\\/a><\\/p><br><\\/div>\",\"es\":\"Un p\\u00f3ster que resume la informaci\\u00f3n sobre un proyecto para implementar un Kit de herramientas de suelo que puede ser utilizado por socios en peque\\u00f1as granjas para recopilar informaci\\u00f3n sobre la salud del suelo y comprender mejor el impacto del manejo, la rotaci\\u00f3n de cultivos, los forrajes y el manejo de residuos.\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>A poster summarising information about a project to implement a Soil Tool Kit which can be used by partners on smallholder farms to collect information about soil health and build a better understanding of the impact of management, crop rotations, forages and residue management. <\\/p><div class=\\\"site-branding\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p class=\\\"site-title\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/smallholder-sha.org\\/\\\" rel=\\\"home\\\">Smallholder Soil Health Assessment<\\/a><\\/p><p class=\\\"site-title\\\"><br><\\/p><p class=\\\"site-title\\\"><br><\\/p><p class=\\\"site-title\\\">Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p><br><\\/div>\",\"es\":\"Un p\\u00f3ster que resume la informaci\\u00f3n sobre un proyecto para implementar un Kit de herramientas de suelo que puede ser utilizado por socios en peque\\u00f1as granjas para recopilar informaci\\u00f3n sobre la salud del suelo y comprender mejor el impacto del manejo, la rotaci\\u00f3n de cultivos, los forrajes y el manejo de residuos.\"}','2019-10-23 14:46:23','2019-10-23 14:46:23'),(1870,'App\\Models\\Trove',314,7,'description','{\"en\":\"<p>A case study produced for the symposium on Managing biodiversity in agricultural systems, Montreal, 8-12 November, 2001.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\">The paper examines methods and practices for farming and soil management used by farmers in Arumeru for addressing decreased crop yields associated with poor soil fertility, and how a focus on \'agrodiversity\' is helping them work in challenging conditions.<br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Extract:<\\/span><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\u201cManagement diversity\\u201d (i.e. land transforming operations which influence the behavior of physical and\\r\\nchemical aspects of the soil, surface and near surface physical and biological processes, hydrology, micro-\\r\\nclimate etc. (Brookfield and Stocking, 1999) and its impact on agrodiversity) is the focus of this paper.\\r\\nDifferent methods of managing the land, water and biota for crop production and the maintenance of soil\\r\\nfertility and structure are examined. Diverse soil management methods used by farmers in Arumeru to\\r\\naddress diverse constraints all aimed at soil productivity improvement, agrodiversity enhancement and\\r\\nconservation are considered.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>A case study produced for the symposium on Managing biodiversity in agricultural systems, Montreal, 8-12 November, 2001.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\">The paper examines methods and practices for farming and soil management used by farmers in Arumeru for addressing decreased crop yields associated with poor soil fertility, and how a focus on \'agrodiversity\' is helping them work in challenging conditions.<br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Extract:<\\/span><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\u201cManagement diversity\\u201d (i.e. land transforming operations which influence the behavior of physical and\\r\\nchemical aspects of the soil, surface and near surface physical and biological processes, hydrology, micro-\\r\\nclimate etc. (Brookfield and Stocking, 1999) and its impact on agrodiversity) is the focus of this 