es is focused on \\r\\nevaluating sorghum and pearl millet varieties but contains advice that \\r\\nwould be helpful for a range of participatory research projects. It \\r\\nincludes methods for \\r\\nidentifying priority evaluation criteria with farmers, as well as \\r\\ndifferent options for documenting farmers choices and evaluations. <\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">This is a guide to conducting an open-ended evaluation with farmers to collect qualitative data about their opinions. It is designed to be used when the researcher\\/NGO staff\\/development agent is not familiar with the farmers\' opinions about a certain technology and wishes to explore the opinions and experiences of the farmers.&nbsp; <\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">The guide presents step by step guidance of how to conduct such an evaluation, examples of the kinds of questions that can be asked to obtain useful information, and how to document the results. <br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Produced \\r\\nwith the involvement of the following organisations: AMSP, AOPP, CIRAD, \\r\\nCOPROSEM, ICRISAT, IER Institut d\'Econmie Rurale, INERA, UGCPA, Union \\r\\nLocale des producteurs de Cereales de Dioila<br><\\/p>\",\"fr\":\"Partie d\'une s\\u00e9rie de fiches d\'information et de guides pratiques sur l\'\\u00e9valuation participative des vari\\u00e9t\\u00e9s avec les agriculteurs. La s\\u00e9rie se concentre sur l\\u2019\\u00e9valuation des vari\\u00e9t\\u00e9s de sorgho et de mil, mais contient des conseils utiles pour divers projets de recherche participative. Il inclut des m\\u00e9thodes pour identifier les crit\\u00e8res d\\u2019\\u00e9valuation prioritaires avec les agriculteurs, ainsi que diff\\u00e9rentes options pour documenter les choix et les \\u00e9valuations des agriculteurs.<br><br>Ceci est un guide pour mener une \\u00e9valuation ouverte avec les agriculteurs afin de collecter des donn\\u00e9es qualitatives sur leurs opinions. Il est con\\u00e7u pour \\u00eatre utilis\\u00e9 lorsque le chercheur \\/ le personnel de l\'ONG \\/ l\'agent de d\\u00e9veloppement n\'est pas au courant des opinions des agriculteurs sur une technologie donn\\u00e9e et souhaite explorer les opinions et les exp\\u00e9riences de ces derniers.<br><br>Ce guide explique pas \\u00e0 pas comment proc\\u00e9der \\u00e0 une telle \\u00e9valuation, donne des exemples du type de questions pouvant \\u00eatre pos\\u00e9es pour obtenir des informations utiles et explique comment documenter les r\\u00e9sultats.<br><br><br>Produit avec la participation des organisations suivantes: AMSP, AOPP, CIRAD, COPROSEM, ICRISAT, IER Institut d\'Econmie Rurale, INERA, UGCPA, Union Locale des producteurs de Cereales de Dioila.\"}','{\"en\":\"<p>Part of a series of factsheets and practical guides for conducting \\r\\nparticipatory variety evaluation with farmers. The series is focused on \\r\\nevaluating sorghum and pearl millet varieties but contains advice that \\r\\nwould be helpful for a range of participatory research projects. It \\r\\nincludes methods for \\r\\nidentifying priority evaluation criteria with farmers, as well as \\r\\ndifferent options for documenting farmers choices and evaluations. <\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">This is a guide to conducting an open-ended evaluation with farmers to collect qualitative data about their opinions. It is designed to be used when the researcher\\/NGO staff\\/development agent is not familiar with the farmers\' opinions about a certain technology and wishes to explore the opinions and experiences of the farmers.&nbsp; <\\/p><p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\">The guide presents step by step guidance of how to conduct such an evaluation, examples of the kinds of questions that can be asked to obtain useful information, and how to document the results. <br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Produced \\r\\nwith the involvement of the following organisations: AMSP, AOPP, CIRAD, \\r\\nCOPROSEM, ICRISAT, IER Institut d\'Econmie Rurale, IN