conomic, Political, Environmental, Socio-Economic\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Methodology<\\/span>: High level summary of key agroecological principles\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Usage<\\/span>: These principles could form the basis of assessment - but by themselves are not an assesment tool.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Relevance to CCRP<\\/span>: High. Principles are well thought out and clearly explained.<\\/p>\"}',1,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/agroecological-principles-cisde_2019-05-14_14:17:38\\\\/2019-05-14_14:17:38_cidse-ae-principles-infographic-en.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-05-14_14:17:38_cidse-ae-principles-infographic-en.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"cidse-ae-principles-infographic-en.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":174423,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.cidse.org/\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-05-14 13:17:39','2019-08-21 11:59:54',NULL,NULL,'files/agroecological-principles-cisde_2019-05-14_14:17:38/agroecological-principles-cisde_2019-05-14_14:17:38.zip',1),(131,'{\"en\":\"M\\u00c1S ALL\\u00c1 DE LOS PROMEDIOS: NUEVOS ENFOQUES PARA ENTENDER  LA HETEROGENEIDAD Y EL RIESGO DEL \\u00c9XITO O FRACASO DE LA TECNOLOG\\u00cdA  EN LOS SISTEMAS AGR\\u00cdCOLAS DE PEQUE\\u00d1OS PRODUCTORES\"}','mas-alla-de-los-promedios-nuevos-enfoques-para-entender-la-heterogeneidad-y-el-riesgo-del-exito-o-fracaso-de-la-tecnologia-en-los-sistemas-agricolas-de-pequenos-productores_2019-05-14_14:18:21',NULL,'{\"en\":\"Traducci\\u00f3n del art\\u00edculo original de los mismos autores. Se recomienda leer este art\\u00edculo para reforzar el caso de lo importante que es entender la variabilidad y sus fuentes al explorar datos y tener en cuenta que la comparaci\\u00f3n de promedios no siempre resulta en informaci\\u00f3n \\u00fatil.\"}',1,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/mas-alla-de-los-promedios-nuevos-enfoques-para-entender-la-heterogeneidad-y-el-riesgo-del-exito-o-fracaso-de-la-tecnologia-en-los-sistemas-agricolas-de-pequenos-productores_2019-05-14_14:18:21\\\\/2019-05-14_14:18:21_vanlauwe-coe-mas-alla-de-promedios-2.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-05-14_14:18:21_vanlauwe-coe-mas-alla-de-promedios-2.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"vanlauwe-coe-mas-alla-de-promedios-2.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":1629049,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,NULL,'2019-05-14 13:18:23','2019-05-14 13:18:23',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(132,'{\"en\":\"The 10 Elements of Agroecology\"}','the-10-elements-of-agroecology_2019-05-14_14:18:59',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Summary:&nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/span>A useful framework produced by FAO As an analytical tool, the 10 Elements can help countries to operationalise agroecology. It comparees to other frameworks proposed by others that can be useful as the basis to assess the extent to which an agroecolocial lense is used in the analysis, transformation or evaluation of an agricultural system<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Dimensions Used: <\\/span>Efficiency; Recycling; Regulation; Synergies; Diversity; Resilience; Circular Solidarity Economy; Culture &amp; Food Traditions; Co-Creation of Knowledge; Human &amp; Social Value; Responsible Governance\\r\\n\\r\\n**Methodology**: High level summary of key agroecological principles\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Usage: <\\/span>These principles could form the basis of assessment - but by themselves are not an assesment tool.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Relevance to CCRP:<\\/span> High. Principles are given detailed explanations, and justification.<\\/p>\"}',1,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/the-10-elements-of-agroecology_2019-05-14_14:18:59\\\\/2019-05-14_14:18:59_the-10-elements-of-agroecology-fao.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-05-14_14:18:59_the-10-elements-of-agroecology-fao.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"the-10-elements-of-agroecology-fao.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":3961178,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.fao.org/agroecology/knowledge/10-elements/en/\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-05-14 13:19:02','2019-07-11 15:23:17',NULL,NULL,'files/the-10-elements-of-agroecology_2019-05-14_14:18:59/the-10-elements-of-agroecology_2019-05-14_14:18:59.zip',1),(133,'{\"en\":\"Agroecology Criteria Tool (ACT)  - Biovision\"}','agroecology-criteria-tool-act-biovision_2019-05-14_14:19:44',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Summary:<\\/span><br>The Agroecology Criteria Tool (ACT) methodology is based on the analytical framework by Gliessman on the 5 levels of food system change and is embedded within the 10 Elements of Agroecology by FAO. Each element of the transition includes a list of relevant topics (inclusion criteria), which were based on past work by DeLonge et al.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Dimensions Used:<\\/span><br>Efficiency; Recycling; Regulation; Synergies; Diversity; Resilience; Circular Solidarity Economy; Culture &amp; Food Traditions; Co-Creation of Knowledge; Human &amp; Social Value; Responsible Governance\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Methodology:<\\/span> <br>Under each dimension a number of binary Yes\\/No criteria are outlined, where \\\"Yes\\\" would indicate an agroecological criteria. As such it is very easy to complete the tool in a subjective way, as all questions are \\\"Yes\\/No\\\". Results are presented in the form of radar plots showing agroecological performance across the various dimensions.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Usage:<\\/span> <br>It is an online tool, but the tool is simple and could easily be recreated in ODK or other form builder tools for use offline. In this resource trove you will find Excel files in English and Spanish where the tools has been transcribed into a rubric too.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Relevance to CCRP:<\\/span><br>Moderate. Tool is extremely easy to use and produce results. However, the subjective nature of questions means the tool will lack nuance, and different people will provide different assesments to the same project\\/farm\\/plot. Outputs are limited to radar plots, but outputs manipulated in various different ways.<\\/p>\"}',1,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/agroecology-criteria-tool-act-biovision_2019-05-14_14:19:44\\\\/2019-05-14_14:19:44_aei-research-rubric-20-feb2019-en.docx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-05-14_14:19:44_aei-research-rubric-20-feb2019-en.docx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"aei-research-rubric-20-feb2019-en.docx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"docx\\\",\\\"size\\\":15894,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/agroecology-criteria-tool-act-biovision_2019-05-14_14:19:44\\\\/2019-05-14_14:19:45_aei-research-rubric-20-feb2019-sp-translation.docx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-05-14_14:19:45_aei-research-rubric-20-feb2019-sp-translation.docx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"aei-research-rubric-20-feb2019-sp-translation.docx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"docx\\\",\\\"size\\\":15293,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.agroecology-pool.org/methodology/\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-05-14 13:19:45','2019-07-31 13:17:28',NULL,NULL,'files/agroecology-criteria-tool-act-biovision_2019-05-14_14:19:44/agroecology-criteria-tool-act-biovision_2019-05-14_14:19:44.zip',1),(134,'{\"en\":\"Agroecology explained to children\"}','agroecology-explained-to-children_2019-05-14_14:22:06',NULL,'{\"en\":\"Video used to start up discussion about what is agroecology in workshops\"}',1,13,'cover_images/troves/48518c9a016dfbd15cde5e1e45a8c245.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bLqYE-m2nE4\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-05-14 13:22:06','2019-05-15 07:14:19',NULL,'bLqYE-m2nE4',NULL,1),(135,'{\"en\":\"Agroecology for Africa animation\"}','agroecology-for-africa-animation