en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2018-09-01','2019-05-21 15:55:38','2019-07-31 13:55:10',NULL,'0fqnofuZwXI',NULL,1),(223,'{\"en\":\"Hypothesis Testing\"}','hypothesis-testing_2019-05-21_16:01:34',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This recording is of a webinar given by Stats4SD. \\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>In this penultimate webinar, Alex Riba discusses hypothesis tests - what they are, and what they can tell you. \\r\\n\\r\\nAs part of this, he explains the concept of a p-value, how hypothesis tests link to confidence intervals, and gives some (semi) formal definitions of null and alternative hypotheses. \\r\\n\\r\\nHe also explores a set of practical examples to discuss how to apply hypothesis testing as part of a real analysis.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\r\\nThis webinar was hosted by WorldFish for the Gender &amp; Breeding Postdoctoral Fellow Initiative. It was funded by the CGIAR.<\\/p>\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/fd01514974da24625497dd4ee35e4d20.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2018-06-01','2019-05-21 16:01:34','2019-07-31 13:51:59',NULL,'9sHfGwffrOI',NULL,1),(224,'{\"en\":\"Coming Down from the Mountain\"}','coming-down-from-the-mountain_2019-05-21_16:26:36',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This is a recording of a webinar given by Stats4SD. \\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Roger Stern wraps up this short webinar series by giving an overview of statistical analysis thinking, practice and teaching over the past 50 years. \\r\\n\\r\\nHe explores some of the reasons why statistics training is often still stuck \\\"up the mountain\\\" and gives some ideas on how statisticians and non-statisticians can be trained in a more practical way to allow them to do better statistics and (perhaps) even enjoy some of it.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>This webinar was hosted by WorldFish for the Gender &amp; Breeding Postdoctoral Fellow Initiative. It was funded by the CGIAR.<\\/p>\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/5adadd4fe49d1a9fed1c19d7a294db4e.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2018-06-01','2019-05-21 16:26:36','2019-07-31 13:57:46',NULL,'4mXqU8P8gIk',NULL,1),(225,'{\"en\":\"Estimation:  Precision and Variability\"}','estimation-precision-and-variability_2019-05-21_16:28:41',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This is a recording of a webinar given by Stats4SD. \\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Sam Dumble explains some key concepts about precision and variability within a dataset, using a small custom web app to demonstrate the concepts discussed. \\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>The webinar includes: <\\/p><ul><li>a brief recap of summary statistics and graphics<\\/li><li> a discussion of estimation from samples, including an explanation of what a confidence interval means. <\\/li><li>the important difference between precision and accuracy<\\/li><li>some discussion of disaggregation of data and what that means for your study design. \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/li><\\/ul><p>This webinar was hosted by WorldFish for the Gender &amp; Breeding Postdoctoral Fellow Initiative. It was funded by the CGIAR.<\\/p>\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/abb266b58014a7e22d52f7a38ab4f207.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2018-05-01','2019-05-21 16:28:41','2019-07-31 13:59:44',NULL,'uhzx8HMEMzM',NULL,1),(226,'{\"en\":\"How to prepare a strategy for data analysis\"}','how-to-prepare-a-strategy-for-data-analysis_2019-05-21_16:30:18',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This is a recording of a webinar given by Stats4SD.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>\\r\\nAlex Riba and Carlos Barahona discuss the topic of preparing a strategy for data analysis, including the idea of starting with your final report, and working backwards to determine the other parts of your project. \\r\\n\\r\\nIn the second half, Alex presents a case study - an analysis plan developed at the start of a previous project, which clearly defines what information products are required for the final output.\\r\\n\\r\\n<\\/p><p>This webinar was hosted by WorldFish for the Gender &amp; Breeding Postdoctoral Fellow Initiative. It was funded by the CGIAR.<\\/p>\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/28be13d53