-agricultural-development_2019-07-24_15:23:49',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 7\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\" style=\\\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%)\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A paper arguing that the agricultural development efforts should support the practical integration of indigenous and traditional knowledge and local knowledge systems in various areas and sectors of agriculture to\\r\\nreach the sustainable development goals of a happier and healthier humanity and global\\r\\nenvironment.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Produced by the Food and Agriculture Organisation of the United Nations.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p><\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,17,'cover_images/troves/4412ccf3e97bfc24640b3d48a09d06c2.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.fao.org/3/a-mk953e.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2014-06-01','2019-07-24 15:23:50','2019-10-23 14:43:47',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(300,'{\"en\":\"Local Forecast Communication in the altiplano\"}','local-forecast-communication-in-the-altiplano_2019-07-24_15:34:23',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A paper, produced by the American Meteorological Society, which discusses the case of two communities of Andean farmers that reject weather forecasts broadcasted by the national weather service in favour of local experts using traditional forecasting methods. <br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Excerpt:<\\/span><br><\\/p><p>Agricultural production systems are extremely\\r\\nsensitive to climate variability. This is especially\\r\\ntrue for small farmer production systems in\\r\\ndeveloping countries where there are few resources\\r\\nto cushion the impacts of climatic shocks. Seasonal\\r\\nand monthly forecasts hold the promise of reducing\\r\\nthe impacts of these shocks by allowing farmers to\\r\\ntake actions that will either minimize the impacts of\\r\\nadverse weather conditions or take advantage of good\\r\\ngrowing conditions. To do this requires that small\\r\\nfarmers receive forecasts in the form and time needed\\r\\nto help them make decisions. In the last 10 years, there\\r\\nhas been a growing realization that farmers have not\\r\\nused forecasts to the degree that the forecast community had hoped. As a result, considerable effort has been devoted to understanding\\r\\nwhy this has not taken place. This paper describes the\\r\\nnetworks used to transmit forecast information in the\\r\\nAltiplano of Bolivia and Peru with special reference\\r\\nto three indigenous communities. The implications\\r\\nof these findings for improved forecast utilization are\\r\\nthen discussed.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p><\\/div><\\/div><\\/div><\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/7f81b9221ae68d1d0649b5a950757be2.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/pdf/10.1175/2008BAMS2183.1\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-24 15:34:24','2019-10-23 14:43:53',NULL,NULL,'files/local-forecast-communication-in-the-altiplano_2019-07-24_15:34:23/local-forecast-communication-in-the-altiplano_2019-07-24_15:34:23.zip',1),(301,'{\"en\":\"Protecting Community Rights over Traditional Knowledge: Implications of customary laws and practices - Key findings and recommendations 2005-2009\"}','protecting-community-rights-over-traditional-knowledge-implications-of-customary-laws-and-practices-key-findings-and-recommendations-2005-2009_2019-07-24_15:54:17',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><p>Key findings report from an action-research project \\\"focused on developing alternative tools to protect traditional\\r\\nknowledge which are rooted in local customary laws rather than based on existing Intellectual Property standards.\\\"<\\/p><p>Produced by International Institute for Environment and Development (IIED)\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/71070ef56b0dbc77d0b0c690ebe192c6.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://pubs.iied.org/pdfs/14591IIED.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2010-01-01','2019-07-24 15:54:18','2019-10-23 14:43:59',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(302,'{\"en\":\"Catalyzing Networks for Social Change: A Funder\'s Guide\"}','catalyzing-networks-for-social-change-a-funders-guide_2019-07-24_16:25:29',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A guide produced by Monitor Institute and Grantmakers for Effective Organisations (GEO) aimed at grantmakers and funders to help them to invest in and catalyze networks.<\\/p><p>Discusses the importance of networks and collaboration for social development initiatives and research.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/4c61bd8f78d8e457772ff8c07e5d64c4.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://community-wealth.org/sites/clone.community-wealth.org/files/downloads/tool-catalyzing-social-change.pdf\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-24 16:25:29','2019-10-23 14:44:03',NULL,NULL,'files/catalyzing-networks-for-social-change-a-funders-guide_2019-07-24_16:25:29/catalyzing-networks-for-social-change-a-funders-guide_2019-07-24_16:25:29.zip',1),(303,'{\"en\":\"Four Network Principles for Collaboration Success\"}','four-network-principles-for-collaboration-success_2019-07-24_16:31:32',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">An article from The Foundation Review Volume 5, Issue 1.<br><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Extract:<\\/span><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><ul><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t<p><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><ul><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<p><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><ul><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><ul style=\\\"list-style-type: none\\\"><ul><\\/ul><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><ul><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">This article identifies a set of four counterintuitive\\r\\nprinciples that are critical to collaboration success and offers insights for how nonprofit leaders\\r\\ncan ensure that their collaborations can have an\\r\\nimpact that is dramatically greater than the sum of\\r\\nthe individual parts.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><ul><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">Based on a decade of research developing\\r\\ndetailed case studies on a range of successful\\r\\nnetworks, the authors have identified a common\\r\\npattern of factors that are essential to effective\\r\\nnetworking.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><ul><\\/ul>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">The principles are: focus on mission before organization; manage through trust, not control; promote\\r\\nothers, not yourself; and build constellations, not\\r\\nstars.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><br><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/729967cc9599460183226b6fbf98d2f0.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://scholarworks.gvsu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1009&context=tfr\"}]}',NULL,'2013-06-01','2019-07-24 16:31:32','2019-10-23 14:44:33',NULL,NULL,'files/four-network-principles-for-collaboration-success_2019-07-24_16:31:32/four-network-principles-for-collaboration-success_2019-07-24_16:31:32.zip',1),(304,'{\"en\":\"80 Tools for Participatory Development\"}','80-tools-for-participatory-development_2019-07-24_16:45:44',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\" style=\\\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%)\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A collection of methodologies and tools to be used to facilitate \\r\\ncollective action and solutions based on full stakeholder participation.\\r\\n <\\/p>Contains practical advice for facilitation of participatory activities such as workshops. <p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\u00a9 Inter-American Institute for Cooperation on Agriculture (IICA).\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">From the blurb:<\\/span><br><\\/p><p>This book is a \\u201ctoolbox\\u201d for\\r\\nrural-development stakeholders\\r\\nand professionals \\u2013 extension\\r\\nworkers, advocates, community\\r\\nleaders, researchers \\u2013 who wish\\r\\nto improve and systematize\\r\\ncommunity participation in\\r\\nprojects and initiatives. It is\\r\\nintended for those who have\\r\\nrealized, through their own\\r\\nexperiences, that participation\\r\\nis an essential prerequisite for\\r\\nsustainable development. \\r\\n<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p><br><\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/cb819bc0a758472d724d1916f403d231.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://repositorio.iica.int/bitstream/11324/4129/2/BVE17089190i.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2008-01-01','2019-07-24 16:45:45','2019-10-23 14:44:40',NULL,NULL,'files/80-tools-for-participatory-development_2019-07-24_16:45:44/80-tools-for-participatory-development_2019-07-24_16:45:44.zip',1),(305,'{\"en\":\"Participatory Research Methods for Technology Evaluation: A Manual for Scientists Working with Farmers\"}','participatory-research-methods-for-technology-evaluation-a-manual-for-scientists-working-with-farmers_2019-07-24_16:50:57',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Abstract:<\\/span><br>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>This manual presents methods that enable agricultural scientist and farmers to\\r\\nevaluate technologies\\/practices jointly. The methods are specifically designed for\\r\\nparticipatory research on germplasm and soil fertility technologies, and they are illustrated\\r\\nwith actual examples from three research projects. The manual begins by reviewing\\r\\nconceptual issues that are important in participatory research and presents information to\\r\\nassist researchers in selecting research sites and fieldwork participants. Next, the manual\\r\\ndescribes the rationale and associated methods for each major activity in farmer participatory\\r\\nresearch: diagnosing farmers\\u2019 conditions, evaluating current and new technologies\\/practices,\\r\\nand assessing their impact. Goals, procedures, advantages, and limitations of each method are\\r\\noutlined. The manual also presents detailed information on analyzing data gathered through\\r\\nparticipatory methods, discusses differences between gathering data through participatory\\r\\nmethods and more traditional structured farm surveys, and offers examples, based on field\\r\\nexperience, of the choices and strategies involved in applying these methods.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>International Maize and Wheat Improvement Center (CIMMYT)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/50dc15f8d80d41c06ad620121027432c.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://repository.cimmyt.org/xmlui/bitstream/handle/10883/1023/74275.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2001-01-01','2019-07-24 16:50:58','2019-10-23 14:44:46',NULL,NULL,'files/participatory-research-methods-for-technology-evaluation-a-manual-for-scientists-working-with-farmers_2019-07-24_16:50:57/participatory-research-methods-for-technology-evaluation-a-manual-for-scientists-working-with-farmers_2019-07-24_16:50:57.zip',1),(306,'{\"en\":\"Farmer Led Documentation and Knowledge Sharing: Case Studies from Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda and Zambia\"}','farmer-led-documentation-and-knowledge-sharing-case-studies-from-kenya-tanzania-uganda-and-zambia_2019-07-24_17:00:54',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\" style=\\\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%)\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>This book contains case studies of projects promoting Farmer Led Documentation (FLD) - a \\\"participatory communication strategy\\\" seeking to allow communities to document and share their local and indigenous knowledge. <br><\\/p><p>\\u00a9 2010 PELUM Uganda\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Extract:<\\/span><\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 9\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\">Purpose of the Publication\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>PROLINNOVA states that although development agents have been interested in FLD, little is known about\\r\\nthe best designs of such documentation processes or about the available and appropriate media and their\\r\\nuse including those making use of modern Information and Communication Technologies (ICT). Therefore this\\r\\npublication aims at bringing out the FLD experience in varying settings in Kenya, Tanzania, Uganda, and Zambia,\\r\\nas well as different areas of interest (Climate Change and variability, Natural Resource Management, Indigenous\\r\\nKnowledge and Local Innovations) in order to demonstrate the FLD documentation process, commonly used\\r\\nmethods, tools, and the impact these have on the local communities where FLD is practiced.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\">What is presented in the publication\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>The publication presents the FLD experience through the farmers own viewpoint. The case studies presented\\r\\nin this publication were written by the implementers of the pilots and were shared and edited during a write\\r\\nshop organized by PELUM Uganda. The case studies demonstrate the ownership of the FLD process by the\\r\\nlocal communities which includes problem identification by participating communities, setting objectives to\\r\\nhandle the identified problems using FLD and the process used. This process included documenting: how\\r\\nit was done, how the farmers were enabled to take lead, who was involved and their roles. This publication\\r\\nelaborates the strategies used in the FLD projects, the results of the implementation, lessons learnt, challenges\\r\\nmet and how the process was being sustained in the local communities.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/d4416ecd2a951a0fcc92812981541d40.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://pelum.net/wp-content/uploads/2010/05/FLD-final-publication.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2010-01-01','2019-07-24 17:00:55','2019-10-23 14:44:56',NULL,NULL,'files/farmer-led-documentation-and-knowledge-sharing-case-studies-from-kenya-tanzania-uganda-and-zambia_2019-07-24_17:00:54/farmer-led-documentation-and-knowledge-sharing-case-studies-from-kenya-tanzania-uganda-and-zambia_2019-07-24_17:00:54.zip',1),(307,'{\"en\":\"The Field Guide to Human-Centered Design\"}','the-field-guide-to-human-centered-design_2019-07-24_17:06:32',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 4\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>By IDEO.org<\\/p><p>This book is available from <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.designkit.org\\/\\/resources\\/1\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Design Kit<\\/a> as a free PDF download. <br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Extract:<\\/span><\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 9\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>Embracing human-centered design means believing that all problems,\\r\\neven the seemingly intractable ones like poverty, gender equality,<br>\\r\\nand clean water, are solvable. Moreover, it means believing that the\\r\\npeople who face those problems every day are the ones who hold the\\r\\nkey to their answer. Human-centered design offers problem solvers of\\r\\nany stripe a chance to design with communities, to deeply understand\\r\\nthe people they\\u2019re looking to serve, to dream up scores of ideas, and to\\r\\ncreate innovative new solutions rooted in people\\u2019s actual needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>At IDEO.org and IDEO, we\\u2019ve used human-centered design for decades\\r\\nto create products, services, experiences, and social enterprises that\\r\\nhave been adopted and embraced because we\\u2019ve kept people\\u2019s lives and\\r\\ndesires at the core. The social sector is ripe for innovation, and we\\u2019ve\\r\\nseen time and again how our approach has the power to unlock real\\r\\nimpact. Being a human-centered designer is about believing that as\\r\\nlong as you stay grounded in what you\\u2019ve learned from people, your\\r\\nteam can arrive at new solutions that the world needs. And with this\\r\\nField Guide, you\\u2019re now armed with the tools needed to bring that\\r\\nbelief to life.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/d4c623863fde295a0cce39c1208b71be.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.designkit.org//resources/1\"}]}',NULL,'2015-05-24','2019-07-24 17:06:33','2019-10-23 14:45:04',NULL,NULL,'files/the-field-guide-to-human-centered-design_2019-07-24_17:06:32/the-field-guide-to-human-centered-design_2019-07-24_17:06:32.zip',1),(308,'{\"en\":\"Handbook for Participatory Action Research, Planning and Evaluation\",\"es\":\"Gui\\u0301a para la Investigacio\\u0301n, la Planificacio\\u0301n y la Evaluacio\\u0301n Participativas\",\"fr\":\"Guide de la recherche-action, la planification et l\\u2019e\\u0301valuation participatives\"}','handbook-for-participatory-action-research-planning-and-evaluation_2019-07-24_17:14:50',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 4\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"font-family: Helvetica; font-size: 9pt;\\\">This handbook is available in English, French and Spanish. It is an integrated collection of skillful means to engage people and\\r\\nmobilize evidence in complex settings involving multiple stakeholders. It draws\\r\\ninspiration from different disciplines, theoretical perspectives and methodological\\r\\napproaches. Fully participatory and flexible, the techniques and underlying ideas are\\r\\naccessible to beginners and will provide experienced researchers and facilitators with\\r\\na new approach to educational, workplace, community and public engagement.\\r\\nPeople in the voluntary, academic, private and government sectors are using them\\r\\nfor community-based action-inquiry and research, project or programme planning\\r\\nand evaluation, organizational learning and problem solving on all scales.<\\/span><br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 9.000000pt; font-family: \'Helvetica\'\\\">Produced by SAS2 Dialogue<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 9.000000pt; font-family: \'Helvetica\'\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">The handbook is free to download from the<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.participatoryactionresearch.net\\/publications\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\"> SAS2 website<\\/a>, although you will need to register with an email address first.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-size: 9.000000pt; font-family: \'Helvetica\'\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p><p><br><span style=\\\"font-size: 9.000000pt; font-family: \'Helvetica\'\\\">Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check.<span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"> <\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\",\"es\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>Esta gui\\u0301a es un conjunto integral de herramientas y procesos adapatados y novedosos para\\r\\nhacer parti\\u0301cipes a los actores y movilizar la evidencia en entornos complejos que incluyan\\r\\nmu\\u0301ltiples actores. Las herramientas y los procesos que abarca la gui\\u0301a\\u0301 recurren a la\\r\\ninspiracio\\u0301n de diferentes disciplinas, perspectivas teo\\u0301ricas y enfoques metodolo\\u0301gicos.\\r\\nTanto las herramientas como los conceptos subyacentes son participativos y flexibles, son\\r\\naccesibles para principiantes y novatos, y ponen a su disposicio\\u0301n investigadores y\\r\\nfacilitadores experimentados con un nuevo enfoque para la participacio\\u0301n educativa,\\r\\ntrabajadora, comunitaria y ci\\u0301vica. Diversos actores de los sectores acade\\u0301mico, voluntario,\\r\\nprivado y gubernamental los esta\\u0301n utilizando para la investigacio\\u0301n-accio\\u0301n comunitaria, la\\r\\nplanificacio\\u0301n y la evaluacio\\u0301n de proyectos y programas, el aprendizaje organizativo y la\\r\\nparticipacio\\u0301n social.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">El manual se puede descargar gratis del <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.participatoryactionresearch.net\\/publications\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">sitio web de SAS2<\\/a>, aunque primero deber\\u00e1 registrarse con una direcci\\u00f3n de correo electr\\u00f3nico.<\\/span><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\",\"fr\":\"<p>Ce manuel est une collection int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e de moyens habiles pour engager les gens et mobiliser des preuves dans des environnements complexes impliquant de multiples parties prenantes. Il s\'inspire de diff\\u00e9rentes disciplines, perspectives th\\u00e9oriques et approches m\\u00e9thodologiques. Enti\\u00e8rement participatives et flexibles, les techniques et les id\\u00e9es sous-jacentes sont accessibles aux d\\u00e9butants et fourniront aux chercheurs exp\\u00e9riment\\u00e9s et aux animateurs une nouvelle approche de l\\u2019\\u00e9ducation, du milieu de travail, de la communaut\\u00e9 et du public. Les acteurs des secteurs associatif, acad\\u00e9mique, priv\\u00e9 et gouvernemental les utilisent pour des enqu\\u00eates et des enqu\\u00eates communautaires, pour la planification et l\'\\u00e9valuation de projets ou de programmes, pour l\'apprentissage organisationnel et pour la r\\u00e9solution de probl\\u00e8mes \\u00e0 toutes les \\u00e9chelles.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Le manuel est t\\u00e9l\\u00e9chargeable gratuitement sur <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.participatoryactionresearch.net\\/publications\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">le site Web de SAS2<\\/a>, bien que vous deviez d\'abord vous enregistrer avec une adresse \\u00e9lectronique.<br><\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/8e8102a78c3a5c140738c512e1188b5f.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\", \"es\": \"[]\", \"fr\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.participatoryactionresearch.net/publications\"}], \"es\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.participatoryactionresearch.net/publications\"}], \"fr\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.participatoryactionresearch.net/publications\"}]}',NULL,'2019-03-01','2019-07-24 17:14:52','2019-10-23 14:45:22',NULL,NULL,'files/handbook-for-participatory-action-research-planning-and-evaluation_2019-07-24_17:14:50/handbook-for-participatory-action-research-planning-and-evaluation_2019-07-24_17:14:50.zip',1),(309,'{\"en\":\"The Four Principles of Social Networks\"}','the-four-principles-of-social-networks_2019-07-25_09:03:24',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>Outlines the four principles of any social network (such as a Farmer Research Network) that strives to create positive, sustainable outcomes for individuals, families, and communities. <br><\\/p><p>Source: Hi Howard, The Piton Foundation<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/fd47ac72871825523e637cfb87df93b0.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.ccrp.org/sites/default/files/networks.pdf\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 09:03:25','2019-10-23 14:45:28',NULL,NULL,'files/the-four-principles-of-social-networks_2019-07-25_09:03:24/the-four-principles-of-social-networks_2019-07-25_09:03:24.zip',1),(310,'{\"en\":\"AflaSTOP Grain Drying Sourcebook\"}','aflastop-grain-drying-sourcebook_2019-07-25_09:44:51',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A sourcebook collecting together a range of methods for drying and storing grains to arrest the growth of aflatoxin. These methods can improve the safety and quality of grain. Each method is presented with diagrams, key facts, an overview of the operating parameters, resource\\r\\nrequirements, and positive and negative aspects of adoption.<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\"><p>The book was produced by the AflaSTOP project of ACDI-VOCA, with support of the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/840791640e62f9e6b5567e06ab8fc3bd.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.acdivoca.org/2016/03/grain-drying-sourcebook/\"}]}',NULL,'2016-03-01','2019-07-25 09:44:52','2019-10-23 14:46:04',NULL,NULL,'files/aflastop-grain-drying-sourcebook_2019-07-25_09:44:51/aflastop-grain-drying-sourcebook_2019-07-25_09:44:51.zip',1),(311,'{\"en\":\"Postharvest Handling Manual for Maize, Millet, Sorghum, Sweet Potato and Cassava\"}','postharvest-handling-manual-for-maize-millet-sorghum-sweet-potato-and-cassava_2019-07-25_09:52:30',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"section\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">Maize, millet, sorghum, sweetpotatoes and cassava are the major crops grown and consumed in\\r\\nUganda. However, most of the food produced is lost postharvest (20-30%), mainly due to poor\\r\\npostharvest handling methods, including late harvesting, poor harvesting and sorting methods,\\r\\ninsufficient drying, inappropriate storage conditions, poor processing, use of defective packaging,\\r\\nand infestation by molds, insects and rodents. <\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">This manual gives guidelines on post-harvest practices\\r\\nand technologies that can be used to maintain quality and reduce losses in maize, millet, sorghum,\\r\\ncassava and sweetpotatoes handling.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p><br><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">A manual from Makerere University, VEDCO and NARO.\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><br><span style=\\\"background-color: inherit;\\\">Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/0e4c81b5cdef063c7504043f23dbe676.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/postharvest-handling-manual-for-maize-millet-sorghum-sweet-potato-and-cassava_2019-07-25_09:52:30\\\\/2019-07-25_09:52:30_post-harvest-manual-makerere-2016.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-07-25_09:52:30_post-harvest-manual-makerere-2016.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Post-harvest_Manual_Makerere_2016.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":3048881,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 09:52:31','2019-10-23 14:46:11',NULL,NULL,'files/postharvest-handling-manual-for-maize-millet-sorghum-sweet-potato-and-cassava_2019-07-25_09:52:30/postharvest-handling-manual-for-maize-millet-sorghum-sweet-potato-and-cassava_2019-07-25_09:52:30.zip',1),(312,'{\"en\":\"Integrating scientific and farmers\' evaluation of soil quality indicators in Central Kenya\"}','integrating-scientific-and-farmers-evaluation-of-soil-quality-indicators-in-central-kenya_2019-07-25_10:10:41',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Abstract\\r\\n<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A study was conducted to determine farmers\' perceptions of soil quality and common soil management practices that influenced soil fertility\\r\\nwithin farmers\' fields in Chuka and Gachoka divisions, Kenya. Soils were characterised by smallholders after which they were geo-referenced and\\r\\nsampled at surface depth (0\\u201320 cm) for subsequent physical and chemical analyses, to determine differences within farmers\' soil quality\\r\\ncategories. Indicators for distinguishing productive and non-productive fields included crop yield and performance, soil colour and soil texture.\\r\\nThere were significant differences among soil fertility categories, using parametric techniques (ANOVA) for key soil properties (pb0.005),\\r\\nimplying that there was a qualitative difference in the soils that were characterised as different by farmers. Fertile soils had significantly higher pH,\\r\\ntotal organic carbon, exchangeable cations and available-N. Factor analysis on 15 soil properties identified 4 main factors that explained 68% of\\r\\nthe total variance in soil quality. The four Varimax-rotated factors were designated as contrasts that described soil quality status on farmers\' fields.\\r\\nThe first factor grouped calcium, magnesium and soil pH, while the second component comprised available nitrogen, organic carbon and total\\r\\nnitrogen. The third factor included plant nutrients mainly extractable phosphorus and available nitrogen, while the fourth factor comprised soil\\r\\nphysical properties (macroaggregates, microaggregates, silt, and clay). Soil fertility and crop management practices that were investigated\\r\\nindicated that farmers understood and consequently utilised spatial heterogeneity and temporal variability in soil quality status within their farms\\r\\nas a resource to maintain or enhance agricultural productivity.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\u00a9 2007 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. \\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,17,'cover_images/troves/54e34e6fa72ffcd55b9437a7bb4ddbd0.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.academia.edu/13725917/Integrating_scientific_and_farmers_evaluation_of_soil_quality_indicators_in_Central_Kenya\"}]}',NULL,'2007-01-01','2019-07-25 10:10:41','2019-10-23 14:46:18',NULL,NULL,'files/integrating-scientific-and-farmers-evaluation-of-soil-quality-indicators-in-central-kenya_2019-07-25_10:10:41/integrating-scientific-and-farmers-evaluation-of-soil-quality-indicators-in-central-kenya_2019-07-25_10:10:41.zip',1),(313,'{\"en\":\"Building and Assessing Soil Health Across the CCRP Program: A cross-cutting soils effort within McKnight communities of practice\",\"es\":\"Construyendo y Evaluando la Salud del Suelo en el Programa CCRP: un proyecto trasversal en las comunidades de pra\\u0301ctica McKnight\"}','building-and-assessing-soil-health-across-the-ccrp-program-a-cross-cutting-soils-effort-within-mcknight-communities-of-practice_2019-07-25_10:43:26',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A poster summarising information about a project to implement a Soil Tool Kit which can be used by partners on smallholder farms to collect information about soil health and build a better understanding of the impact of management, crop rotations, forages and residue management. <\\/p><div class=\\\"site-branding\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p class=\\\"site-title\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/smallholder-sha.org\\/\\\" rel=\\\"home\\\">Smallholder Soil Health Assessment<\\/a><\\/p><p class=\\\"site-title\\\"><br><\\/p><p class=\\\"site-title\\\"><br><\\/p><p class=\\\"site-title\\\">Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p><br><\\/div>\",\"es\":\"Un p\\u00f3ster que resume la informaci\\u00f3n sobre un proyecto para implementar un Kit de herramientas de suelo que puede ser utilizado por socios en peque\\u00f1as granjas para recopilar informaci\\u00f3n sobre la salud del suelo y comprender mejor el impacto del manejo, la rotaci\\u00f3n de cultivos, los forrajes y el manejo de residuos.\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/d55a4aae84dfe61167bb8971231f5add.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/building-and-assessing-soil-health-across-the-ccrp-program-a-cross-cutting-soils-effort-within-mcknight-communities-of-practice_2019-07-25_10:43:26\\\\/2019-07-25_10:43:26_east-africa-cop-poster-2018-vanek-soils.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-07-25_10:43:26_east-africa-cop-poster-2018-vanek-soils.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"East_Africa_CoP_poster_2018_Vanek-Soils.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":1141167,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\", \"es\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/building-and-assessing-soil-health-across-the-ccrp-program-a-cross-cutting-soils-effort-within-mcknight-communities-of-practice_2019-07-25_10:43:26\\\\/2019-07-30_09:38:54_andes-cdp-poster-2018-vanek-suelos.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-07-30_09:38:54_andes-cdp-poster-2018-vanek-suelos.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Andes_CdP_poster_2018_Vanek_Suelos.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":1262793,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 10:43:28','2019-10-23 14:46:23',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(314,'{\"en\":\"Soil Management And Agrodiversity: A Case Study From Arumeru, Arusha, Tanzania\"}','soil-management-and-agrodiversity-a-case-study-from-arumeru-arusha-tanzania_2019-07-25_11:12:58',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A case study produced for the symposium on Managing biodiversity in agricultural systems, Montreal, 8-12 November, 2001.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\">The paper examines methods and practices for farming and soil management used by farmers in Arumeru for addressing decreased crop yields associated with poor soil fertility, and how a focus on \'agrodiversity\' is helping them work in challenging conditions.<br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Extract:<\\/span><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\"><br><\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 1\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\u201cManagement diversity\\u201d (i.e. land transforming operations which influence the behavior of physical and\\r\\nchemical aspects of the soil, surface and near surface physical and biological processes, hydrology, micro-\\r\\nclimate etc. (Brookfield and Stocking, 1999) and its impact on agrodiversity) is the focus of this paper.\\r\\nDifferent methods of managing the land, water and biota for crop production and the maintenance of soil\\r\\nfertility and structure are examined. Diverse soil management methods used by farmers in Arumeru to\\r\\naddress diverse constraints all aimed at soil productivity improvement, agrodiversity enhancement and\\r\\nconservation are considered.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<\\/div><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}',7,17,'cover_images/troves/c22f0356a9958ef38c119cd91627b4c1.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.fao.org/fileadmin/user_upload/kagera/resource/soil_management_agrobiodiversity.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2001-11-01','2019-07-25 11:12:58','2019-10-23 14:46:30',NULL,NULL,'files/soil-management-and-agrodiversity-a-case-study-from-arumeru-arusha-tanzania_2019-07-25_11:12:58/soil-management-and-agrodiversity-a-case-study-from-arumeru-arusha-tanzania_2019-07-25_11:12:58.zip',1),(315,'{\"en\":\"Testing Your Soil With Plants\"}','testing-your-soil-with-plants_2019-07-25_11:22:01',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A short guide with instructions on how a farmer can analyse their soil by examining the plants growing in it, without the need for laboratory testing, which is expensive and inaccessible for many smallholder farmers.<\\/p><p>The document explains the advantages of this approach, and provides information on what various symptoms, observable in plants, might indicate about the health and fertility of soil.<\\/p><p>By \\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<style>\\r\\n<!--\\r\\n \\/* Font Definitions *\\/\\r\\n @font-face\\r\\n\\t{font-family:\\\"Cambria Math\\\";\\r\\n\\tpanose-1:2 4 5 3 5 4 6 3 2 4;\\r\\n\\tmso-font-charset:0;\\r\\n\\tmso-generic-font-family:roman;\\r\\n\\tmso-font-pitch:variable;\\r\\n\\tmso-font-signature:3 0 0 0 1 0;}\\r\\n@font-face\\r\\n\\t{font-family:Calibri;\\r\\n\\tpanose-1:2 15 5 2 2 2 4 3 2 4;\\r\\n\\tmso-font-charset:0;\\r\\n\\tmso-generic-font-family:swiss;\\r\\n\\tmso-font-pitch:variable;\\r\\n\\tmso-font-signature:-536858881 -1073732485 9 0 511 0;}\\r\\n \\/* Style Definitions *\\/\\r\\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\\r\\n\\t{mso-style-unhide:no;\\r\\n\\tmso-style-qformat:yes;\\r\\n\\tmso-style-parent:\\\"\\\";\\r\\n\\tmargin-top:0cm;\\r\\n\\tmargin-right:0cm;\\r\\n\\tmargin-bottom:10.0pt;\\r\\n\\tmargin-left:0cm;\\r\\n\\tline-height:115%;\\r\\n\\tmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\\r\\n\\tfont-size:11.0pt;\\r\\n\\tfont-family:\\\"Calibri\\\",sans-serif;\\r\\n\\tmso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\\r\\n\\tmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\\r\\n\\tmso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;\\r\\n\\tmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;\\r\\n\\tmso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\\r\\n\\tmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\\r\\n\\tmso-bidi-font-family:\\\"Times New Roman\\\";\\r\\n\\tmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;\\r\\n\\tmso-ansi-language:EN-US;\\r\\n\\tmso-fareast-language:EN-US;}\\r\\n.MsoChpDefault\\r\\n\\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\\r\\n\\tmso-default-props:yes;\\r\\n\\tfont-size:11.0pt;\\r\\n\\tmso-ansi-font-size:11.0pt;\\r\\n\\tmso-bidi-font-size:11.0pt;\\r\\n\\tfont-family:\\\"Calibri\\\"