d health risks.<br><\\/p><p>Food systems are a major driver of climate change. In turn, climate change exacerbates a range of health risks associated with food systems. <\\/p><p>Extracted from the report, \'<span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\"><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ipes-food.org\\/_img\\/upload\\/files\\/Health_FullReport(1).pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Unravelling The Food\\u2013Health Nexus Addressing Practices, Political Economy, And Power Relations To Build Healthier Food Systems<\\/a><\\/span>\', produced by PES-Food for the Global Alliance. <br><\\/p><p>Graphic produced by Hypenotic.<br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/213586bb0f6da43e8e07f8d4997f1c29.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/diagram-the-food-health-climate-nexus_2019-07-25_13:27:20\\\\/2019-07-25_13:27:20_5-thefood-health-climatenexus-e1508790353357.jpg\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-07-25_13:27:20_5-thefood-health-climatenexus-e1508790353357.jpg\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"5_TheFood-Health-Climatenexus-e1508790353357.jpg\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"jpg\\\",\\\"size\\\":198198,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2017-10-01','2019-07-25 13:27:30','2019-08-21 14:49:03','2019-08-21 14:49:03',NULL,'files/diagram-the-food-health-climate-nexus_2019-07-25_13:27:20/diagram-the-food-health-climate-nexus_2019-07-25_13:27:20.zip',0),(317,'{\"en\":\"Diagram: How food systems affect human health - Five Channels of Impact\"}','diagram-how-food-systems-affect-human-health-five-channels-of-impact_2019-07-25_13:34:43',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>Diagram showing How food systems affect human health. <\\/p><p>Food systems affect human health through five key channels. The resulting health impacts are exacerbated by a series of factors shown on the right of the diagram.<\\/p><p> <p>Extracted from the report, \'<span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\"><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.ipes-food.org\\/_img\\/upload\\/files\\/Health_FullReport(1).pdf\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Unravelling The Food\\u2013Health Nexus Addressing Practices, Political Economy, And Power Relations To Build Healthier Food Systems<\\/a><\\/span>\', produced by PES-Food for the Global Alliance. <br><\\/p>Graphic produced by Hypenotic.<\\/p>\"}',7,20,'cover_images/troves/064dffdbfac52b5870f81ce6f65fa7be.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/diagram-how-food-systems-affect-human-health-five-channels-of-impact_2019-07-25_13:34:43\\\\/2019-07-25_13:34:43_2-5-channelsofimpact-e1508790591127.jpg\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-07-25_13:34:43_2-5-channelsofimpact-e1508790591127.jpg\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"2_5-channelsofimpact-e1508790591127.jpg\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"jpg\\\",\\\"size\\\":115710,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2017-12-01','2019-07-25 13:34:44','2019-08-21 14:49:41','2019-08-21 14:49:41',NULL,'files/diagram-how-food-systems-affect-human-health-five-channels-of-impact_2019-07-25_13:34:43/diagram-how-food-systems-affect-human-health-five-channels-of-impact_2019-07-25_13:34:43.zip',0),(318,'{\"en\":\"Bambara market growth and utilization\"}','bambara-market-growth-and-utilization_2019-07-25_13:52:27',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A brochure promoting the benefits of the \\\"underutilized\\\" bambara groundnut, particularly as a source of protein in Malawi, where protein-malnutrition is a public health concern. Includes details of uses, varieties, health benefits and nutritional composition. <\\/p><p>The brochure also sets out the objectives of the BAMGNUT Project, which aims to increase bambara production and consumption. <\\/p><p>Produced by Dr . A. Mwangwela  with Lilongwe University of Agriculture and Natural Resources.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/9a96161da53762669d5137967ba38331.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/bambara-market-growth-and-utilization_2019-07-25_13:52:27\\\\/2019-07-25_13:52:27_bambara-brochure-malawi.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-07-25_13:52:27_bambara-brochure-malawi.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"bambara_brochure-Malawi.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":951625,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 13:52:28','2019-10-23 14:47:11',NULL,NULL,'files/bambara-market-growth-and-utilization_2019-07-25_13:52:27/bambara-market-growth-and-utilization_2019-07-25_13:52:27.zip',1),(319,'{\"en\":\"The Talking Toolkit. How smallholding farmers and local governments can together adapt to climate change\"}','the-talking-toolkit-how-smallholding-farmers-and-local-governments-can-together-adapt-to-climate-change_2019-07-25_14:12:16',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A resource available online from the World Agroforestry Centre (ICRAF).<span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Description from the website:<\\/span><br><\\/p><p>\\\"We have created this toolkit to help everyone better understand the \\r\\nexposure of farmers to climate change and variability, what impact it \\r\\nmight have on them and food production, and how they can adapt. This \\r\\ncollection of participatory exercises, which we call \\u2018tools\\u2019, are \\r\\ndesigned for those who facilitate discussions with farmers: development \\r\\nworkers, researchers, agricultural organizations and government \\r\\npolicy-makers. We assume that you are involved in a research or \\r\\ndevelopment project related to disaster and climate change and want to \\r\\nlearn how to use proven research methods to achieve the project\\u2019s \\r\\nobjectives. The tools have all been designed to help clear and practical\\r\\n communication about extreme weather events, climate change and \\r\\nvariability and the ways we can start to adapt to our changing \\r\\nenvironment. They help survey the needs and build on the knowledge of \\r\\nfarmers, establishing what is the \\u2018baseline\\u2019 or starting point for \\r\\ndevelopment and land-use plans. The Talking Toolkit has been supported \\r\\nby the CGIAR Research Programs on Forests, Trees and Agroforestry, and \\r\\non Climate Change, Agriculture and Food Security.\\\"<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\"}',7,21,'cover_images/troves/238305b53e1d4944ce4bd18641700c9b.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.worldagroforestry.org/output/talking-toolkit\"}]}',NULL,'2013-01-01','2019-07-25 14:12:17','2019-10-23 14:47:18',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(320,'{\"en\":\"Poster - Trees in multi-Use Landscapes in Southeast Asia (TULSEA): A negotiation support toolbox for Integrated Natural Resource Management (INRM)\"}','poster-trees-in-multi-use-landscapes-in-southeast-asia-tulsea-a-negotiation-support-toolbox-for-integrated-natural-resource-management-inrm_2019-07-25_14:30:50',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-above field-wrapper body field\\\"><div class=\\\"field-label\\\">TULSEA poster available from World Agroforestry Centre (ICRAF) website<span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">.<br><\\/span><\\/div><div class=\\\"field-label\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/div><div class=\\\"field-label\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Abstract:&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/div><p>The\\r\\n negotiation support systems (NSS) approach that ICRAF developed in SE \\r\\nAsia requires tools or instruments for rapid appraisal of the site \\r\\nspecific form of general problems and issues. The TUL-SEA project will \\r\\nfurther develop the\'toolbox\' containing Participatory Landscape \\r\\nAppraisal (PALA), Rapid appraisal of tenure claims (RATA), market (RMA),\\r\\n hydrology (RHA), agrobiodiversity (RABA) and carbon stocks (RaCSA). It \\r\\nwill also test and further develop the simulation models for scenario \\r\\nanalysis of landscape-level impacts of changes in market access (FALLOW)\\r\\n or agroforestry technology (WaNuLCAS). These tools may be used by local\\r\\n resource managers or national institutions to appraise the likely \\r\\nimpacts of new technologies and changes in market access and to support \\r\\nevidence-based negotiations of contentious issues. Therefore, ICRAF is \\r\\nmanaging the Trees in multi-Use Landscapes in Southeast Asia (TULSEA) \\r\\nproject to bridge perception gaps between stakeholders (local, \\r\\npublic\\/policy and scientific knowledge paradigms), increase recognition \\r\\nand respect for these multiple knowledge systems, provide quantification\\r\\n of tradeoffs between economic and environmental impacts at landscape \\r\\nscale, and enable joint analysis of plausible scenarios based on \\r\\navailable data and information. The activities of TULSEA Project are \\r\\ndivided into 4 working packages (WP), there are WP1 for improving the \\r\\ntools from existing generic tools and methods, WP2 for capacity \\r\\nbuilding, WP3 for site testing of the tools and WP4 for synthesis. The \\r\\nproject may be able to improved land use practices contribute to \\r\\nincreased and sustained productivity and conservation, reduced conflicts\\r\\n and equitable use of land, water and forest resources in multi-use \\r\\nlandscapes with trees while the income of smallholder producers is \\r\\nincreased through research relevant to major high value fruit and other \\r\\ntree production systems.<\\/p>\\r\\n<\\/div>\"}',7,20,'cover_images/troves/43c8d0e6e3f38c400f647afca4b38a5b.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.worldagroforestry.org/publication/trees-multi-use-landscapes-southeast-asia-tulsea-negotiation-support-toolbox-integrated\"}]}',NULL,'2008-01-01','2019-07-25 14:30:51','2019-07-25 14:48:45','2019-07-25 14:48:45',NULL,NULL,0),(321,'{\"en\":\"Payment for Ecosystem Services - Co-investment in ecosystem services: global lessons from payment and incentive schemes.\"}','payment-for-ecosystem-services-co-investment-in-ecosystem-services-global-lessons-from-payment-and-incentive-schemes_2019-07-25_14:39:55',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A book, produced by World Agroforestry Centre (ICRAF), available from <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.worldagroforestry.org\\/sd\\/environmental-services\\/PES\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">their website<\\/a>.<br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"><\\/span><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Description from the website:<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\"><\\/span><\\/p><p>This publication discusses key lessons \\r\\nfrom various development stages of landscape stewardship for ecosystem \\r\\nservices provision. It focuses in particular on agricultural landscapes \\r\\nin Africa, Asia, and Latin America, which have not featured prominently \\r\\nin existing literature.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Human use, \\r\\noveruse and neglect are degrading ecosystems, the very fabric which is \\r\\nproducing ecosystem services that benefit human well-being, and which \\r\\nallowed natural capital to develop. Stewardships that might ensure \\r\\necosystem service provision in agricultural landscapes, are in reality \\r\\nextensively complex and comprise the interaction of social-ecological \\r\\nsystems in a world ruled by economic and political feedback. In order to\\r\\n ensure their operationalization and sustainability, empirical cases of \\r\\nlandscape stewardship for ecosystem service provisions in Africa and \\r\\nAsia show that incentive-based mechanisms, as a ways of governing the \\r\\nlandscape, need to be fair to the actors involved as well as fulfil \\r\\ntheir main goal of providing ecosystem services efficiently.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">A host of rich and diverse empirical cases are the result of more than a decade of field experience with Pro-poor Rewards for Environmental Services in Africa (PRESA) and Rewarding the Upland Poor for Environmental Services (RUPES) in Asia, two projects coordinated by the World Agroforestry Centre. This book highlights the gaps between the theory and the implementation of operational and sustainable ecosystem service incentive-based mechanisms on the ground. It provides and reviews arguments as to why specific forms of payment for ecosystem services (PES) schemes (including pro-poor payments, rewards, and co-investment) can be viable approaches toward sustainable land-use practices.<br><br>To this end, this book:<\\/p><ul><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Provides new insights that support development practitioners with appropriate leverage points so that they may increase the potential of payment for ecosystem service (PES) schemes to deliver the desired outcomes.<\\/li><li style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Stimulates debate among scientists and analysts about PES as a theory of change in the developing-world context and where new models or knowledge are needed.<br><\\/li><\\/ul><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Recommends appropriate interventions for policy-makers to apply PES as a tool for sustainable land governance and management in contexts where poverty is rampant, business activity is low and environmental funds need to be better targeted in providing ecosystem services.<\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\"><br><\\/p><p style=\\\"text-align: justify;\\\">Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <br><br><\\/p>\"}',7,21,'cover_images/troves/1f18e1bc4d7d1aa45aa5ec8d981a21f0.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.worldagroforestry.org/sd/environmental-services/PES\"}]}',NULL,'2018-06-01','2019-07-25 14:39:56','2019-10-23 14:47:48',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(322,'{\"en\":\"5Capitals: A Tool for Assessing the Poverty Impacts of Value Chain Development\"}','5capitals-a-tool-for-assessing-the-poverty-impacts-of-value-chain-development_2019-07-25_15:09:47',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>The 5Capitals manual and other publications, available from World Agroforestry Centre (ICRAF).<br><\\/p><p>From the website:<br><\\/p><p>The 5Capitals toolkit provides those interested in value chain \\r\\ndevelopment with an innovative framework for assessing outcomes and \\r\\nimpacts. The framework focuses on understanding the needs and \\r\\ncircumstances of smallholders and local enterprises engaged in value \\r\\nchain development and helping stakeholders in value chain development to\\r\\n design interventions that better respond to these actors.<\\/p><p>The 5Capitals manual, titled <em>5Capitals: A Tool for Assessing the Poverty Impacts of Value Chain Development, <\\/em>was\\r\\n designed by an international team of development practitioners, \\r\\nresearchers and donors and was tested extensively in Asia, Africa, the \\r\\nUnited States and Latin America. Design of the tool was led by CATIE \\r\\nwith financial support from the Ford Foundation.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Note: This resource was added to this database as part of a migration of\\r\\n resources from the now defunct CCRP Sphaera platform, and is still \\r\\nawaiting a comprehensive review and quality check. <\\/p>\"}',7,21,'cover_images/troves/9ff4ec233e42bb18fd58f260822af0a5.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.worldagroforestry.org/output/5capitals-toolkit\"}]}',NULL,'2012-06-01','2019-07-25 15:09:48','2019-10-23 14:47:59',NULL,NULL,'files/5capitals-a-tool-for-assessing-the-poverty-impacts-of-value-chain-development_2019-07-25_15:09:47/5capitals-a-tool-for-assessing-the-poverty-impacts-of-value-chain-development_2019-07-25_15:09:47.zip',1),(323,'{\"en\":\"Video: Integrated approach against striga\",\"fr\":\"Lutte int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e contre striga\"}','video-integrated-approach-against-striga_2019-07-25_15:20:29',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced for ICRISAT about using multiple control methods to reduce striga and obtain a good yield of sorghum, millet, maize or rice. Available in many languages.<\\/p><br>\",\"fr\":\"Une vid\\u00e9o r\\u00e9alis\\u00e9e pour l\'ICRISAT sur l\'utilisation de plusieurs m\\u00e9thodes de contr\\u00f4le pour r\\u00e9duire la striga et obtenir un bon rendement en sorgho, mil, ma\\u00efs ou riz.\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/6f322085edd2d901fb42ce80bda6ed1e.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\", \"fr\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/integrated-approach-against-striga\"}], \"fr\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/fr/lutte-integree-contre-striga\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 15:20:29','2019-10-23 14:49:25',NULL,NULL,'files/video-integrated-approach-against-striga_2019-07-25_15:20:29/video-integrated-approach-against-striga_2019-07-25_15:20:29.zip',1),(324,'{\"en\":\"Video: Striga Biology\",\"fr\":\"La biologie du striga\"}','video-striga-biology_2019-07-25_15:36:23',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced for ICRISAT about striga, a parasitic weed that causes great yield losses from cereal crops. Provides information about the biology, including the tiny seeds, germination, how it spreads, and how communities must work together to prevent its spread. Available in many languages.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><br>\",\"fr\":\"Une vid\\u00e9o r\\u00e9alis\\u00e9e pour l\'ICRISAT sur la striga, une adventice parasite qui provoque de grandes pertes de rendement pour les cultures de c\\u00e9r\\u00e9ales. Fournit des informations sur la biologie, notamment les graines minuscules, la germination, son mode de propagation et la mani\\u00e8re dont les communaut\\u00e9s doivent travailler ensemble pour en pr\\u00e9venir le d\\u00e9veloppement.\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/90357e228ada03cd9ef94845c872b412.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\", \"fr\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/striga-biology\"}], \"fr\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/fr/la-biologie-du-striga\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 15:36:23','2019-10-23 14:49:19',NULL,NULL,'files/video-striga-biology_2019-07-25_15:36:23/video-striga-biology_2019-07-25_15:36:23.zip',1),(325,'{\"en\":\"Video: Joining hands against striga\",\"fr\":\"L\\u2019arrachage manuel du striga\"}','joining-hands-against-striga_2019-07-25_16:06:15',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced for ICRISAT about ways of managing and preventing the spread of the parasitic striga weed, and the importance of farmer communities cooperating to help prevent major yield losses. Available in many languages.<br><\\/p><br>\",\"fr\":\"Une vid\\u00e9o r\\u00e9alis\\u00e9e pour l\'ICRISAT sur les moyens de g\\u00e9rer et de pr\\u00e9venir la propagation de la striga, une herbe parasite, et sur l\'importance de la coop\\u00e9ration des communaut\\u00e9s d\'agriculteurs pour \\u00e9viter des pertes de rendement importantes.\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/cdb3649bd036a5987e7593b64148668e.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\", \"fr\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/joining-hands-against-striga\"}], \"fr\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/fr/larrachage-manuel-du-striga\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 16:06:15','2019-10-23 14:49:11',NULL,NULL,'files/joining-hands-against-striga_2019-07-25_16:06:15/joining-hands-against-striga_2019-07-25_16:06:15.zip',1),(326,'{\"en\":\"Video: Composting to beat striga\",\"fr\":\"Du compost contre le striga\"}','video-composting-to-beat-striga_2019-07-25_16:23:41',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced for ICRISAT about the benefits of using compost over manure. What is less known is that the \\r\\nmicro-organisms in compost attack striga seeds in the soil. Compost also\\r\\n decreases the amount of striga that will sprout, and reduces its \\r\\nnegative effect on cereal crops.<\\/p><p>The video also talks about how to make compost, showing how farmers in northeast\\r\\n Mali make compost as one of the strategies of integrated striga and \\r\\nsoil fertility management.<\\/p><p>Available in many languages.<\\/p>\",\"fr\":\"Une vid\\u00e9o r\\u00e9alis\\u00e9e pour l\'ICRISAT sur les avantages de l\'utilisation du compost sur le fumier. Ce que l\\u2019on sait moins, c\\u2019est que les micro-organismes pr\\u00e9sents dans le compost attaquent les graines de striga dans le sol. Le compost diminue \\u00e9galement la quantit\\u00e9 de striga qui va germer, ainsi que ses effets n\\u00e9gatifs sur les cultures de c\\u00e9r\\u00e9ales.<br><br>La vid\\u00e9o explique \\u00e9galement comment faire du compost, montrant comment les agriculteurs du nord-est du Mali font du compost l\'une des strat\\u00e9gies de gestion int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e de la striga et de la fertilit\\u00e9 des sols.\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/21ff80c79cd30b9e962d197d71c53000.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\", \"fr\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/composting-beat-striga\"}], \"fr\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/fr/du-compost-contre-le-striga\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 16:23:41','2019-08-21 14:53:25',NULL,NULL,'files/video-composting-to-beat-striga_2019-07-25_16:23:41/video-composting-to-beat-striga_2019-07-25_16:23:41.zip',1),(327,'{\"en\":\"Video: Grow Row by Row\",\"fr\":\"Cultiver ligne par ligne\"}','video-grow-row-by-row_2019-07-25_16:30:51',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A video produced by ICRISAT about planting methods and practices that can be used to help manage striga. Available in many languages.<\\/p><p>\\\"Farmers in northern Nigeria are changing the way they intercrop their \\r\\nsorghum and millet with cowpea. By planting both crops at higher \\r\\ndensities and in separate rows, and by applying some organic and mineral\\r\\n fertilizer, they harvest more and reduce damage by the parasitic weed \\r\\nstriga. It is one of the strategies of integrated striga and soil \\r\\nfertility management.\\\"<\\/p>\",\"fr\":\"<p>Une vid\\u00e9o produite par l\'ICRISAT sur les m\\u00e9thodes et pratiques de plantation pouvant \\u00eatre utilis\\u00e9es pour aider \\u00e0 g\\u00e9rer la striga.<\\/p><p>\\\"Les agriculteurs du nord du Nigeria changent la fa\\u00e7on dont ils \\r\\nintercalent leurs sorgho et mil avec le ni\\u00e9b\\u00e9. En semant les deux \\r\\ncultures \\u00e0 plus haute densit\\u00e9 et dans des lignes s\\u00e9par\\u00e9es, et en \\r\\nappliquant un peu d\'engrais organiques et min\\u00e9ral, ils r\\u00e9coltent plus et\\r\\n r\\u00e9duisent les dommages caus\\u00e9s par le striga, une mauvaise herbe \\r\\nparasitaire. C\\u2019est une des strat\\u00e9gies de la gestion int\\u00e9gr\\u00e9e du striga \\r\\net de la fertilit\\u00e9 du sol.\\\"<\\/p>\"}',7,16,'cover_images/troves/1ce16120d8f512a5445a5e0cd414828a.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\", \"fr\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/grow-row-row\"}], \"fr\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/fr/cultiver-ligne-par-ligne\"}, {}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-07-25 16:30:51','2019-08-21 14:54:14',NULL,NULL,'files/video-grow-row-by-row_2019-07-25_16:30:51/video-grow-row-by-row_2019-07-25_16:30:51.zip',1),(328,'{\"en\":\"Langscape Magazine Vol. 2  Issue 12 - Emerging Paradigms Series Part 1: Biocultural Diversity: An Emerging Paradigm in a Changing World\"}','langscape-magazine-vol-2-issue-12-emerging-paradigms-series-part-1-biocultural-diversity-an-emerging-paradigm-in-a-changing-world_2019-07-25_17:18:25',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\">Langscape<\\/span> is a magazine published by the international nonprofit organisation, Terralingua. Its focus is biocultural diversity, and it aims to \\\"promote a paradigm shift by illustrating biocultural diversity through scientific and traditional knowledge, within an elegant sensory context of articles, stories and art.\\\"<\\/p><p>This issue contains a number of articles relevant to