L,0),(394,'{\"en\":\"Access Agriculture\",\"es\":\"Access Agriculture\",\"fr\":\"Access Agriculture\"}','access-agriculture_2019-08-15_16:29:17',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.accessagriculture.org\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Access Agriculture<\\/a> is an international NGO which showcases agricultural training videos in local languages. These are ideal for farmer training, and may be of interest to researchers , students, extensionists, educators and, of course, farmers. To develop local language versions, mass multiply and disseminate \\r\\nagricultural training videos, Access Agriculture collaborates with more than 200 communication professionals across the globe.<\\/p><p>Their website hosts many training videos in support of sustainable agriculture in developing countries. These are well-produced, easy to understand and available in multiple languages. The videos may be downloaded, and many come with related written materials as well. <br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\",\"es\":\"<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.accessagriculture.org\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Access Agriculture<\\/a> es una ONG internacional que exhibe videos de capacitaci\\u00f3n agr\\u00edcola en los idiomas locales. Estos son ideales para la capacitaci\\u00f3n de agricultores y pueden ser de inter\\u00e9s para investigadores, estudiantes, extensionistas, educadores y, por supuesto, agricultores. Para desarrollar versiones en el idioma local, multiplicar en masa y difundir videos de capacitaci\\u00f3n agr\\u00edcola, Access Agriculture colabora con m\\u00e1s de 200 profesionales de la comunicaci\\u00f3n en todo el mundo.<br><br>Su sitio web alberga muchos videos de capacitaci\\u00f3n en apoyo de la agricultura sostenible en los pa\\u00edses en desarrollo. Est\\u00e1n bien producidos, son f\\u00e1ciles de entender y est\\u00e1n disponibles en varios idiomas. Los videos se pueden descargar, y muchos vienen con materiales escritos relacionados tambi\\u00e9n.\",\"fr\":\"<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.accessagriculture.org\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Access Agriculture<\\/a> est une ONG internationale qui pr\\u00e9sente des vid\\u00e9os de formation agricole dans les langues locales. Celles-ci sont id\\u00e9ales pour la formation des agriculteurs et peuvent int\\u00e9resser les chercheurs, les \\u00e9tudiants, les vulgarisateurs, les \\u00e9ducateurs et, bien s\\u00fbr, les agriculteurs. Pour d\\u00e9velopper des versions en langue locale, multiplier en masse et diffuser des vid\\u00e9os de formation en agriculture, Access Agriculture collabore avec plus de 200 professionnels de la communication du monde entier.<br><br>Leur site Web h\\u00e9berge de nombreuses vid\\u00e9os de formation en faveur de l\'agriculture durable dans les pays en d\\u00e9veloppement. Celles-ci sont bien produites, faciles \\u00e0 comprendre et disponibles dans plusieurs langues. Les vid\\u00e9os peuvent \\u00eatre t\\u00e9l\\u00e9charg\\u00e9es et nombre d\'entre elles sont accompagn\\u00e9es de documents \\u00e9crits.<br>\"}',7,21,'cover_images/troves/0728f32c935c44c396815d09a27a3260.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\", \"es\": \"[]\", \"fr\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/\"}], \"es\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/\"}], \"fr\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.accessagriculture.org/\"}]}',NULL,NULL,'2019-08-15 16:29:18','2019-08-20 15:31:39',NULL,NULL,'files/access-agriculture_2019-08-15_16:29:17/access-agriculture_2019-08-15_16:29:17.zip',1),(395,'{\"en\":\"Designing Participatory On-Farm Experiments: Resources for Training\"}','designing-participatory-on-farm-experiments-resources-for-training_2019-08-15_17:03:00',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 9\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A collection of training materials to support the design of participatory on-farm experiments. <\\/p><p>This book contains training guidelines and materials, a collection of theme papers and toolkit papers. It provides valuable reference and practical guidance for anyone interested in participatory research. <br><\\/p><p>The materials in the publication  resulted from a series of four training\\r\\nworkshops on participatory on-farm experiments organized by the Statistical Services Centre\\r\\nbetween\\r\\n1995 and 2000 for the benefit of scientists and technicians working \\r\\nunder its collaborative research and development programmes and \\r\\nprojects. <\\/p><p>The materials were developed collaboratively between the World Agroforestry Centre and\\r\\nthe Statistical Services Centre of the University of Reading, with financial support from the following: Netherlands\' Government, European\\r\\nCommission, United Kingdom Department For International Development, Swedish\\r\\nInternational Development Agency, Canadian International Development Agency,\\r\\nRockefeller Foundation and others.<\\/p><\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/8472191010421fc1e805bb990abea3f3.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/designing-participatory-on-farm-experiments-resources-for-training_2019-08-15_17:03:00\\\\/2019-08-15_17:03:00_designing-participatory-on-farm-experiments1.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-15_17:03:00_designing-participatory-on-farm-experiments1.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Designing_Participatory_On-farm_experiments(1).pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":18735757,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2003-01-01','2019-08-15 17:03:01','2019-08-16 10:53:34',NULL,NULL,'files/designing-participatory-on-farm-experiments-resources-for-training_2019-08-15_17:03:00/designing-participatory-on-farm-experiments-resources-for-training_2019-08-15_17:03:00.zip',1),(396,'{\"en\":\"How select an 5-17 years old girl household member randomly with ODK form\"}','how-select-an-5-17-years-old-girl-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-16_16:04:17',NULL,'{\"en\":null}',2,13,NULL,0,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,NULL,'2019-08-16 16:04:17','2019-08-20 14:55:44','2019-08-20 14:55:44',NULL,NULL,0),(397,'{\"en\":\"How select a household member randomly with ODK form\"}','how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-16_16:41:58',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\">This is an example of selecting a household member randomly using an XLS form.&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">The name, age and gender of each household member are entered using a repeat group and the name of girl selected is displayed in the last note.&nbsp;<\\/span><div><br><\\/div><div><span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\">The example works as follows:<\\/span><\\/div><div><span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\"><br><\\/span><\\/div><ol><li><span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\">You build the roster within the repeat group.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/li><li><span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\"><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">Within each repeat group, the <\\/span><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; font-weight: bold;\\\">eligibleGirl <\\/span><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">calculate field is populated with the person\\u2019s name if and only if they are \\u201celigible\\u201d. <\\/span><\\/span><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\">In the example given here, &nbsp;only 5-17 year old females are eligible. This condition can be modified by changing the &nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">eligibleGirl <\\/span>calculate statement:<\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;\\\">&nbsp;if(${age}&gt;4 and ${age}&lt;18 and ${female}=1, ${name},\\\"\\\" )<\\/span>.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/li><li><span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\"><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">After the repeat group, the <\\/span><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; font-weight: bold;\\\">join() <\\/span><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\">statement is used to generate a list of space-separated names - this is the full list of \\u201celigible\\u201d household members - the list you will then choose a random name from.&nbsp;<\\/span><\\/span><\\/li><li><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; font-family: Arial;\\\">Finally,&nbsp;<\\/span><span style=\\\"-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: Arial;\\\">&nbsp;the <span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">selectedGirl <\\/span>calculate field selects a random name from the list&nbsp;with <\\/span><span style=\\\"font-family: &quot;Courier New&quot;;\\\">selected-at(${listgirspos},int(random()*${n_selected}))<\\/span>. &nbsp;<\\/span><\\/li><\\/ol>\"}',2,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-16_16:41:58\\\\/2019-08-16_16:41:58_random-list-name.xlsx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-16_16:41:58_random-list-name.xlsx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"random_list_name.xlsx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"xlsx\\\",\\\"size\\\":11149,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2019-08-01','2019-08-16 16:41:59','2019-08-20 14:55:48','2019-08-20 14:55:48',NULL,'files/how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-16_16:41:58/how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-16_16:41:58.zip',0),(398,'{\"en\":\"How select a household member randomly with ODK form\"}','how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-20_10:45:41',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This is an example of selecting randomly a female household member with age between 5 and 17. Inside the repeat group, the position function calculates the current iteration index and the conditional if adds the index into a list, if the girls are eligible. Outside the repeat group, the girl has selected from the index generated randomly. The name is displayed with indexed-repeat() that return the name by index.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>The ODK form returns the list of the eligible girls\' ID,&nbsp; the number of girls eligible, the ID of the girl selected and the full name of the girl selected.<\\/p><p>&nbsp;<\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">Uses:<\\/span><\\/p><p>You can modify the if statement in the \'eligibleGirl\' field to use what-ever criteria you wanted. For example, if you had a question about the member\'s current eduction, you could use this template to select a random household member who was currently attending school.&nbsp;<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}',2,13,'cover_images/troves/1abf0867a3120370be9cbfa298149941.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-20_10:45:41\\\\/2019-08-20_11:44:11_random-list-name.xlsx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-20_11:44:11_random-list-name.xlsx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"random-list-name.xlsx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"xlsx\\\",\\\"size\\\":14624,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2019-08-01','2019-08-20 10:45:41','2019-08-20 11:44:12',NULL,NULL,'files/how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-20_10:45:41/how-select-a-household-member-randomly-with-odk-form_2019-08-20_10:45:41.zip',1),(399,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Approaches to the Analysis of Survey Data\"}','statistical-guides-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-survey-data_2019-08-20_16:07:50',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on how to approach the analysis of survey data. <br><\\/p><p>\\\"This guide is concerned with some fundamental ideas of analysis of data from\\r\\nsurveys. The discussion is at a statistically simple level; other more sophisticated\\r\\nstatistical approaches are outlined in our guide Modern Methods of Analysis. Our aim\\r\\nhere is to clarify the ideas that successful data analysts usually need to consider to\\r\\ncomplete a survey analysis task purposefully.\\\"<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a contract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff working on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for staff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help researchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/51832d70ad10a7c1d2705a09425d7be8.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-survey-data_2019-08-20_16:07:50\\\\/2019-08-20_16:07:50_approaches-to-the-analysis-of-survey-data.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-20_16:07:50_approaches-to-the-analysis-of-survey-data.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Approaches_to_the_analysis_of_survey_data.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":275001,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2001-03-01','2019-08-20 16:07:51','2019-08-21 11:29:10',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-survey-data_2019-08-20_16:07:50/statistical-guides-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-survey-data_2019-08-20_16:07:50.zip',1),(400,'{\"en\":\"Data Management Support Pack\"}','data-management-support-pack_2019-08-20_16:13:57',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>The CCAFS-CIAT&nbsp;Data Management Support Pack is a collection of resources, including template documents and video guides, on data management. It contains useful information for researchers, principal investigators and data managers.<br><\\/p><p>It is \\\"designed to help\\r\\n you produce high quality, reusable and open data from your research \\r\\nactivities. It consists of documents, templates and videos covering the \\r\\ndifferent aspects of data management and ranging from the overarching \\r\\nconcepts and strategies through to the day-to-day activities.\\\"<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/ccafs.cgiar.org\\/publications\\/data-management-strategy\\\"><\\/a><\\/p>\"}',7,21,'cover_images/troves/b3493192d37038880ec069a442569936.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://ccafs.cgiar.org/data-management-support-pack\"}]}',NULL,'2016-08-01','2019-08-20 16:13:58','2019-08-21 11:27:17',NULL,NULL,'files/data-management-support-pack_2019-08-20_16:13:57/data-management-support-pack_2019-08-20_16:13:57.zip',1),(401,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Concepts Underlying the Design of Experiments\"}','statistical-guides-concepts-underlying-the-design-of-experiments_2019-08-21_09:25:34',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on the key concepts of experimental design. <br><\\/p>\\\"This guide describes the main concepts that are involved in designing an experiment.\\r\\nIts direct use is to assist scientists involved in the design of on-station field trials, but\\r\\nmany of the concepts also apply to the design of other research exercises. These range\\r\\nfrom simulation exercises, and laboratory studies, to on-farm experiments,\\r\\nparticipatory studies and surveys.\\\"<p>\\r\\n<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/ae3b066e8a8e6d818d67cc837f8eedc9.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-concepts-underlying-the-design-of-experiments_2019-08-21_09:25:34\\\\/2019-08-21_09:25:34_concepts-underlying-design-of-experiments.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_09:25:34_concepts-underlying-design-of-experiments.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Concepts_Underlying_Design_Of_Experiments.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":184382,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-03-01','2019-08-21 09:25:34','2019-08-21 11:28:17',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-concepts-underlying-the-design-of-experiments_2019-08-21_09:25:34/statistical-guides-concepts-underlying-the-design-of-experiments_2019-08-21_09:25:34.zip',1),(402,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Data Management Guidelines for Experimental Projects\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos para el manejo de datos de proyectos experimentales\"}','statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on managing data for research projects. Planning the data management aspects of a project from the outset helps avoid problems later on.<\\/p><p> \\\"Research projects often involve the collection of a large volume of data. The data\\r\\nhave then to be processed and analysed, with results and summaries being prepared for\\r\\npublication in some form. For this sequence to proceed smoothly, the project requires\\r\\na well-defined system of data management. This booklet gives some guidelines on the\\r\\ncomponents of such a system.\\\"\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"es\":\"<p>Un folleto que proporciona orientaci\\u00f3n sobre la gesti\\u00f3n de datos para proyectos de investigaci\\u00f3n. Planificar los aspectos de gesti\\u00f3n de datos de un proyecto desde el principio ayuda a evitar problemas m\\u00e1s adelante.<\\/p><p>\\\"Los proyectos de investigacio\\u0301n frecuentemente comprenden la recoleccio\\u0301n de grandes volu\\u0301menes de datos. E\\u0301stos tienen que ser luego procesados y analizados y los resultados y si\\u0301ntesis deben ser preparados para su publicacio\\u0301n en algu\\u0301n formato. Para que e\\u0301sta secuencia ocurra de manera a\\u0301gil, el proyecto requiere un sistema de manejo de datos bien definido. La presente publicacio\\u0301n ofrece algunas gui\\u0301as sobre los componentes de tal sistema.\\\"<br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>El SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}',7,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30\\\\/2019-08-21_09:36:30_data-management-guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_09:36:30_data-management-guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Data_Management_Guidelines.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":45008,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\", \"es\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30\\\\/2019-10-10_15:32:19_guia3.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:32:19_guia3.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia3.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":194897,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"es\": null}',NULL,'1998-03-01','2019-08-21 09:36:31','2019-10-10 15:32:19',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30/statistical-guides-data-management-guidelines-for-experimental-projects_2019-08-21_09:36:30.zip',1),(403,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Good Practice Case Studies\"}','statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><\\/p><p><\\/p><p>A collection of case studies giving examples of good statistical practice in various aspects of research and experiment design.<\\/p><p>The topics covered are:<\\/p><ol><li>Good practice in well-linked studies using several methodologies<\\/li><li>Good Practice in Survey Design and Analysis<\\/li><li>Good practice in on-farm studies<\\/li><li>Good practice in researcher and farmer experimentation<\\/li><li>Determining the effectiveness of a proposed sample sizes<\\/li><li>Good practice in the preparation of research protocols<\\/li><li>Developing a sampling strategy for a nation-wide survey in Malawi<\\/li><\\/ol><p><\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/3a876634bbf5664a1ecdd14d92ec1063.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs1-well-linked-studies-using-several-methodologies.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs1-well-linked-studies-using-several-methodologies.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS1 - Well-linked studies using several methodologies.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":18078,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs2-survey-design-and-analysis.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs2-survey-design-and-analysis.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS2 - Survey Design and Analysis.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":25990,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs3-on-farm-studies.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs3-on-farm-studies.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS3 - On-farm Studies.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":24641,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs4-researcher-and-farmer-experimentation.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:26_gpcs4-researcher-and-farmer-experimentation.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS4 - Researcher and Farmer Experimentation.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":29330,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs5-effectiveness-of-proposed-sample-sizes.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs5-effectiveness-of-proposed-sample-sizes.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS5 - Effectiveness of Proposed Sample Sizes.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":30258,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs6-data-management.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs6-data-management.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS6 - Data Management.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":187570,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs7-preparation-of-research-protocols.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs7-preparation-of-research-protocols.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS7 - Preparation of Research Protocols.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":184279,\\\"type_id\\\":1},{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26\\\\/2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs8-developing-a-sampling-strategy-for-a-nation-wide-survey-in-malawi.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:02:27_gpcs8-developing-a-sampling-strategy-for-a-nation-wide-survey-in-malawi.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"GPCS8 - Developing a Sampling Strategy for a Nation-wide Survey in Malawi.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":37395,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,NULL,'2019-08-21 10:02:27','2019-08-21 10:58:48',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26/statistical-guides-good-practice-case-studies_2019-08-21_10:02:26.zip',0),(404,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Guidelines for Planning Effective Surveys\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos para planear encuestas efectivas\"}','statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A booklet on planning surveys for research. The guide covers planning, when a survey is appropriate to use, setting up a survey, designing questionnaires, sampling principles, quality assurance and survey data analysis.<br><\\/p><p>\\\"This booklet provides guidelines about surveys which may be contemplated as part of\\r\\nthe programme of project work. It is intended to provide guidance for those involved\\r\\nin natural resources research or bilateral projects, and to help those who review project\\r\\nactivities. They should be able to recognise where a survey may be needed to realise\\r\\nstated objectives of the project and to check that a survey is realistically formulated\\\"\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\",\"es\":\"<p>Un folleto sobre la planificaci\\u00f3n de encuestas para la investigaci\\u00f3n. La gu\\u00eda cubre la planificaci\\u00f3n, cuando una encuesta es apropiada para usar, establecer una encuesta, dise\\u00f1ar cuestionarios, principios de muestreo, garant\\u00eda de calidad y an\\u00e1lisis de datos de encuestas.<br><\\/p><p>\\\"Esta publicacio\\u0301n ofrece gui\\u0301as acerca del disen\\u0303o de encuestas que pueden ser contempladas como parte del programa de trabajo de un proyecto. La misma pretende ser u\\u0301til a quienes este\\u0301n involucrados en investigacio\\u0301n en recursos naturales o proyectos bilaterales y puede ayudar a quienes supervisan actividades de los proyectos. Los unos y los otros deben estar en capacidad de reconocer cuando una encuesta puede ser necesaria para alcanzar los objetivos establecidos en el proyecto y de evaluar que la encuesta sea formulada de manera realista.\\\"<br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>El SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC.<\\/p>\"}',7,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28\\\\/2019-08-21_10:14:28_guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:14:28_guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guidelines_for_Planning_Effective_Surveys.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":188768,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\", \"es\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28\\\\/2019-10-10_15:41:33_guia5.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:41:33_guia5.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia5.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":126787,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-03-01','2019-08-21 10:14:29','2019-10-30 07:47:08',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28/statistical-guides-guidelines-for-planning-effective-surveys_2019-08-21_10:14:28.zip',1),(405,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Confidence and Significance - Key Concepts of Inferential Statistics\"}','statistical-guides-confidence-and-significance-key-concepts-of-inferential-statistics_2019-08-21_10:33:33',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving an overview of inferential statistics. This includes concepts such as estimation, hypothesis testing, standard errors, confidence intervals, significance and analysis of variance. The guide aims to provide an easy-to-understand introduction to these topics, which are often poorly understood among non-statisticians in research.<br><\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/6117935bf56a702395b3543b3abc2ff9.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-confidence-and-significance-key-concepts-of-inferential-statistics_2019-08-21_10:33:33\\\\/2019-08-21_10:33:33_inferential-statistics.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:33:33_inferential-statistics.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Inferential_Statistics.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":292799,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2001-02-01','2019-08-21 10:33:34','2019-08-21 10:33:36',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-confidence-and-significance-key-concepts-of-inferential-statistics_2019-08-21_10:33:33/statistical-guides-confidence-and-significance-key-concepts-of-inferential-statistics_2019-08-21_10:33:33.zip',0),(406,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Mixed Models and Multilevel Data Structures in Agriculture\"}','statistical-guides-mixed-models-and-multilevel-data-structures-in-agriculture_2019-08-21_10:51:07',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet aiming to help the reader understand what heirarchical data structures are and how they may be analysed. It presents several examples to help demonstrate these concepts.<br><\\/p><p>From the introduction:<br><\\/p><p>\\\"Hierarchical or multilevel data structures can occur in many areas of agricultural\\r\\nresearch \\u2013 for instance in on-farm trials, where there can be information at the village,\\r\\nfarm and plot or animal level. Experiments in animal breeding are often concerned\\r\\nwith attributing variation in traits of offspring, such as their growth, to the sires and\\r\\ndams from which they were bred. Researchers in this discipline are therefore familiar\\r\\nwith the idea that livestock data often have some hierarchical structure with different\\r\\nlevels of variation.\\r\\n<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 5\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>Analysis of variance \\u2013 except in balanced or nested designs \\u2013 has been difficult to\\r\\napply to data with a multilevel structure. Mixed modelling is becoming a standard\\r\\napproach for analysing these types of data, particularly since it can deal with\\r\\ncomplicated or \\\"messy\\\" structures. The mixed model facilities are now available in\\r\\nsome of the more powerful statistical packages such as Genstat and SAS.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>There seems to be some \\\"mystique\\\" surrounding these methods, and our claim is that\\r\\nthere should not be. The purpose of this guide is to review the general concepts of\\r\\nmixed models. We illustrate by example how to recognise the structure in the data\\r\\nand how to fit and interpret a mixed model analysis. The reader is expected to be\\r\\nfamiliar with simple analysis of variance methods.\\\"\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>This guide was produced in collaboration with the International Livestock Research Institute (ILRI)\\r\\n<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 4\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/8eaac3880ad172c207d055135d73a92c.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-mixed-models-and-multilevel-data-structures-in-agriculture_2019-08-21_10:51:07\\\\/2019-08-21_10:51:07_mixed-models-and-multilevel-data-structures.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_10:51:07_mixed-models-and-multilevel-data-structures.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Mixed_Models_And_Multilevel_Data_Structures.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":392189,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2001-03-01','2019-08-21 10:51:08','2019-08-21 11:17:14',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-mixed-models-and-multilevel-data-structures-in-agriculture_2019-08-21_10:51:07/statistical-guides-mixed-models-and-multilevel-data-structures-in-agriculture_2019-08-21_10:51:07.zip',1),(407,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Modern Approaches to the Analysis of Experimental Data\"}','statistical-guides-modern-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-experimental-data_2019-08-21_10:59:04',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on analysis of data. It discusses the three main parts of the process: relating the analysis to the stated objectives of the study, exploratory and descriptive analysis, and ANOVA and formal inference methods.<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\\"This guide offers advice to researchers on a reliable approach to the analysis of on-\\r\\nstation and on-farm trials. The analysis should satisfy the objectives of the experiment\\r\\nand ensure that the researcher gets as much as possible out of the data collected. This\\r\\napproach is described in Part A of this guide. Part B summarises some common\\r\\ncomplications that often arise in the analysis of experimental data.\\\"\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p><\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/ae235ee472d52cfaec348c338f9e2104.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-modern-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-experimental-data_2019-08-21_10:59:04\\\\/2019-08-21_11:01:36_modern-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-experimental-data.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_11:01:36_modern-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-experimental-data.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Modern_Approaches_To_the_Analysis_of_Experimental_Data.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":218921,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2001-01-01','2019-08-21 10:59:04','2019-08-21 11:01:39',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-modern-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-experimental-data_2019-08-21_10:59:04/statistical-guides-modern-approaches-to-the-analysis-of-experimental-data_2019-08-21_10:59:04.zip',0),(408,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Modern Methods of Analysis\"}','statistical-guides-modern-methods-of-analysis_2019-08-21_11:13:56',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet which follows on from the guides \'<span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\">Approaches to the Analysis of Survey Data<\\/span>\' and \'<span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\">Modern Approaches to the Analysis of Experimental Data<\\/span>\', and presents some more modern approaches. These are more technically advanced and require the use of statistical software. They are presented in the guide with the aim of permitting users to assess whether any of these methods would be of value for their analysis.<\\/p><p>The topics covered&nbsp; include: exploratory methods, multivariate methods, generalised linear models, and multilevel models. <br><\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/b5b3ad3e02f61d0fcd0cd57ac849c314.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-modern-methods-of-analysis_2019-08-21_11:13:56\\\\/2019-08-21_11:13:56_modern-methods-of-analysis.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_11:13:56_modern-methods-of-analysis.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Modern_Methods_Of-Analysis.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":382054,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2002-07-01','2019-08-21 11:13:56','2019-08-21 11:13:58',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-modern-methods-of-analysis_2019-08-21_11:13:56/statistical-guides-modern-methods-of-analysis_2019-08-21_11:13:56.zip',0),(409,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Moving on from MSTAT\"}','statistical-guides-moving-on-from-mstat_2019-08-21_15:45:38',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>From the introduction:<\\/p><p>\\\"This guide has been written as part of our work for DFID to encourage good statistical\\r\\npractice. It is to assist research teams in planning their computing strategy.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>MSTAT has been effective in many developing countries, in introducing statistical\\r\\ncomputing to staff who have had no previous experience. It remains a useful package\\r\\nfor the design of trials and for some of its specialist facilities, in particular for\\r\\nbreeding programs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>However, MSTAT is limited in its facilities for the analysis of experimental data and\\r\\nrelatively cumbersome to use for the Analysis of Variance, compared to the ease of\\r\\nuse of modern statistical software under Windows. A recent development is that at\\r\\nleast one modern statistics package can read MSTAT files directly. This increases the\\r\\nflexibility of analyses both for staff who have historical data in MSTAT files and for\\r\\nthose who would like to combine their use of MSTAT with the transfer to more\\r\\npowerful software when the need arises.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>This guide illustrates some advantages in using a more powerful package than\\r\\nMSTAT for the design and analysis of experimental data. We use Genstat for this\\r\\npurpose for two reasons. Firstly, Genstat is an excellent package for the analysis of\\r\\ndata from agricultural experiments and secondly Genstat has provided the facility for\\r\\nthe transfer of MSTAT files. We believe that it is now much easier to learn a new\\r\\nWindows package, compared to a few years ago and that full exploitation of\\r\\nexperimental data needs access to a modern statistical package, such as Genstat\\\"\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/b8e5166c0533b41f7f4b4ae7a1eeced9.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-moving-on-from-mstat_2019-08-21_15:45:38\\\\/2019-08-21_15:45:38_moving-on-from-mstat.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_15:45:38_moving-on-from-mstat.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Moving_On_From_MSTAT.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":640889,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-03-01','2019-08-21 15:45:39','2019-08-21 15:45:40',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-moving-on-from-mstat_2019-08-21_15:45:38/statistical-guides-moving-on-from-mstat_2019-08-21_15:45:38.zip',0),(410,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: On-Farm Trials \\u2013 Some Biometric Guidelines\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos para experimentaci\\u00f3n en fincas de productores\"}','statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet giving guidance on how to design and conduct an on-farm experiment with the participation of farmers. Includes information about setting objectives, selecting farms to involve, choosing treatments and units, measurements and analysis of results. <br><\\/p><p>From the introduction:<\\/p><p>\\\"Farmer-participatory research trials have rapidly gained popularity in the past few\\r\\nyears with due consideration being given to the knowledge, problems and priorities of\\r\\nfarming families. The move towards participatory on-farm research means that many\\r\\nresearchers, such as breeders and agronomists, who have been trained in techniques of\\r\\non-station research, are now under pressure to move on-farm. It is therefore perhaps\\r\\nnot surprising that the design of such trials has, too often, resulted in miniaturised\\r\\nresearch institute experiments. Conditions for on-farm trials are typically less\\r\\ncontrolled than those for research institute fields, and this means that more thoughtful\\r\\ndesigns are needed.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\"><p>This booklet concentrates primarily on providing guidelines on aspects of the design\\r\\nand analysis of on-farm trials that are different from on-station research. It is\\r\\nconcerned primarily with experiments where the farmer has considerable involvement\\r\\n\\u2013 and not situations where the farmer\\u2019s only participation is by providing land.\\r\\nEqually, it does not include experiments that are really just demonstrations. You\\r\\nshould therefore ask yourself whether your experiment (a) involves the farmer in\\r\\ndesign, management or assessment, (b) seeks to address unanswered questions and (c)\\r\\nis an experiment, i.e. it involves planned changes.\\\"<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\",\"es\":\"<p>Un folleto que brinda orientaci\\u00f3n sobre c\\u00f3mo dise\\u00f1ar y realizar un experimento en la granja con la participaci\\u00f3n de los agricultores. Incluye informaci\\u00f3n sobre el establecimiento de objetivos, la selecci\\u00f3n de fincas para involucrar, la elecci\\u00f3n de tratamientos y unidades, mediciones y an\\u00e1lisis de resultados.<br><\\/p><p>\\\"Los trabajos de investigacio\\u0301n con participacio\\u0301n de los agricultores han ganado popularidad ra\\u0301pidamente en los an\\u0303os recientes, debido a la importancia que esta\\u0301 recibiendo el conocimiento, los problemas y prioridades del agricultor y su familia. Esta tendencia hacia la investigacio\\u0301n en finca significa que muchos investigadores, tales como mejoradores, zootecnistas o agro\\u0301nomos, quienes han sido entrenados en te\\u0301cnicas de investigacio\\u0301n tradicional en estaciones experimentales, esta\\u0301n ahora bajo la presio\\u0301n de trasladarse a la investigacio\\u0301n en la finca del agricultor. Es por esto que quiza\\u0301s no sorprenda que el disen\\u0303o de tales investigaciones ha resultado, muy a menudo, en experimentos de estacio\\u0301n experimental miniaturizados. Las condiciones de los experimentos en fincas de agricultores son ti\\u0301picamente menos controladas que en los campos de institutos de investigacio\\u0301n, y eso significa que se requieren disen\\u0303os mucho ma\\u0301s meditados.<br>Esta publicacio\\u0301n se concentra fundamentalmente en brindar gui\\u0301as sobre aspectos del disen\\u0303o y ana\\u0301lisis de experimentos en campos de productores que son diferentes de la investigacio\\u0301n en estaciones experimentales. Trata ba\\u0301sicamente con experimentos donde el agricultor esta\\u0301 involucrado de una manera importante - y no en situaciones donde la participacio\\u0301n del agricultor se limita solamente a facilitar sus campos. De igual manera, no incluye experimentos que son realmente solo demostrativos. Usted debe preguntarse si su experimento (a) involucra al agricultor en el disen\\u0303o, manejo y evaluacio\\u0301n, (b) busca responder a preguntas que no han sido contestadas y (c) es realmente un experimento, es decir, implica cambios planificados.\\\"<br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\nEl SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC\"}',7,13,NULL,0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18\\\\/2019-08-21_15:52:18_onfarmtrials.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-08-21_15:52:18_onfarmtrials.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"OnFarmTrials.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":232699,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\", \"es\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18\\\\/2019-10-10_15:39:22_guia4.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:39:22_guia4.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia4.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":118809,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"es\": null}',NULL,'1998-03-01','2019-08-21 15:52:19','2019-10-10 15:39:22',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18/statistical-guides-on-farm-trials-some-biometric-guidelines_2019-08-21_15:52:18.zip',0),(411,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: One Animal Per Farm? A guide to resolving the statistical difficulties encountered by on-farm researchers working with small livestock numbers in the developing world\"}','statistical-guides-one-animal-per-farm-a-guide-to-resolving-the-statistical-difficulties-encountered-by-on-farm-researchers-working-with-small-livestock-numbers-in-the-developing-world_2019-09-02_15:30:50',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A short booklet addressing the specific difficulties encountered in agricultural experimentation when conducting on-farm studies where there&nbsp; may only be one animal per farm. These difficulties arise from the need to replicate experimental treatments and therefore conduct studies across multiple farms, which results in a large amount of variation between the animals in the experiment. The booklet provides advice and guidance on designing experiments in this situation.<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/7a5546f77097cb4f8d91a29cba8673b4.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-one-animal-per-farm-a-guide-to-resolving-the-statistical-difficulties-encountered-by-on-farm-researchers-working-with-small-livestock-numbers-in-the-developing-world_2019-09-02_15:30:50\\\\/2019-09-02_15:30:50_oneanimalperfarm.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-02_15:30:50_oneanimalperfarm.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"OneAnimalPerFarm.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":225430,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-03-01','2019-09-02 15:30:50','2019-09-02 15:30:59',NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(412,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Informative Presentation of Tables, Graphs and Statistics\"}','statistical-guides-informative-presentation-of-tables-graphs-and-statistics_2019-09-02_15:37:56',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>From the introduction:<\\/p><p>\\\"In this guide we concern ourselves with the effective transmission of numerical\\r\\ninformation in project reports and serious publications, such as scientific papers which\\r\\nmight be prepared by DFID-funded researchers. For presentation of general statistical\\r\\ninformation, we recommend an authoritative source of guidance: \\\"Plain Figures\\\"\\r\\n(1996, 2nd edition) by Myra Chapman and Cathy Wykes, published by H.M.\\r\\nStationery Office, a 148 page book with many full-colour illustrations. \\\"Plain\\r\\nFigures\\\" is particularly intended for those addressing non-specialist audiences; this\\r\\nguide sets out to reinforce and complement it, focusing on points most relevant to\\r\\nthose presenting structured research results to an informed audience. We give\\r\\nguidelines for layout of graphs, charts and tables, then for the presentation of results of\\r\\nstatistical analyses.\\\"<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\"><div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\"><div class=\\\"column\\\"><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/3e87b69fd414d989f7d1709adf4c6bd7.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"{\\\"1\\\":{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-informative-presentation-of-tables-graphs-and-statistics_2019-09-02_15:37:56\\\\/2019-09-05_16:28:03_informativepresentationoftablesgraphsandstatistics-mar2000.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-05_16:28:03_informativepresentationoftablesgraphsandstatistics-mar2000.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"InformativePresentationOfTablesGraphsAndStatistics-Mar2000.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":357559,\\\"type_id\\\":1}}\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-03-01','2019-09-02 15:37:57','2019-09-05 16:29:31',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-informative-presentation-of-tables-graphs-and-statistics_2019-09-02_15:37:56/statistical-guides-informative-presentation-of-tables-graphs-and-statistics_2019-09-02_15:37:56.zip',1),(413,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: The Role of a Database Package for Research Projects\"}','statistical-guides-the-role-of-a-database-package-for-research-projects_2019-09-02_16:00:35',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A booklet providing guidance on the strengths and weaknesses of spreadsheet and database software as tools for use in research projects. It aims to help the reader understand whether they require the use of database software to manage their project data. <br><\\/p><p>From the introduction:<br><\\/p><p>\\\"This guide is to help researchers and research managers to decide whether they need to\\r\\nmake use of a database package to manage their data. We use Microsoft Access as an\\r\\nexample, but the concepts are general and apply equally to any relational database\\r\\npackage.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>There are many textbooks on Access, but they concentrate primarily on HOW to use\\r\\nthe software. This guide concentrates on WHETHER the software is needed and if so,\\r\\nwhat skills do different members of the project team need.\\\"\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/cfbb7077ccb80a852864f7be7b6738a1.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-the-role-of-a-database-package-for-research-projects_2019-09-02_16:00:35\\\\/2019-09-02_16:00:35_roleofdatabasepackageforresearchprojects.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-02_16:00:35_roleofdatabasepackageforresearchprojects.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"RoleOfDatabasePackageForResearchProjects.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":483493,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-11-01','2019-09-02 16:00:36','2019-09-02 16:00:37',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-the-role-of-a-database-package-for-research-projects_2019-09-02_16:00:35/statistical-guides-the-role-of-a-database-package-for-research-projects_2019-09-02_16:00:35.zip',0),(414,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Some Basic Ideas of Sampling\"}','statistical-guides-some-basic-ideas-of-sampling_2019-09-02_16:21:01',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>From the introduction:<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 4\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\\"This booklet is about ideas needed to devise an intelligent sampling plan, and is not a\\r\\ncookbook. We are concerned with basic, widely useful concepts. Our aim is to\\r\\npresent general principles for achieving good, defensible sampling practice, by the\\r\\nsystematic application of common sense rather than mathematics. When committing\\r\\nresources, sampling is often a crucial stage. If possible, checking with an\\r\\nunderstanding statistician may improve efficiency and effectiveness at this point; the\\r\\nbooklet defines some of what a statistician would like you to think about before\\r\\ndiscussing your work setting in more detail.\\\"<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/1bfa701de6b5ba801fc7b05a064667de.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-some-basic-ideas-of-sampling_2019-09-02_16:21:01\\\\/2019-09-02_16:21:01_some-basic-ideas-of-sampling.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-02_16:21:01_some-basic-ideas-of-sampling.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Some_Basic_Ideas_Of_Sampling.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":333418,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-11-01','2019-09-02 16:21:02','2019-09-02 16:21:03',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-some-basic-ideas-of-sampling_2019-09-02_16:21:01/statistical-guides-some-basic-ideas-of-sampling_2019-09-02_16:21:01.zip',0),(415,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Disciplined Use of Spreadsheet Packages for Data Entry (2nd Edition: Revised for Excel 2007)\"}','statistical-guides-disciplined-use-of-spreadsheet-packages-for-data-entry-2nd-edition-revised-for-excel-2007_2019-09-02_16:26:10',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This booklet gives guidance on best practice for using Excel in an appropriate way in order to facilitate effective data entry.<\\/p><p>From the introduction:<\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\\"In our guide called \\u201cData Management Guidelines for Experimental Projects\\u201d,1 we\\r\\nnoted that spreadsheets are commonly used for data entry because they are familiar, in\\r\\nwidespread use and very flexible. However, we also stated, as a warning:\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>Their very flexibility means they can result in poor data entry and management. They\\r\\nshould thus be used with great care. Users should apply the same rigour and\\r\\ndiscipline that is obligatory with more structured data entry software.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>This guide is to explain what we mean by \\u201cgreat care\\u201d and \\u201crigour and discipline\\u201d and\\r\\nhence to show how a spreadsheet package can be used effectively for data entry. In\\r\\nthe illustrations we have used Excel 2007 as an example of a spreadsheet package, but\\r\\nour strategy applies equally to other spreadsheets.\\\"<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/d7dc268378b13bcb1b30f8c112b225ac.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-disciplined-use-of-spreadsheet-packages-for-data-entry-2nd-edition-revised-for-excel-2007_2019-09-02_16:26:10\\\\/2019-09-02_16:26:10_spreadsheets-for-data-entry-excel-2007.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-02_16:26:10_spreadsheets-for-data-entry-excel-2007.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Spreadsheets_for_Data_Entry (Excel 2007).pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":1022506,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2009-02-01','2019-09-02 16:26:11','2019-09-02 16:26:11',NULL,NULL,NULL,0),(416,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: The Statistical Background to ANOVA\"}','statistical-guides-the-statistical-background-to-anova_2019-09-02_16:38:48',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 2\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>From the introduction:<br><\\/p><p>\\\"This material was first produced as the statistical background to accompany a set of\\r\\ncomputer programs (collectively called GENANOVA) for the analysis of\\r\\nexperimental data. We have reproduced the guide because it provides a very clear\\r\\nexplanation of many important concepts concerned with the design and analysis of\\r\\nexperiments. These concepts are described in a way that should be clear to non-\\r\\nstatisticians and are equally relevant, whatever software is used for the analysis.\\\"<\\/p><p>\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>This guide was originally written by Professor S C Pearce, and has been adapted for inclusion in these guides by the University of Reading Statistical Services Centre.<\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/b9203575388dc5e737941810634e6e88.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-the-statistical-background-to-anova_2019-09-02_16:38:48\\\\/2019-09-02_16:38:48_statistical-background-to-anova.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-02_16:38:48_statistical-background-to-anova.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Statistical_Background_To-ANOVA.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":403632,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,NULL,'2019-09-02 16:38:49','2019-09-02 16:38:49',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-the-statistical-background-to-anova_2019-09-02_16:38:48/statistical-guides-the-statistical-background-to-anova_2019-09-02_16:38:48.zip',0),(417,'{\"en\":\"What is Mixed Methods Research?\"}','what-is-mixed-methods-research_2019-09-03_09:56:30',NULL,'{\"en\":\"A short video by John Creswell of the University of Nebraska-Lincoln discussing principles of mixed methods research. Easy to follow, a good introduction about how do integrate methods in research.\"}',5,16,'cover_images/troves/9b0ffd5492f6a39bb70bf2ff0e3d247a.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2013-04-01','2019-09-03 09:56:30','2019-12-03 19:04:42',NULL,'1OaNiTlpyX8',NULL,1),(418,'{\"en\":\"Principles of FRN\"}','principles-of-frn_2019-09-03_10:29:42',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>Working principles for Farmer Research Networks from CCRP. This is a version that is still in circulation in 2019, but is likely to evolve.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>(<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/pixnio.com\\/es\\/\\\">im\\u00e1genes gratis<\\/a>)\"}',5,13,'cover_images/troves/44103b7d3311b162fa46c5551d582baf.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/principles-of-frn_2019-09-03_10:29:42\\\\/2019-09-03_10:29:42_frn-principles-updated-2017.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-03_10:29:42_frn-principles-updated-2017.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"FRN_principles_updated 2017.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":342083,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2017-01-01','2019-09-03 10:29:42','2019-09-03 12:23:24',NULL,NULL,'files/principles-of-frn_2019-09-03_10:29:42/principles-of-frn_2019-09-03_10:29:42.zip',1),(419,'{\"en\":\"Principios de la RAI\"}','principios-de-la-rai_2019-09-03_10:34:56',NULL,'{\"en\":\"Esta es la version en Espa\\u00f1ol del documento Principles of FRNs. Estos principios son un documento de inicial que compila los principios discutidos for CCRP para su iniciativa de Redes de Agricultores Investigadores. Es seguro que el documento va a evolucionar y nuevas versiones deberian estar disponibles en el futuro.<br><br><br>(<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/pixnio.com\\/es\\/\\\">im\\u00e1genes gratis<\\/a>)\"}',5,13,'cover_images/troves/4776419e4427bcba1b263651b61de1eb.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/principios-de-la-rai_2019-09-03_10:34:56\\\\/2019-09-03_10:34:56_principios-de-las-redes-de-agricultores-investigadores.docx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-09-03_10:34:56_principios-de-las-redes-de-agricultores-investigadores.docx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Principios de las Redes de Agricultores Investigadores.docx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"docx\\\",\\\"size\\\":14670,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2017-09-01','2019-09-03 10:34:56','2019-09-03 12:22:49',NULL,NULL,'files/principios-de-la-rai_2019-09-03_10:34:56/principios-de-la-rai_2019-09-03_10:34:56.zip',1),(420,'{\"en\":\"Sesi\\u00f3n 4: \\u00bfC\\u00f3mo lograr la integraci\\u00f3n de m\\u00e9todos cualitativos y cuantitativos?\"}','sesion-4-como-lograr-la-integracion-de-metodos-cualitativos-y-cuantitativos_2019-09-04_13:51:15',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span lang=\\\"es-419\\\" style=\\\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif;\\r\\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\r\\ncolor:#656565;mso-ansi-language:#580A;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\\\">En esta\\r\\nsesi\\u00f3n exploraremos un video y 2 art\\u00edculos que discuten o ejemplifican c\\u00f3mo el\\r\\nuso de m\\u00e9todos cualitativos y cuantitativos contribuyen a un proceso de\\r\\ninvestigaci\\u00f3n y c\\u00f3mo sucede su integraci\\u00f3n. N\\u00f3tese que hablamos de m\\u00e9todos y no\\r\\nde datos cuantitativos o cualitativos. Datos de ambos tipos son generados en\\r\\ncualquier proceso de investigaci\\u00f3n independientemente del m\\u00e9todo usado. Esto es\\r\\nporque nuestra percepci\\u00f3n y estudio de la realidad requiere el uso de datos (e\\r\\ninformaci\\u00f3n) que es de los dos tipos. Habiendo dicho esto, el tipo de m\\u00e9todo,\\r\\ncualitativo o cuantitativo, es mas probable que genere datos que pertenecen a\\r\\nese tipo, y por lo tanto c\\u00f3mo tratamos esos datos esta muy asociado con el tipo\\r\\nde m\\u00e9todo.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span lang=\\\"es-419\\\" style=\\\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif;\\r\\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\r\\ncolor:#656565;mso-ansi-language:#580A;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\\\">La diferencia\\r\\nentre los m\\u00e9todos esta asociada a la disciplina o filosof\\u00eda en donde se\\r\\noriginaron. Las reglas que se consideran adecuadas y la raz\\u00f3n para su uso,\\r\\ndeben ser bien entendidas cuando se hace su selecci\\u00f3n.<o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span lang=\\\"es-419\\\" style=\\\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif;\\r\\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\r\\ncolor:#656565;mso-ansi-language:#580A;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\\\">Finalmente,\\r\\nprocesos de investigaci\\u00f3n complejos siempre requieren el uso y combinaci\\u00f3n de\\r\\nm\\u00e9todos. El dise\\u00f1o de investigaciones complejas requiere la selecci\\u00f3n y\\r\\ndecisi\\u00f3n de c\\u00f3mo los m\\u00e9todos se complementan para lograr obtener informaci\\u00f3n\\r\\nque satisfacen los objetivos de la investigaci\\u00f3n.<\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span lang=\\\"es-419\\\" style=\\\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif;\\r\\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\r\\ncolor:#656565;mso-ansi-language:#580A;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\\\"><o:p><br><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p class=\\\"MsoNormal\\\" style=\\\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span lang=\\\"es-419\\\" style=\\\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif;\\r\\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\\r\\ncolor:#656565;mso-ansi-language:#580A;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB\\\"><o:p><br><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-top: 0cm; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\\\"><span lang=\\\"es-419\\\" style=\\\"font-size:\\r\\n10.5pt;font-family:&quot;Century Gothic&quot;,sans-serif;color:#656565;mso-ansi-language:\\r\\n#580A\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">El webinario <\\/span><o:p><\\/o:p><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\\\"margin-top: 0cm; background-image: initial; backgr