d how to access it.<\\/p><p>It can be used to provide individuals and groups within CCRP a quick overview of who we are and how they can work with RMS. <\\/p><p>The PDF version of this document is also <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/stats4sd.org\\/resources\\/436\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">available on the resources site<\\/a>, shared publicly so grantees can access it. This version is provided for Stats4SD staff to edit and share as required.<br><\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/2763ed8df8865f2cb04f1e552f8f6a53.jpg',0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/about-the-research-methods-support-project-editable-word-document-version_2019-10-03_13:20:06\\\\/2019-10-03_13:20:06_about-the-research-methods-support-project.docx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-03_13:20:06_about-the-research-methods-support-project.docx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"About the Research Methods Support Project.docx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"docx\\\",\\\"size\\\":34248,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2019-10-01','2019-10-03 13:20:06','2019-10-03 13:20:08',NULL,NULL,'files/about-the-research-methods-support-project-editable-word-document-version_2019-10-03_13:20:06/about-the-research-methods-support-project-editable-word-document-version_2019-10-03_13:20:06.zip',0),(438,'{\"en\":\"Notas de campo: la gu\\u00eda r\\u00e1pida\"}','notas-de-campo-la-guia-rapida_2019-10-08_11:45:22',NULL,'{\"en\":\"Una gu\\u00eda r\\u00e1pida sobre c\\u00f3mo tomar mejores notas de campo.&nbsp;\"}',8,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"{\\\"1\\\":{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/notas-de-campo-la-guia-rapida_2019-10-08_11:45:22\\\\/2019-10-10_16:20:05_notas-de-campo.docx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_16:20:05_notas-de-campo.docx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Notas de campo.docx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"docx\\\",\\\"size\\\":33707,\\\"type_id\\\":1}}\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2019-10-01','2019-10-08 11:45:22','2019-10-10 16:20:51',NULL,NULL,'files/notas-de-campo-la-guia-rapida_2019-10-08_11:45:22/notas-de-campo-la-guia-rapida_2019-10-08_11:45:22.zip',1),(439,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Statistical Guidelines for Natural Resources Projects\",\"es\":\"Lineamientos Estad\\u00edsticos para Proyectos de Recursos Naturales\"}','statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This is the first in the series of guides aimed at supporting staff involved in research projects to identify their biometric or statistical needs. This is an introductory guide, and provides a more general overview of the areas of a research project where an understanding of statistical ideas is important.<br><\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">From the introduction:<\\/span><\\/p><p>\\\"Without sufficient confidence in statistics, researchers plan designs that are often conservative, primarily to ensure a simple analysis. While this is sometimes appropriate, simple improvements can often result in more informative experiments, or surveys, for the same cost. Measurements may be made that are inappropriate for the objectives of the study, and are subsequently not analysed. Data entry can become a very time-consuming part of the study if it is not planned in advance. The analysis may be rushed, using inappropriate software, because of the pressure to produce results quickly. The study is then concluded, with the realisation that there is much more that can still be learned from the data. However, funding is at an end, and problems in the data management have made it difficult to allow easy access to the data, even for future researchers within the country where the study was made.<br>In this guide we consider these stages, from planning to presentation, in turn. Its aim is to encourage the researcher to think about the crucial aspects of planning, analysing and interpreting data.\\\"<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Part of a series of statistical guides by The University of Reading\\r\\nStatistical Services Centre, which were originally written as part of a \\r\\ncontract with DFID to give guidance to research and support staff \\r\\nworking on DFID Natural Resources projects. They provide guidelines for \\r\\nstaff involved in the development and\\r\\npresentation of research projects. The guidelines are intended to help \\r\\nresearchers to\\r\\nidentify their biometric or statistical needs.\\r\\n<br><br><\\/p>\",\"es\":\"<p>Esta es la primera de la serie de gu\\u00edas destinadas a apoyar al personal involucrado en proyectos de investigaci\\u00f3n para identificar sus necesidades biom\\u00e9tricas o estad\\u00edsticas. Esta es una gu\\u00eda introductoria y proporciona una visi\\u00f3n general m\\u00e1s general de las \\u00e1reas de un proyecto de investigaci\\u00f3n donde es importante comprender las ideas estad\\u00edsticas.<\\/p><p>De la introducci\\u00f3n<\\/p><p>\\\"Sin suficiente confianza en la estad\\u00edstica, los investigadores usan a menudo dise\\u00f1os conservadores, fundamentalmente para asegurarse un an\\u00e1lisis simple. Aunque esto es algunas veces apropiado, la introducci\\u00f3n de mejoras sencillas pueden resultar en encuestas o experimentos m\\u00e1s informativos por el mismo costo. Por ejemplo, se pueden tomar medidas que no son adecuadas a los objetivos del estudio y en consecuencia, no son posteriormente analizadas. La recolecci\\u00f3n de datos puede llegar a requerir una parte importante del tiempo dedicado al estudio si ello no se planifica adecuadamente con anterioridad. El an\\u00e1lisis puede ser apresurado, usando programas inform\\u00e1ticos inapropiados, debido a la presi\\u00f3n de producir resultados r\\u00e1pidamente. El estudio se concluye de esa forma, con el convencimiento de que a\\u00fan puede aprenderse de los datos, pero ya est\\u00e1 por agotarse el financiamiento y los problemas con el manejo de los datos hacen dif\\u00edcil su acceso a\\u00fan para futuros investigadores dentro del mismo pa\\u00eds donde fue hecho el estudio.<br>En la presente gu\\u00eda consideramos esas etapas, desde la planificaci\\u00f3n hasta la presentaci\\u00f3n. Su objetivo es animar al investigador a pensar acerca de los aspectos cruciales de la planificaci\\u00f3n, el an\\u00e1lisis y la interpretaci\\u00f3n de los datos.\\\"<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>El SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC.<\\/p>\"}',7,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23\\\\/2019-10-10_11:57:23_statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_11:57:23_statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Statistical_Guidelines_for_Natural_Resources_Projects.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":182432,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\", \"es\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23\\\\/2019-10-10_15:01:07_guia1.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:01:07_guia1.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia1.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":117330,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'1998-03-01','2019-10-10 11:57:24','2019-10-30 07:48:23',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23/statistical-guides-statistical-guidelines-for-natural-resources-projects_2019-10-10_11:57:23.zip',1),(440,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Using Excel for Statistics - Tips and Warnings\"}','statistical-guides-using-excel-for-statistics-tips-and-warnings_2019-10-10_12:24:14',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A booklet aimed at staff working withing research projects, providing information about using Excel for statistical work. Although Excel can be very helpful for data manipulation, summary, tabulation and its graphical capabilities, and has the benefit of being more familiar to the average user, it can result in poor practice if not used optimally, and it is not ideal for more advanced statistical methods such as ANOVA.&nbsp; This guide helps the user understand how and when to make use of Excel within a research project context and contains tips and warnings for avoiding problems.\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">From the introduction:<\\/span><\\/p><p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>\\\"The availability of spreadsheets that include facilities for data management and\\r\\nstatistical analysis has changed the way people manage their information. Their\\r\\npower and ease of use have given new opportunities for data analysis, but they have\\r\\nalso brought new problems and challenges for the user.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>[...]<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>In this guide we point out strengths, and weaknesses, when using Excel for statistical\\r\\ntasks. We include data management, descriptive statistics, pivot tables, probability\\r\\ndistributions, hypothesis tests, analysis of variance and regression. We give the\\r\\nsalient points as tips and warnings. For those who need more than Excel we list some\\r\\nof the ways that users can add to its facilities, or use Excel in combination with other\\r\\nsoftware. Finally we give our conclusions about the use of Excel for statistical work.\\\"<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\"}',7,13,NULL,0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-using-excel-for-statistics-tips-and-warnings_2019-10-10_12:24:14\\\\/2019-10-10_12:24:14_using-excel-for-statistics.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_12:24:14_using-excel-for-statistics.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Using_Excel_for_Statistics.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":361041,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2000-11-01','2019-10-10 12:24:14','2019-10-10 12:24:16',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-using-excel-for-statistics-tips-and-warnings_2019-10-10_12:24:14/statistical-guides-using-excel-for-statistics-tips-and-warnings_2019-10-10_12:24:14.zip',0),(441,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Writing up Research: A statistical perspective\"}','writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_13:57:37',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><\\/p><p>A guide on how to write up a data analysis for data-related research work, aimed at research scientists who may not be experienced users of statistics. It could also be useful for a more experiences researcher writing up results from studies involving multidisciplinary teams and objectives.<br><\\/p>The guide is focused on natural resources research, but the general principles are also relevant in other types of research. The aim is to\\r\\nprovide guidance on how to report results of investigations in a way that clearly\\r\\ndemonstrates the evidence base for research recommendations. <p><\\/p><p>This guide was produced by the Statistical Services Centre of the University of Reading with funding from DFID\'s Forestry Research Programme (FRP), Project ZF0183, as part of work to support research scientists at DFID with the statistical aspects of research projects. <br><\\/p>\"}',7,13,NULL,0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_13:57:37\\\\/2019-10-10_13:57:37_writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_13:57:37_writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Writing up research - a statistical perspective.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":350474,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2006-01-01','2019-10-10 13:57:37','2019-10-10 14:01:43',NULL,NULL,'files/writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_13:57:37/writing-up-research-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_13:57:37.zip',0),(442,'{\"en\":\"Statistical Guides: Writing Research Protocols: A statistical perspective\"}','statistical-guides-writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_14:35:01',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/p><div class=\\\"page\\\" title=\\\"Page 3\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"layoutArea\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<div class=\\\"column\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>A guide written for researcher scientists on writing good research protocols to plan and record project activities. <\\/p><p><span style=\\\"font-weight: bold;\\\">From the introduction:<\\/span><br><\\/p><p>\\\"In carrying a project from inception to completion, one link in the chain is the analysis of data\\r\\ncollected. If the material for analysis is inadequately organised or documented, this process\\r\\nmay be confused, or done badly. This guide aims to reduce such problems at an early stage.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t\\t<p>The material below probably has most to say to relatively inexperienced researchers, such as\\r\\nPh.D. students taking on particular activities within larger projects. Of course we are well-\\r\\naware that experienced project leaders already do much of what we are suggesting, insofar as\\r\\nit is relevant to the special circumstances of their project, but we hope that at least some of\\r\\nour points will be helpful to them too.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>[...]<br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\r\\n<p>This guide is a plea for more systematic and more complete recording of planning information, in the form of a protocol, to ensure that the project process \\u2013 especially the analysis stage \\u2013 can be efficient and effective, and that the legacy of the project does not languish unusable after the exercise has ended.\\\"<\\/p><p>This guide was produced by the Statistical Services Centre of the \\r\\nUniversity of Reading with funding from DFID\'s Forestry Research \\r\\nProgramme (FRP), Project ZF0183, as part of work to support research \\r\\nscientists at DFID with the statistical aspects of research projects. <\\/p>\"}',7,13,NULL,0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/statistical-guides-writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_14:35:01\\\\/2019-10-10_14:35:01_writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_14:35:01_writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Writing_Research_Protocols-a_statistical_perspective.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":1155186,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2006-01-01','2019-10-10 14:35:01','2019-10-10 14:35:03',NULL,NULL,'files/statistical-guides-writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_14:35:01/statistical-guides-writing-research-protocols-a-statistical-perspective_2019-10-10_14:35:01.zip',0),(443,'{\"en\":\"Lineamientos para archivo de datos: lecciones de un estudio de caso\"}','lineamientos-para-archivo-de-datos-lecciones-de-un-estudio-de-caso_2019-10-10_15:13:40',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>Esto es parte de una serie de gu\\u00edas destinadas a apoyar al personal involucrado en proyectos de investigaci\\u00f3n para identificar sus necesidades biom\\u00e9tricas o estad\\u00edsticas.<br><\\/p><p>De la introducci\\u00f3n:<\\/p><p>\\\"Una parte integral de muchos proyectos de investigaci\\u00f3n es la recolecci\\u00f3n de datos de encuestas o experimentos, a un considerable costo en tiempo y esfuerzo. Se debe tener gran cuidado para producir datos de buena calidad, tanto en la etapa de recolecci\\u00f3n como en la de introducci\\u00f3n en la computadora, pero usualmente se hace poco \\u00e9nfasis en asegurarse que los datos est\\u00e9n disponibles para otros usuarios, en forma tal que permita que los datos sean realmente comprendidos y usados correctamente en subsecuentes estudios. Idealmente la creaci\\u00f3n de un archivo tiene que estar integrada con el trabajo en progreso de un proyecto, m\\u00e1s que ser una idea tard\\u00eda en el momento en que el equipo de investigaci\\u00f3n se ha dispersado.<br>Esta breve gu\\u00eda pretende hacer conciencia sobre la importancia de conservar los datos de un proyecto, discutir las caracter\\u00edsticas que hacen un buen archivo de datos y ofrecer un ejemplo de un archivo exitoso.<br><p>Esta es una serie de gu\\u00edas para t\\u00e9cnicos\\r\\ninvolucrados en el desarrollo y la presentaci\\u00f3n de proyectos\\r\\nde investigaci\\u00f3n. Las gu\\u00edas tienen el\\r\\nprop\\u00f3sito de ayudar a los investigadores a identificar sus\\r\\nnecesidades estad\\u00edsticas o biom\\u00e9tricas.\\\"<\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>La serie de gu\\u00edas biom\\u00e9tricas fueron producidas originalmente \\r\\n  en idioma ingl\\u00e9s, por el <a>Centro de Servicios Estad\\u00edsticos (SSC)<\\/a> de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.rdg.ac.uk\\/\\\">Universidad de Reading<\\/a>, para el Departamento para \\r\\n  el Desarrollo Internacional (DFID) del Gobierno del Reino Unido.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>El SSC y el DFID aprobaron la solicitud de la <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.una.ac.cr\\\">Universidad Nacional (UNA, Costa Rica)<\\/a>\\r\\npara proceder a la traducci\\u00f3n, edici\\u00f3n,\\r\\npublicaci\\u00f3n y distribuci\\u00f3n de las gu\\u00edas en\\r\\nidioma castellano, con el prop\\u00f3sito de extender sus\\r\\nbeneficios a proyectos e investigadores de pa\\u00edses\\r\\nhispanohablantes, fundamentalmente del \\u00e1rea de Centro\\r\\nAm\\u00e9rica y el Caribe. El <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.catie.ac.cr\\/\\\">Centro Agron\\u00f3mico Tropical de\\r\\nInvestigaci\\u00f3n y Ense\\u00f1anza (CATIE, Costa Rica)<\\/a> ha\\r\\nfinanciado la publicaci\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana de\\r\\nlas cinco primeras gu\\u00edas. La traducci\\u00f3n y\\r\\nedici\\u00f3n de la versi\\u00f3n castellana estuvo a cargo del\\r\\n<a href=\\\"mailto: camachoj@sol.racsa.co.cr\\\">Dr. Jorge\\r\\nCamacho-Sandoval<\\/a>, Escuela de Ciencias Agrarias, Universidad\\r\\nNacional y fue supervisada por <a href=\\\"mailto: c.e.barahona@reading.ac.uk\\\">Carlos Barahona<\\/a> del\\r\\nSSC.<\\/p><\\/p>\"}',7,13,NULL,0,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/lineamientos-para-archivo-de-datos-lecciones-de-un-estudio-de-caso_2019-10-10_15:13:40\\\\/2019-10-10_15:13:40_guia2.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-10_15:13:40_guia2.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Guia2.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":95991,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'1999-01-01','2019-10-10 15:13:41','2019-10-10 15:13:42',NULL,NULL,'files/lineamientos-para-archivo-de-datos-lecciones-de-un-estudio-de-caso_2019-10-10_15:13:40/lineamientos-para-archivo-de-datos-lecciones-de-un-estudio-de-caso_2019-10-10_15:13:40.zip',0),(444,'{\"en\":\"Patton\\u2019s 40 Purposeful Sampling Strategies - Infographic\"}','pattons-40-purposeful-sampling-strategies-infographic_2019-10-15_11:09:01',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>An infographic, created by Sara Vaca based on information from Michael Q. Patton\'s \'<span style=\\\"font-style: italic;\\\"><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/uk.sagepub.com\\/en-gb\\/eur\\/qualitative-research-evaluation-methods\\/book232962\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Qualitative Research and Evaluation Methods<\\/a><\\/span>\' (Patton, 2015).&nbsp; It illustrates 40 sampling strategies for use in qualitative studies. The strategies are described and shown visually in simplistic diagram form, making them easier to understand quickly. They are also categorised into types of sampling for different kinds of data requirements.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>This graphic could be a very helpful source of suggestions or a quick reference guide for researchers, students or anyone interested in designing a qualitative study or survey. It would also be a useful handout or shareble reference to accompany training such as in a workshop or webinar.<br><\\/p>\"}',7,22,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.saravaca.com/project/pattons-40-purposeful-sampling-strategies/\"}]}',NULL,'2018-04-01','2019-10-15 11:09:01','2019-10-15 12:42:34',NULL,NULL,'files/pattons-40-purposeful-sampling-strategies-infographic_2019-10-15_11:09:01/pattons-40-purposeful-sampling-strategies-infographic_2019-10-15_11:09:01.zip'