a.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://medium.com/@accountability/community-led-research-is-what-todays-development-needs-global-community-action-guides-to-40246a2e9b71\"}]}',NULL,'2018-12-01','2019-10-22 10:19:19','2019-10-23 13:51:57',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(456,'{\"en\":\"Global Community Action Guides\"}','global-community-action-guides_2019-10-22_10:36:11',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>This pack contains three booklets on community-led research created by the International Accountability Project (IAP).<\\/p><p>These resources are focused on development projects, and contain resources and advice that would be very relevant and valuable for anyone working with or alongside an FRN or similar community project. <\\/p><p>The booklets contain practical advice, including guidance about safety and risks involved in community action, suggested activities and questions, and a checklist breaking down the steps of the research process. <br><\\/p><p>From the <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/medium.com\\/@accountability\\/community-led-research-is-what-todays-development-needs-global-community-action-guides-to-40246a2e9b71\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">website<\\/a> description:<\\/p><p>\\\"Community members, organizers, and civil society representatives can use these materials to mobilize communities, document harms and rights violations, and advance community-led campaigns. <\\/p><p>[...]<\\/p><p>There are three booklets in this Community Action Guide:<\\/p><ol><li>The <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bit.ly\\/guideiap\\\" class=\\\"ar ce mw mx my mz\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\"><span class=\\\"ld md\\\">Community Action Guide on Community-led Research<\\/span><\\/a>\\r\\n provides clear and detailed guidance on each step of the research \\r\\nprocess, and suggests activities and tools to build capacity and advance\\r\\n community-led methods. This booklet also includes information on safety\\r\\n and security, and the stories of three community organizers who used \\r\\ncommunity-led research to support community advocacy.<br><br><\\/li><li><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bit.ly\\/checklistiap\\\" class=\\\"ar ce mw mx my mz\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\"><span class=\\\"ld md\\\">We\\u2019re Experts Too! A Checklist to Support Community-led Research<\\/span><\\/a>\\r\\n presents a concise overview of community-led research. Breaking down \\r\\nthe process into clear steps from preparation to implementation to \\r\\nadvocacy, the Checklist can be used on its own, or as a supplement to \\r\\nthe <span class=\\\"ld md\\\">Community Action Guide on Community-Led Research. <\\/span>This booklet also includes links to resources and tools to further illustrate each step.<br><br><\\/li><li>The <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bit.ly\\/surveyiap\\\" class=\\\"ar ce mw mx my mz\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\"><span class=\\\"ld md\\\">Survey Template for Community-led Research<\\/span><\\/a><span class=\\\"ld md\\\"> <\\/span>contains\\r\\n instructions and sample survey questions that have been developed and \\r\\nused by communities and civil society partners in 14 countries around \\r\\nthe world. These questions were designed to help communities explore \\r\\ntheir direct experiences and expertise about the process and impact of \\r\\ndestructive development projects, and to identify their ideas and \\r\\npriorities for their visions of development. This template can be \\r\\nadapted and translated to fit different contexts, with an editable \\r\\nversion available for download <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/accountabilityproject.org\\/wp-content\\/uploads\\/2019\\/01\\/Community-Led-Research-Survey-Template.docx\\\" class=\\\"ar ce mw mx my mz\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\" rel=\\\"noopener\\\">here<\\/a>.\\\"<\\/li><\\/ol>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/ccab6917763ee62c86662719388fc3e0.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://accountabilityproject.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IAP-Comm-Act-Guide-web.pdf\"}, {\"path\": \"https://accountabilityproject.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IAP-Comm-Act-Checklist-web.pdf\"}, {\"path\": \"https://accountabilityproject.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IAP-Comm-Act-Survey-web.pdf\"}, {}]}',NULL,'2018-12-01','2019-10-22 10:36:12','2019-10-23 13:51:44',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(457,'{\"en\":\"Ethical photography guidelines\"}','ethical-photography-guidelines_2019-10-23_13:16:27',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>ILRI research\\r\\npublishing\\r\\nprocedure 10:\\r\\nethical\\r\\nphotography\\r\\nguidelines.<\\/p><p>An excellent overview of the ethical considerations associated with using photography in fieldwork.<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p>\"}',8,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://hdl.handle.net/10568/89055\"}]}',NULL,'2018-02-01','2019-10-23 13:16:28','2019-10-30 07:50:10',NULL,NULL,'files/ethical-photography-guidelines_2019-10-23_13:16:27/ethical-photography-guidelines_2019-10-23_13:16:27.zip',1),(458,'{\"en\":\"R package for calculating fertility and child mortality rates from DHS data\"}','r-package-for-calculating-fertility-and-child-mortality-rates-from-dhs-data_2019-10-24_15:13:07',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A useful package has been designed with the intention of making it easier to calculate key fertility and child mortality indicators, key to the SDGs and general health\\/demographic tracking in developing countries. <\\/p><p>As the DHS datasets are quite cumbersome and often very large (tens of thousands of observations of over 1000 variables sometimes), hopefully this package will aid in smoothing this process.&nbsp; It includes functions for calculating total fertility rate (TFR), age-specific fertility rates (ASFRs),&nbsp; child mortality rate (CMR), neonatal mortality rate (NMMR) and more.&nbsp; It is specifically designed with DHS datasets in mind.&nbsp;<\\/p>\"}',25,19,'cover_images/troves/c34bcc21493cd6cccd807f67bc5f7eb8.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://rdrr.io/cran/DHS.rates/\"}]}',NULL,'2019-10-01','2019-10-24 15:13:08','2019-10-24 16:30:56',NULL,NULL,'files/r-package-for-calculating-fertility-and-child-mortality-rates-from-dhs-data_2019-10-24_15:13:07/r-package-for-calculating-fertility-and-child-mortality-rates-from-dhs-data_2019-10-24_15:13:07.zip',1),(459,'{\"en\":\"Uso de la fotograf\\u00eda en la investigaci\\u00f3n\"}','uso-de-la-fotografia-en-la-investigacion_2019-10-28_13:45:02',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<div>La fotograf\\u00eda (tanto fija como en video) puede desempe\\u00f1ar un papel importante en el trabajo de campo y la recopilaci\\u00f3n de datos, as\\u00ed como en la gesti\\u00f3n y an\\u00e1lisis de datos.<\\/div><div><br><\\/div><div>Este recurso ofrece algunas ideas sobre diferentes formas de usar la fotograf\\u00eda en el campo, que incluyen:<\\/div><div><br><\\/div><ol><li>Fotoelicitaci\\u00f3n<\\/li><li>Fotograf\\u00eda participativa<\\/li><li>Uso de fotograf\\u00edas para explicar anomal\\u00edas.<\\/li><li>Incluye algunos detalles sobre consideraciones \\u00e9ticas.<\\/li><\\/ol>\"}',8,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/uso-de-la-fotografia-en-la-investigacion_2019-10-28_13:45:02\\\\/2019-10-28_13:45:02_uso-de-la-fotografia-en-la-investigacion.docx\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-10-28_13:45:02_uso-de-la-fotografia-en-la-investigacion.docx\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Uso de la fotografi\\\\u0301a en la investigacio\\\\u0301n.docx\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"docx\\\",\\\"size\\\":199426,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2019-10-01','2019-10-28 13:45:03','2019-10-31 12:43:54',NULL,NULL,'files/uso-de-la-fotografia-en-la-investigacion_2019-10-28_13:45:02/uso-de-la-fotografia-en-la-investigacion_2019-10-28_13:45:02.zip',1),(460,'{\"en\":\"Literature Reviews: Common Errors Made When Conducting a Literature Review\"}','literature-reviews-common-errors-made-when-conducting-a-literature-review_2019-10-31_16:24:21',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A useful discussion of common errors that can be easily avoided when conducting a literature review.<\\/p><p>In 12-minute video this Dr Michael Quinn Patton gives an explanation of what a literature review\\r\\n is and the purpose - explaining how it enables you to understand your \\r\\n\'intellectual heritage\', and where your research fits into and builds on work that has already been done. He lists common errors and provides practical advice on avoiding these and conducting a good-quality, robust literature review. <\\/p><p>The video would be helpful for students, researchers, and those involved in academia or wanting to better understand the process of academic research and writing. <br><\\/p>\"}',5,16,'cover_images/troves/b1ac40f6ca18b394f107374602c27463.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}',NULL,'2015-01-01','2019-10-31 16:24:21','2019-10-31 17:06:55',NULL,'NiDHOr3NHRA',NULL,1),(461,'{\"es\":\"Construcci\\u00f3n de Tipolog\\u00edas\"}','construccion-de-tipologias_2019-11-30_20:02:50',NULL,'{\"es\":\"<p>Para captar la variabilidad de los sistemas de explotaci\\u00f3n agropecuaria, las tipolog\\u00edas son una\\r\\nherramienta de uso frecuente. Las tipolog\\u00edas en investigaci\\u00f3n para proyectos de desarrollo se utilizan\\r\\npara obtener eficazmente los ajustes, mejores pol\\u00edticas e innovaciones que se requieren para el modelo\\r\\nde finca \\u00f3ptimo, con el fin de lograr los objetivos de Humidtropics.\\r\\nEl objetivo de este documento es proporcionar directrices para la construcci\\u00f3n de tipolog\\u00edas. El enfoque\\r\\ngeneral de tipolog\\u00eda que aqu\\u00ed se propone es combinar con estad\\u00edstica multivariante el conocimiento de\\r\\nexpertos obtenido a trav\\u00e9s de un enfoque participativo.<br><\\/p>\"}',28,13,NULL,1,'{\"es\": \"[]\"}','{\"es\": [{\"path\": \"http://humidtropics.cgiar.org/wp-content/uploads/downloads/2015/04/Typology-Guidelines-Espan%CC%83ol_v2.pdf\"}, {}]}',NULL,'2019-11-30','2019-11-30 20:02:50','2019-12-17 07:25:39','2019-12-17 07:25:39',NULL,NULL,0),(462,'{\"es\":\"Typology construction\"}','typology-construction_2019-11-30_20:04:44',NULL,'{\"es\":\"<p>Farming systems in the humid tropics exist across a wide variety of cultures and landscapes. The\\r\\nbiophysical, institutional, social and economic drivers differ between contexts, resulting in different\\r\\nresponses of farmers and communities between and within areas. Moreover, farms are in different\\r\\ndevelopment stages, and farmers have different skills and ambitions. Over time, these differences in\\r\\ndrivers and in farm features lead to temporal and spatial variability between and within farming systems.\\r\\nThe existing farming systems variability is challenging to fully comprehend, leading to partial\\r\\nrepresentation of reality. Various tools and methods (e.g. wealth rankings, farm typologies, distributions)\\r\\nhave been developed to understand and deal with farming systems diversity. When using these tools and\\r\\nmethods, a trade-off is made between the quality of representing reality and the level of detail required.\\r\\nAn often-used methodology to deal with variability and diversity is typology construction, i.e. the\\r\\ngrouping of farms\\/households.\\r\\nIn this document we provide guidelines for constructing typologies. Our objectives are to present a stepwise approach to structure this process, to provide practical advices and suggestions on useful\\r\\ntechniques and to raise awareness of opportunities and pitfalls that arise during typology construction.<br><\\/p>\"}',28,13,NULL,1,'{\"es\": \"[]\"}','{\"es\": [{\"path\": \"http://humidtropics.cgiar.org/wp-content/uploads/downloads/2015/04/Typology-guidelines_v2.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2019-11-30','2019-11-30 20:04:44','2019-12-17 07:25:32','2019-12-17 07:25:32',NULL,NULL,0),(463,'{\"en\":\"How to write an academic article that is interesting, reads smoothly and is globally relevant\"}','how-to-write-an-academic-article-that-is-interesting_2019-12-06_11:37:52',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p class=\\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\\"><span style=\\\"\\\\&quot;font-family:\\\" &quot;source=\\\"\\\" sans=\\\"\\\" pro&quot;,=\\\"\\\" sans-serif;=\\\"\\\" background-image:=\\\"\\\" initial;=\\\"\\\" background-position:=\\\"\\\" background-size:=\\\"\\\" background-repeat:=\\\"\\\" background-attachment:=\\\"\\\" background-origin:=\\\"\\\" background-clip:=\\\"\\\" initial;\\\\\\\"=\\\"\\\">This is a video that presents the personal experience of the author about how to successfully write an academic paper.<\\/span><\\/p><p class=\\\"\\\\&quot;MsoNormal\\\\&quot;\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family: &quot;Source Sans Pro&quot;, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Arial, &quot;Noto Sans&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; font-size: 1rem;\\\">It contains useful tips, real experience and is recommended for anyone planning to write an academic paper. It is really worth watching it!<\\/span><br><\\/p>\"}',1,16,'cover_images/troves/27579917a525ea3f2b73574d8cf4363a.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": null}','{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/how-to-write-an-academic-article-that-is-interesting_2019-12-06_11:37:52\\\\/2019-12-06_11:37:52_how-to-write-an-academic-article-1.mp4\\\",\\\"temp_path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/how-to-write-an-academic-article-that-is-interesting_2019-12-06_11:37:52\\\\/2019-12-06_11:37:52_how-to-write-an-academic-article-1.mp4\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-12-06_11:37:52_how-to-write-an-academic-article-1.mp4\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"How To Write An Academic Article 1.mp4\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"mp4\\\",\\\"size\\\":226350082,\\\"type_id\\\":3}]\"}','2019-12-01','2019-12-06 11:38:01','2019-12-06 13:05:34',NULL,'p71s9zvm3TU','files/how-to-write-an-academic-article-that-is-interesting_2019-12-06_11:37:52/how-to-write-an-academic-article-that-is-interesting_2019-12-06_11:37:52.zip',0),(464,'{\"en\":\"Guide to measuring farm input and output data\"}','guide-to-measuring-farm-input-and-output-data_2019-12-16_10:24:50',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p>A guide to measuring smallholder farm inputs a output data.&nbsp; Such data is often collected via a&nbsp; survey using recall, with farmers asked about quantities. Such data is often of poor quality.&nbsp; The guide describes factors to look at to predict if low quality data is likely. It then suggests alternative methods that could better information. It should be relevant to anyone who is contemplating using recall methods to collect farm input and output data.<br><\\/p>\"}',3,13,NULL,1,'{\"en\": \"[{\\\"path\\\":\\\"files\\\\/guide-to-measuring-farm-input-and-output-data_2019-12-16_10:24:50\\\\/2019-12-16_10:24:50_coe-et-at-2019-guide-to-input-output-data.pdf\\\",\\\"storedName\\\":\\\"2019-12-16_10:24:50_coe-et-at-2019-guide-to-input-output-data.pdf\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Coe et at 2019 guide to input output data.pdf\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"pdf\\\",\\\"size\\\":1016665,\\\"type_id\\\":1}]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"http://www.worldagroforestry.org/downloads/Publications/PDFS/MN19067.pdf\"}]}',NULL,'2019-12-01','2019-12-16 10:24:51','2019-12-17 07:25:20',NULL,NULL,'files/guide-to-measuring-farm-input-and-output-data_2019-12-16_10:24:50/guide-to-measuring-farm-input-and-output-data_2019-12-16_10:24:50.zip',1),(465,'{\"en\":\"SAS2: A Guide to Collaborative Inquiry and Social Engagement\"}','sas2-a-guide-to-collaborative-inquiry-and-social-engagement_2020-01-02_15:18:03',NULL,'{\"en\":\"<p><b>From the website:<\\/b><br><\\/p><p><i>SAS2: A Guide to Collaborative Inquiry and Social Engagement<\\/i>\\r\\n represents a significant international effort to support the creation \\r\\nand mobilization of practical, authentic knowledge for social change. \\r\\nThe guiding principle behind SAS2 (Social Analysis Systems, <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.sas2.net\\/\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">www.sas2.net<\\/a>)\\r\\n is that group dialogue and social inquiry are crucial for local and \\r\\nglobal development. Social issues must be addressed socially and in a \\r\\nmultistakeholder mode, not by private interests and experts alone, and \\r\\nthe insights that emerge fully integrated into processes of knowledge \\r\\nproduction, planning, and decision-making.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Part 1 outlines the concepts and skillful means needed to support \\r\\nmultistakeholder dialogue. It also provides detailed instructions on how\\r\\n to integrate and ground collaborative inquiry in the projects, plans, \\r\\nevaluations and activities of multiple stakeholders. Part 2 presents a \\r\\nselection of techniques for collaborative inquiry and examples of \\r\\nreal-life applications in South Asia and Latin America. The examples \\r\\nfocus on a range of issues including land tenure, local economic \\r\\ndevelopment, agriculture, forestry, fisheries, and organizational \\r\\ndevelopment.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>This book will be an invaluable resource for researchers, \\r\\nfacilitators and activists working with people to solve problems and \\r\\nsupport inclusive inquiry and decision-making. It will also be useful to\\r\\n scholars and academics studying and teaching participatory action \\r\\nresearch in the Social Sciences.<\\/p>\"}',7,13,'cover_images/troves/535f841d97692a508c906b68201e60f9.jpg',1,'{\"en\": \"[]\"}','{\"en\": [{\"path\": \"https://www.idrc.ca/en/book/sas2-guide-collaborative-inquiry-and-social-engagement?PublicationID=108\"}]}',NULL,'2008-01-01','2020-01-02 15:18:04','2020-01-06 10:56:26',NULL,NULL,'files/sas2-a-guide-to-collaborative-inquiry-and-social-engagement_2020-01-02_15:18:03/sas2-a-guide-to-collaborative-inquiry-and-social-engagement_2020-01-02_15:18:03.zip',1);
